The building has amazing architecture perfect for taking photographs. There are multiple art showcases of paintings and sculptures that change from time to time. A must when you visit Mexico City if you are a photographer", 'time': 1578544600}, {'author_name': 'Teacher David de la Peña', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/108619578506191284136/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GiRlHZm06VbvPU9y91ukHvGJyNQMN5x2a1VABaJIQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '6 months ago', 'text': 'It is an excellent place to admire art and the architecture.  There are temporary and permanent exhibitions. It\'s opening was in 1982 and the re-opening in the year 2000. At the entrance, outside the building, there is the piece of art "Little Horse", a metallic sculpture from 1802, created by the Spanish Manuel Tolsa, weighing 45,000 kilograms which represents Carlos IV as a Roman emperor. After many moving, It was placed there in 1979.', 'time': 1586080198}]

column15:
[{'author_name': 'Andi', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/109334555965799037661/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-My3SoB9IaFA/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/AMZuucnvxHOL9--kXWZ6K0HnXfSbh-BOtQ/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4/photo.jpg', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '7 months ago', 'text': 'If you saw the movie “Frida” this is a must stop on your visit to Mexico City because actual scenes were filmed here and it will give you a better understanding of how Frida and Diego lived.

But that’s not the only reason to visit this museum. It’s architecture and surroundings will immerse you in the life of the very famous Diego Rivera. The architecture of the place speaks for itself. It evokes the modernists of the time incorporating the artist’s request of a house formed of two bodies.

The scale of the spaces and stairs are off considering the size of Diego being his workspace the only one that seems coherent to his stature. The fully openable windows In The context of San Angel (Neighbourhood where it’s located) allows you to imagine life at the time Diego and Frida inhabited it.

Check for temporary visits before going! Some areas of the house might be closed if there is no exhibit.', 'time': 1583250048}, {'author_name': 'José Carlos G.', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/113247287526301708270/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GjJCcZ_Kqv3zzt3ycNk4YnZr1AWegTW0QK53U2it6E=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '6 months ago', 'text': "This museum is the former home and art studio of Diego Rivera and Frida Kahlo built in 1932. Both buildings are connected by a tiny  bridge at roof level. Diego's is larger than  Frida's, at the distance it resembles their physical look, like the couple standing together.  It has minimalistic decoration and furniture except for the main area of Diego's studio that has tons of mexican art crafts, pottery and art tools.  Back of the main buildings there's another one built for the wife of the architect that created this wonderful venue, Juan O'Gorman. For taking pictures a MX $35 Permit needs to be bought. It is not a crowded place so it can be enjoyed calmly, the cactus fence gives the facade a unique look. The architecture is delightful. There is not original art of either of both artists except for a Dolores del Rio, famous film mexican actress, oil painting made by Diego. There is no parking lot, souvenir store or coffee shop. Entrance is free on Sundays.", 'time': 1584240082}, {'author_name': 'juan carlos C', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/113234472771552750376/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GgBi-Cn8iRyN8wXoH3sVBEBKmvqNwtBR3cC3ZJOUhQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '7 months ago', 'text': 'Wonderful place, museum of history of Diego and Frida.
Better tha the casa azul.', 'time': 1581894396}, {'author_name': 'Sarah Tano', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/114833802882892705765/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GhdGPthMj9eK4ZdO5YHK5R5gPAMengpQ2SCKeWVUw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 4, 'relative_time_description': '10 months ago', 'text': 'The buildings and studio are nice but be prepared for the army of security guards standing over you in every room. Often they were in the way of photos. Only takes about 20 minutes to go through and was 35 pesos to get in plus 30 for a photo pass.', 'time': 1574994867}, {'author_name': 'A A', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/110743342917975863267/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/-JUQLrRftEjg/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/AMZuuckb2iBss7AXJUDq4l7FnhzI4Pkkgw/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4/photo.jpg', 'rating': 4, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': "I enjoyed looking at all the exhibits available for Diego.  Very interesting.  His bedroom was very simply decorated.  The studios of both Frida and Diego we're very large and separated.  The Frida exhibit was unavailable, but guests were still able to access the structure where some photography was viewable.

They offer a brochure which has copies of archived photography of the property.

You must pay extra (30 pesos) for capturing photographs.  It's worth the small price, especially Diego's work.

4 stars since the entire exhibit wasn't available.  But, they do earn you before you pay the admission.", 'time': 1558136914}]

column15:
[{'author_name': 'Paul Donovan', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/105975222390273438184/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-jtRmoHbqZDU/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/AMZuuck9w_D_w9vmDDJzPLEyO3YPR3ZHfw/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5/photo.jpg', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '9 months ago', 'text': 'This is one amazing place and so well presented and preserved. Gives us an idea of how advanced the people were in the past and how inventive they were using available materials to make things work back then. The displays are so well done. You need quite some time to do it justice.', 'time': 1576817387}, {'author_name': 'Daniel Förster', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/112908955699178451942/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Gi6fBhjcc2NixBvrjtnXcDqTbCdCs9fJpBE1MjnfA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '7 months ago', 'text': "Extremely impressive! This is the pinnacle of Aztec culture, ready to be discovered, layer by layer.

It's exciting to be able to both see the ruins of 6 (of a total of 7) layers of the biggest twin temple of old Tenochtitlan, and have the museum exhibit and describe even more pieces from the whole of the large Aztec Empire as well as all of Mesoamerican trade partners.

There are trade pieces, luxury items, and general goods from the deserts of the north to the jungles of the south. There are big stones depicting goddesses and mythological creatures of Mesoamerican cultures and history (not just of Aztec origin, as they shared a lot of their gods and mythology with other cultures).

I'd wish for way more English explanation!! Still, it's 5 stars. Amazing and a must see for everyone coming to Mexico.", 'time': 1583686757}, {'author_name': 'Prashant', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/114649993195702473413/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Gi46gXVYo-bpWI3Tr3PFcfuMZibYIYn7EFYgPY6=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '8 months ago', 'text': 'A reminder of how close the ancient world is to the modern. An old centre of the city right in the middle of the present day Mexico city. The outer compound is actual ground zero of the main temple of the Mexica people. Further in there is an indoor air Conditioned museum that houses all the artefacts in 8 separate rooms which take you on a journey around how life was for the people then. Some ancient relics have been found as early as 2006. A golden piece of history. One drawback I saw was there was no audio guide. Plus some exhibits did not have any English details which was frustrating.', 'time': 1581219399}, {'author_name': 'Alexandra Woolsey-Puffer', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/113184292365006318561/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GgaFmp73eQwsSgWg2HmAoizOscGpd9ALdXemDemAw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': 'So you really do have to visit the site.

The ruins are incredible and there are English texts to explain what you are looking at.

The museum part is a bit of a mishmash and lacking much explanation in English, so for non-Spanish-speaking visitors it’s kind of a wash - a bunch of artifacts with no context.

I cruised though pretty quickly because it just didn’t hold up next to the spectacular ruins and I didn’t really know what I was looking at.', 'time': 1565454436}, {'author_name': 'Stephen Michael Fox Jr', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/103446137287630009095/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GguT50ZN8ZHH83Ve5VG7NVECx3QyNeAIhG934-GRgY=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '10 months ago', 'text': "Awesome archaeological site & museum  right off the City's main square / Zocalo.  You are provided access to walk amongst the ruins at the epicenter of the former indigenous Aztec empire's sacred temple of Hueteocalli.  It's amazing to be there in person and realize what once stood all around you.  The museum inside is well appointed with many informative exhibits and models of the former indigenous capital city.", 'time': 1575347074}]

Very reminiscent to a Farmers market in France !', 'time': 1596237530}, {'author_name': 'Alexander Burg', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/116588249844866069433/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GjeE2MUgTHc7AHMoid85U-gRLkrYEs_d2xm59IK=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '11 months ago', 'text': 'Such a cool market.

They have so many different types of groceries from spices, veggies, flowers, meats, fish. Also a few places to eat too.

You can buy items here like for your house too.', 'time': 1573018156}, {'author_name': 'Jacob Thomas', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/105209665361388451851/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Gg-eG5RX2wJ0A3CueCk6Yu35nxTxO3jGwB8-P01=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '7 months ago', 'text': 'Besides having a great amount of local vendors selling crafts, home remedy items, kitchen goods and supplies, flowers, etc...the foooooood! Whether you’re looking for raw cuts of meat, poultry or fish to bring home or to sit down and eat while you’re there, Mercado Medellin will do you right. And as a long time resident of Michoacán, I can tell you these carnitas and chicharrones are pretty darn good. Enjoy! 😋', 'time': 1583759473}]

[{'author_name': 'Francis XIV', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/105146723054500211385/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GgOLGzPGVKXIxxARcjf2cAOqMLX47MWKCz1MD3hRQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '2 months ago', 'text': 'She’s beauty she’s sublime, this place is so Devine.. worth a visit any time of day or night.', 'time': 1596480296}, {'author_name': 'Niurka Perez', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/102037722084994380631/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Gi82sSvBy9NHl0ouPVxOGHnnnIZaZutc-En9y2K6A=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '2 months ago', 'text': 'this is a stunning church, beautiful taken to the next level, if you are visiting mexico city you will probably visit the zocalo plaza, this church is just next to the plaza, entrance is free and you will be happy you decided to go, really worthy the time.', 'time': 1595898380}, {'author_name': 'michael peltzman', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/117573602532707223421/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Giwppy9leKFLA8DQFMaArroX7n91UVlcPVLW72LL3o=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '3 weeks ago', 'text': 'Beautiful. The main sanctuary has 15 smaller chapels. There are 2 organs inside the sanctuary that are over 300 years old. It was very impressive.', 'time': 1599850009}, {'author_name': 'Edouard JOURDAN', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/101162508288924831849/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GjtVGxNIeeQ1ksyi3lya_kj73FJKK4T7Pqa_g89=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '4 weeks ago', 'text': 'A very unique cathedral. Ideal place for meditation. The baroco spanish style provides a thick mystical atmosphere.', 'time': 1599623898}, {'author_name': 'Kadri Forbes', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/100198765691846528767/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-HNN91i25e9g/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/AMZuuckPGSsWaipitFzsI4ez0EEyqBzvdA/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo/photo.jpg', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '8 months ago', 'text': 'I must say,there is always something ,for everyone in this unique place , for time after time I have been  traveling to Mexico City and I feel so,welcome and above all ,is like you are in Europe,from the historic buildings to the vast amount of unique Architecture setting,is just by far sooo much to do there.
So,I would recommend this to anyone who appreciate history and so on,especially,your money.
Go there,and visit the museum,to the dining and the hospitality!
People are very friendly,and willing to assist you especially,if you don’t speak Spanish.', 'time': 1579807215}]

column15:
[{'author_name': 'Adriana Peña', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/101233337076381262519/reviews', 'language': 'es', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Gjob3OMDSPLV5Mo2YCoPhKuH1rmYuX8vt4L2NXKsg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3', 'rating': 2, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': 'Yo entré con muchas expectativas, ya que es un museo de historia de la bonita delegación Tlalpan, pero al entrar no encontré mucha historia, más que unos cuadros los cuales no decían mucho. Aparte de que está descuidado.
La gente sí es amable
Pero no cumple lo que promete.
Hablando del apartado de arte, es muy buena la exposición.', 'time': 1567561839}, {'author_name': 'De la Teja Organo Oscar Leonardo', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/113248721397939496907/reviews', 'language': 'es', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Giep_L4LF7KylnUFAGjEajgpuwknu2doCikofNlNw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '5 months ago', 'text': 'El\xa0Museo de Historia Natural\xa0es un\xa0museo de historia natural\xa0situado en la\xa0Ciudad de México. Está ubicado en la segunda sección del Bosque de\xa0Chapultepec. Mediante sus\xa0especímenes\xa0en exposición, el museo pretende ofrecer a sus visitantes un resumen de la historia del universo, de la Tierra y del ser humano. Fue fundado originalmente en 1790 como un\xa0gabinete de historia natural\xa0(en aquella época los\xa0gabinetes de curiosidades\xa0fueron los precedentes de los actuales museos). Más tarde, y en algunos momentos puntuales de su historia, ha ido cambiando tanto su nombre como su ubicación. Por ejemplo, de 1909 a 1964 se llamó «Museo Nacional de Historia Natural», pero en 1964 pasó a llamarse oficialmente «Museo de Historia Natural», nombre que ha conservado hasta la actualidad', 'time': 1588779950}, {'author_name': 'Jorge R', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/109210855005969789518/reviews', 'language': 'es', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GiKthmnLxNXxgDTY_ClXm9n9ajdUFg6GlqxHktATEI=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba7', 'rating': 3, 'relative_time_description': '2 years ago', 'text': 'Muy grande el lugar y poco aprovechado deberían de tener más exposiciones es un gran lugar y muy céntrico, una lastima que no tenga una exposición del propio lugar.', 'time': 1512626881}, {'author_name': 'Alfonso Alatorre García', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/114927605428341267110/reviews', 'language': 'es', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GhiZCuKL1Pm0RkPA2wUgaAX0MFwPD5v6ZIsOloP=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '11 months ago', 'text': 'El Taller la Imagen del Rinoceronte Es un magnífico espacio de creación y educación en las artes', 'time': 1573525122}, {'author_name': 'Eduardo Garcia', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/116604853955084877228/reviews', 'language': 'es', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-KozLm6FMsEg/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/AMZuucnz3uxC1bJ5g43fKrwk51aazpns7w/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5/photo.jpg', 'rating': 2, 'relative_time_description': '8 months ago', 'text': 'Solo pase por ahí', 'time': 1578869166}]

column15:
[{'author_name': 'Wayferer', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/113619414791279886766/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GhgayZCnGQ8LNrGpr7fqphLYoL-msXgfxTZky1WY6o=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5', 'rating': 3, 'relative_time_description': '3 months ago', 'text': "By the late 1970s, artist\xa0José Luis Cuevas\xa0had gathered a large collection of\xa0modern artworks\xa0by\xa0Latin American\xa0artists, with the aim of establishing a museum in his name. The collection was kept in the storage facilities of the Carrillo Gil Museum as Cuevas looked for a suitable location for the collection. Having been born in the\xa0historic Centro district\xa0of Mexico City, Cuevas wanted the museum to be located there.

After acquiring the historic Santa Inés Convent building in 1983, and relocating its residents, the\xa0adaptive reuse\xa0project began. Cuevas, along with government agencies and private supporters set to restore the building and perform archeological work. It revealed many of the much older construction elements of the convent. Restoration work was completed in 1988.

While it was primarily restored to its colonial era appearance, Cuevas had the convent's\xa0courtyard\xa0roofed with a plastic dome to have a contrary and modern element.[1]\xa0The complex was repaired under the patronage of the Marquis of La Cadena.[2]\xa0The entrance of the museum is located at 13 Academia Street, around the corner from the Santa Inés Church.[2]\xa0The courtyard's\xa0patio\xa0is dominated by a tall bronze sculpture named “La Giganta” (The Female Giant). Cuevas created this site specific sculpture for this space.[1]\xa0The statue is 8 metres (26\xa0ft) tall and weighs 8 tons.[3]

The José Luis Cuevas Museum opened in July 1992.[3]

CollectionsEdit

The principal exhibition rooms contain artworks by Cuevas, including a room dedicated to works by him and his wife artist Bertha Cuevas, and the 'Pablo Picasso room' displaying his drawings.

The museum's collection also includes many artworks by 19th and 20th century Mexican artists, including:\xa0Francisco Toledo,\xa0Juan Soriano, Vicente Rojo Almazán,\xa0Manuel Felguérez,\xa0Arnold Belkin, Gabriel Macotela. In addition it has works by international modern artists, including\xa0Roberto Matta, Fernando de Szys-Varo,\xa0Leonora Carrington\xa0and\xa0Remedios Varo.", 'time': 1592244565}, {'author_name': 'Timothy Williams', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/107267379049539784837/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Gh3Re78M5EUdwDWtIiuXZSJ-4qYDDGtJWFn6RIgmw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6', 'rating': 4, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': "This is a nice simple museum with El Gigante as the centerpiece. The layout is simple, in a square shape, with small rooms displaying different art pieces and some history. This museum is small insides and won't take all day to go there. I believe it was $10 pesos to enter.", 'time': 1562768310}, {'author_name': 'Jo Anna', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/108738696703454347479/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GiaG7zEqyJ1I4rdLgU1zTAIWsbAP0s5pt3l7adm=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 4, 'relative_time_description': '11 months ago', 'text': 'Very grand atrium space with some interesting art collages.', 'time': 1572933977}, {'author_name': 'Mike Cuenca', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/106517021809541112473/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GgVy78YqrqEgP3gR0G0W1lszQVQCtagGSXFtfPllQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5', 'rating': 3, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': 'I call this museum an homage to narcissism because it's a museum all about Jose Luis Cuevas -- founded by Jose Luis Cuevas. It's good, then, if you like his work. I think the giant sculpture,  "La Giganta," makes it worth a visit.', 'time': 1539364829}, {'author_name': 'Mike Rose', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/103611866596848960988/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-saaoNeAB1j8/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/AMZuucnb42CJkloDTu57IQG56bXtaBN89A/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo/photo.jpg', 'rating': 4, 'relative_time_description': '10 months ago', 'text': 'Marvellous on Sundays with its free concerts', 'time': 1574036176}]

column15:
[{'author_name': 'Ismael Garduño', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/115226583966015086015/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GhJwenK5M3wtAI902PmJTEM9h3t1KlnOGI-poaDSg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': 'A place with lots of working old clocks! The oldest is 500 years. It has sand, sun, water and candle clocks. And a nice collection of phonographs, gramophones and old radios', 'time': 1547343379}, {'author_name': 'Alejandra Castellanos', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/108653477382505278894/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GhFsSjwc6UqKq8Mxwu37WzgaiGUGsCDgbCSHe2t7Q=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '11 months ago', 'text': 'I loved this museum, the guide was really knowledgeable', 'time': 1571400252}, {'author_name': 'linkogecko', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/113464066670189490800/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Gie3zKk3ZUZD3uU2YXNVuuZj7FuzJmTLGBH-5sQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3', 'rating': 3, 'relative_time_description': '2 years ago', 'text': "Not bad, but not what I expected. The idea of a Time Museum is obviously vague, I'd say all museums ARE about time, with some maybe a little bit more than others (natural science museums are very time-heavy, for example). This one earns its name for its vast clock collection, dealing with timekeeping itself; and with time as the artifice of nostalgia and memory, other than old clocks, the museum showcases all manner of antiques, like gramophones, old video and photo cameras, etc. In fact, just looking at its collection and display it probably wouldn't come off as much more than a glorified antiques store.

But what makes it more than that is the decision to have all visits be guided tours where the guides explain the mechanisms at work, their historical context, technological progress and generally try and engage the visitors as much as possible. This is its greatest strength but it can sometimes backfire like it did in my visit. It makes perfect sense that a place full of gears and geeky stuf would attract shall we say, somewhat awkward people (like me) but when it ONLY attracts people like that and a few of them, and the guide isn't really reading the crowd, the whole guided tour side of it can fall flat. This is a weird criticism because the guide is doing their job the best way they know how but if it's not working, it's probably very difficult to find a way to change it a lot.

Having read other reviews it seems to me that the type of people who react most enthusiastically to this place are a). those who love antiques for the sake of what they are and b). older people for whom these aren't antiques, they're memories. Those of us who don't really fall into either category, and who are also a bit uncomfortable in improvised social situations, might not make the most of this place.", 'time': 1536360517}, {'author_name': 'Tom Tracy', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/109417366406150017215/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GgAdot_7K7cZ-J0RtJKvLj2DqvxXYSVyb_yelmbIA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3', 'rating': 3, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': 'I hoped for a history museum but it is an art exhibition.  Maybe your thing, not mine.  Only one item of historical interest, an ancient telephone.  The link between Tlalpan and Mexico City was the first in Latinoamérica.', 'time': 1555739778}, {'author_name': 'Daniel Espinosa', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/107700170921580027230/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Gi7UICN97-gq78rW8uxzWyx4NK4PhzeYBso5n_L=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba2', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '3 years ago', 'text': 'Great place to learn and enjoy the history behind antiques, which are preserved in great shape. There is a little but so beautiful store inside, and the cafe is superb. But even more enjoyable is the people you may find there, and the owner is such a great and kind person. This place is an amazing jewel of culture in our city!', 'time': 1489431181}]

column15:
[{'author_name': 'Michael Santonato', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/114602003226946816470/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GiKbhOu1jd6SBsi2CyTlxrOUXSfgnkN1RCvFaWUjg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '2 weeks ago', 'text': 'Wowwwwwww.... Magnificent experience here at this restaurant! We're from Canada and our friend brought us here.... we are sooooo thankful we came!!

They have amazing dishes and really above average service.  I mean the staff and servers were just excellent! We absolutely loved the food as well.

It just so happens that we came during the Mexican independence month and the unique seasonal dish called "Chile de en Nogada" (sic) was available and it was a knockout!  Thank you so much El Cardenal!

By the way, the decor is fantastic inside as well. Majestic and peaceful. Beautiful and lovely to be in.', 'time': 1600829262}, {'author_name': 'Jen Chang', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/104831633896308675281/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-_Eedg49IKC4/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/AMZuuclyY25c6P42OR6xKw97Y_Rb73ElRw/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3/photo.jpg', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '7 months ago', 'text': "Food excellent but what's best is the service. Cant get better than this 5 star service here. A must to try the bitter sweet hot chocolate. Price is very fair.", 'time': 1582520382}, {'author_name': 'Kurt Latray', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/100073067443482379189/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/-_UhelO7FNtE/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/AMZuuck1IkmLsPQu2r_GElGF32_U-cHLpA/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3/photo.jpg', 'rating': 4, 'relative_time_description': '6 months ago', 'text': 'This is a beautiful little restaurant adjacent to the bazaar de sábado.  The tables are large and accommodating. The entire facility is very beautiful! The food was exceptional and price was very good. The wait staff was very professional and attentive. Compared to many other "hole-in-the-wall" type restaurants in the area this was a breath of fresh air!', 'time': 1584287678}, {'author_name': 'Belina Garcia', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/100432432701723066253/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GjoHWrTfG9pg2w8tM2R9notTLGuxYKEhABVez-f5Q=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '9 months ago', 'text': "My favorite Mexican restaurant bar none. Consider that everything they s sell is made by them in their ranches, farms and kitchens since they control the production stream, it's amazing. Great versions of classic Mexican dishes done right from the bread, nata, meat and sauces. One of a kind! Lovely service, ambiance. Grew up with this place, especially the Hilton on the Alameda Central location brings back memories for me.", 'time': 1576246027}, {'author_name': 'Jazmin Rojas', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/105134418380120294400/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GjdFY3BNVQ5wZG2sUVjA7oQBL-9tSGi3hCtgCOK9w=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5', 'rating': 1, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': 'Went for breakfast with friends and family. Place is beautiful, very nicely decorated and very clean. Service was excellent, servers were very attentive and always looking after us. Food came out fast, food was tasty and had good presentation. My bad review is because at the end of the meal we asked for a glass of water, water smelled like sewage, it was disgusting, I just thought about all the food I ate and the water that was used to make it. We told the waiter and he didn’t say anything, just took the water away. This shouldn’t happen in a restaurant like this, this is unacceptable.
I always recommend this restaurant but I won’t anymore after this incident.', 'time': 1559236350}]

Cant get better than this 5 star service here. A must to try the bitter sweet hot chocolate. Price is very fair.", 'time': 1582520382}, {'author_name': 'Kurt Latray', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/100073067443482379189/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/-_UhelO7FNtE/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/AMZuuck1IkmLsPQu2r_GElGF32_U-cHLpA/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3/photo.jpg', 'rating': 4, 'relative_time_description': '6 months ago', 'text': 'This is a beautiful little restaurant adjacent to the bazaar de sábado.  The tables are large and accommodating. The entire facility is very beautiful! The food was exceptional and price was very good. The wait staff was very professional and attentive. Compared to many other "hole-in-the-wall" type restaurants in the area this was a breath of fresh air!', 'time': 1584287678}, {'author_name': 'Belina Garcia', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/100432432701723066253/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GjoHWrTfG9pg2w8tM2R9notTLGuxYKEhABVez-f5Q=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '9 months ago', 'text': "My favorite Mexican restaurant bar none. Consider that everything they s sell is made by them in their ranches, farms and kitchens since they control the production stream, it's amazing. Great versions of classic Mexican dishes done right from the bread, nata, meat and sauces. One of a kind! Lovely service, ambiance. Grew up with this place, especially the Hilton on the Alameda Central location brings back memories for me.", 'time': 1576246027}, {'author_name': 'Jazmin Rojas', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/105134418380120294400/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GjdFY3BNVQ5wZG2sUVjA7oQBL-9tSGi3hCtgCOK9w=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5', 'rating': 1, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': 'Went for breakfast with friends and family. Place is beautiful, very nicely decorated and very clean. Service was excellent, servers were very attentive and always looking after us. Food came out fast, food was tasty and had good presentation. My bad review is because at the end of the meal we asked for a glass of water, water smelled like sewage, it was disgusting, I just thought about all the food I ate and the water that was used to make it. We told the waiter and he didn’t say anything, just took the water away. This shouldn’t happen in a restaurant like this, this is unacceptable.
I always recommend this restaurant but I won’t anymore after this incident.', 'time': 1559236350}]

column15: [{'author_name': 'Özgür Öge', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/107949225371526525036/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GggvemEiTL4pqIz84KbdchvS4vx2o5Y9L7TqKaTqQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '7 months ago', 'text': "One of the most fun museums I have been in. They explained how tequila and mescal was made and let us experience the difference in their tastes one by one. However, the guiding was all in Spanish, so it is good to have someone to translate if you don't know Spanish.", 'time': 1582583672}, {'author_name': 'Allison Cole', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/111912941530920297664/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GimByUPoDbihHirBUza1myPNrdV9Eg3ggTnXPtpUg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3', 'rating': 4, 'relative_time_description': '6 months ago', 'text': 'I genuinely underestimated how informative this museum was going to be. I admit, before we arrived I thought: "we\'ll get a little knowledge and some shots", but it was so much more than that. The exhibits show the history of tequila and mezcal, the manufacturing process and explain the links of these liquors to the music and culture of not just Mexico but the region. Aside from the museum being informative, we enjoyed the upstairs space (a sort of bar/outdoor cafe) where we had our tequila and mezcal samples.', 'time': 1584025907}, {'author_name': 'Spike Marro', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/107787426939473860493/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-mgYVYoScsO0/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/AMZuuckqY8zO5RQvABUscjCEf_IwZ9qipA/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo/photo.jpg', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '7 months ago', 'text': 'Very educational. Right in the heart of Garibaldi Plaza.  Gift Shop sell bottles and there is a cantina. The terrace bar has an excellent view of the plaza.', 'time': 1582510060}, {'author_name': 'Feria Kazemi', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/115912572471143542265/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GjXtuUqW3GvN2plIHYRJy9JuVwjPgWxnHCs4qjs=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 1, 'relative_time_description': '8 months ago', 'text': 'Restaurant/bar out towards the plaza on the ground floor - similar to other places in the area: avoid. Was demanded a tip. Service wasn’t included in the bill, but saw the menu which said 10% is suggested for great service. On the actual bill, it said 15% is suggested for great service. Fine, still no issue. However, bill arrived with a piece of paper and a scribbled note attached that indicated a «\xa0price\xa0» including service. Not official and definitely not ok. Went up at the counter to pay, still hadn’t thought to not leave a tip, but server came up and confronted me about whether or not I was going to leave a tip. Cashier provided change and you can guess what I did/didn’t do. Server stormed over and grabbed my partner’s unfinished beer.', 'time': 1580952566}, {'author_name': 'Leticia Negreiros', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/115093852601628271414/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GjnRifK6-sYHo-CvFUnZSAcoDNebyJveKI2es1ajio=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': 'The museum was very nice, clean and well managed. The restaurant upstairs was welcoming and I enjoyed a nice afternoon up there. Since the polution was so bad the weekend I came to visit, there were many people at the museum which made it very relaxing.', 'time': 1558064534}]

column15: [{'author_name': 'Roger Tercero', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/107334156662848593271/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/-ZP3Nu2elgbU/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/AMZuucnj6iltTjy6uQmJFNxyh_5Qbekwjg/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3/photo.jpg', 'rating': 3, 'relative_time_description': '7 months ago', 'text': "Just stayed in the kids area. Needs maintenance, most toys are incomplete. A deeper cleaning would be fine. Visited it on Sunday afternoon, so it was not crowded, however toys are limited and you and your kid will have to take turns and wait in order to play. My kids loved it, they're 2 and 4 years old. It's a nice place to bring your little children to try something different, however, they may be a little young for most activities, so don't get disappointed if they get bored in an hour and they want to leave despite the entrance fee. I'm pretty sure is good for older children, but I had not the chance to visit the rest of the museum.\nThere's is a skeleton of a whale hanging on the main room. Kids really enjoy the view, that's worth paying for.\nParking available, but limited. Not really expensive, however you can park outside. Credit cards accepted. Strollers available for rent. Restaurant available inside, good prices.", 'time': 1583942873}, {'author_name': 'cindy genel', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/117916007066474891047/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GhLuJPdlQ9wCc-MfFT2M_57BXQ7vKBCkiJ8pXk3Ww=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba2', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': 'Great place for kids of all ages has a wonderful play area and lots to learn with interactive presentations. Has rest areas and a restaurant/ food market for all day adventurers. Plenty of friendly staff to help you find your way and even teach you a thing or two along the way.', 'time': 1565293766}, {'author_name': 'Jorge Pérez', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/115317430756967094397/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-q5VONb-Dk_M/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/AMZuucmNtwWXKNUORLedVzPApaegyjGD1g/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5/photo.jpg', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '7 months ago', 'text': 'This museum is cheap and educational. Upscale shops so if that's not for you at least go see the fountains & vertical gardens", 'time': 1599876717}, {'author_name': 'Jose Marsal', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/117500551314273097597/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GiaDaIcAPlraoIBIjWWXkhjO1lcW7Jo40yQv3RC=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 4, 'relative_time_description': '7 months ago', 'text': 'Ok for a bit of fun. More for children', 'time': 1583704912}, {'author_name': 'Akyra R', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/118002252740141190349/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GiMGIy72KFuhV81LqTjYyI8wURYNB5mjFMGl4Z8xA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 3, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': 'MUST IMPORTANT: carry portable charger!

Trick Eye Museum it’s an amazing experience if you have the disposition to do your best photography performance... whit creativity, fun and freedom. Anyone judging, I can tell!

However, the AR the experience leaves a lot to be desired... such as the quality of pictures behind the app...

If I recommend something is to go with comfortable clothes ready to look like fools in front of some people ... go with time is also a good suggestion because between what you wait for them to take the picture and the number of rooms at the end we were hurried .

The truth is that it COULD BE BETTER considering the cost ($ 300)... even so, have fun as we do! 🥰', 'time': 1547625236}, {'author_name': 'Maruch Ann', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/114950816129721041646/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Gh9iSdbukYllSmK0uHIOGauBcqiox4I_ve_VeGLEQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba2', 'rating': 4, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': 'My friends and I had a blast at the museum and we could take hundreds of photos. We decided to arrive at the opening time which is the best time if you don’t want to be annoyed by people photobombing your snaps. The AR app failed to live up to my expectations since the people in your photos and videos look out of focus and it uses all your smartphone battery. Fortunately, I noticed it on time, so I decided to stop using it and we were very happy with out pics.', 'time': 1563909052}, {'author_name': 'Yisel Nieto', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/107608959508999436121/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GhXwJmcJUJOqDPXoE3P_6yp3oJt69wbMgdrvt5HlQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '8 months ago', 'text': 'Great place for cute pictures. Highly recommend if you are in the city. The staff is so helpful and ready to assist in creating the illusion.', 'time': 1579308000}]

The musrum has a beautiful courtyard that's perfect for a coffee or lunch break after your visit.", 'time': 1581454813}, {'author_name': 'Wouter Verhoog', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/114668589104053652436/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GgyQXhQ6Qk6eaqDhoJncoMbFNDkHOygmGYE0ypAVA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '10 months ago', 'text': 'The Frans Mayer museum is a real gem: From the amazing glass collection to 17-century furniture and religious artefacts — There’s so much to marvel at.

The courtyard is an oasis in the middle of the enormous metropolis that is Mexico City. Truly a must-visit!', 'time': 1575402979}, {'author_name': 'Hobbit Merhy', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/100872765163204252113/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Gh_CqGW2QPEqoBBFZzvn8Mkvs_uJc1uCjLb21cTyQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': 'I really love this museum, is my favorite one and i go every year to the world press photo expo

There is a food store and a cafe, they are both good decent in quality and price,
I really recommend going', 'time': 1567958152}, {'author_name': 'Sheila Kay', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/107274366365691873864/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-92F8vmu2YzY/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAXo/AMZuuclMpedYpxz9vM__RuWfOfSHgM_fKg/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4/photo.jpg', 'rating': 4, 'relative_time_description': '9 months ago', 'text': "Very lovely collections. column15: [{'author_name': 'Ghia B.', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/117579628165856743928/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-on88R5LRwEw/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/AMZuucnBd6wRWMmlawjwwRLI4XfeyPrdGw/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba2/photo.jpg', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': 'This restaurant is a hidden gem. The food was delicious and the service was impeccable. Eduardo Ramos, who took care of our table, was professional and attentive to details. He explained what each dish consisted of and was patient answering my questions given my basic Spanish. He was kind and gave us amazing recommendations for cocktails and food. I recommend this restaurant for both quality, price and service and thank you Eduardo :)', 'time': 1561163438}, {'author_name': 'Geoffrey Marsan', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/110016361623052015413/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Giqn71YGkGY_JdgWhAODk75iS64q43DBETYgwEO=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': "Third time here. There'll be a fourth, and many more. Service is Michelin star level. The food is fresh, blending elements of international healthy cuisine with authentic Mexican tastes. Quantities are generous, presentation is faultless, and the prices are very low compared to what you would pay for a similar experience in a flagship gastronomic restaurant. My only suggestion would be to have moles on the side, in a cup, so that people with moderate love for them such as myself could adjust the quantity and favour other flavours instead. Well done team, a great future ahead for all those trainees, that's all I can hope for.", 'time': 1543700910}, {'author_name': 'Hemi', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/107023380735125703715/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GhUFyqpFxhe5KZz3bhwpa2jmMBjoBdh6sf7smIyQg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': 'Quite an amazing feast at Zefiro for lunch today. Found via Trip Advisor, the food served was a delectable Mexican dining experience. We ordered tacos for a 1st course expecting small portions out came 2 plates piled with top quality ingredients much like a deconstructed taco. For the main course my wife picked a winner with the grilled capsicum, my dish was also awesome with the ox tongue and cactus. Not expensive when compared to other similar restaurants in Mexico City. And service was outstanding. 5 plus stars.', 'time': 1546484035}, {'author_name': 'Hannes Schollenberger', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/116191796527139694342/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-GZeJZe0ATA0/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/AMZuuclHZ7Cndxp35yk_9z2LWjegseD6Sw/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo/photo.jpg', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': 'A great experience and even more once we got aware that this is run by students of the university. A real must. I had a Zefiro salad and stuffed pepper. Great choice.', 'time': 1556400656}, {'author_name': 'FM Guez', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/113869065402069825731/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-KdtzoYo8a6k/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/AMZuuclopNMPsFGF4LUyZxqNf-ijppMsLQ/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3/photo.jpg', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '9 months ago', 'text': 'Delicious food , well presented and service is perfect. The best food I ate in Mexico. Must go place.', 'time': 1577763217}]

Muy cómodo. Buena capacidad. Excelente trato. Maravillosas obras', 'time': 1584247657}, {'author_name': 'Erik Azpeitia Ruiz', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/114803255459098848094/reviews', 'language': 'es', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Gjl5tNSlqEbq5oiuItZcr_blWRNzNOHQkQ3mzIw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6', 'rating': 4, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': 'Buena atención, una privilegiada ubicación al sur de la ciudad y un cómodo recinto hacen de este teatro una magnífica opción para ver una buena obra. Excelente historia y buenas actuaciones.', 'time': 1567995629}, {'author_name': 'Airi De Leandro', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/111753665284934972495/reviews', 'language': 'es', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GgNMVA99LJJOmrDSYM6tVH42rkXt_7b4TvjsyQxUg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '12 months ago', 'text': 'El teatro es pequeño pero se adapta muy bien a las necesidades del espectador, se encuentra en un segundo piso, cuenta con venta de alimentos y bebidas.\nAprovechan al máximo cada espacio, cuenta con valet parking a un buen costo.', 'time': 1570569350}]

Here you can wander galleries and enjoy rotating exhibits of artwork. The museum features many exhibits by Mexican City artists. It's a great place to visit in Mexico!", 'time': 1597925859}, {'author_name': 'Santiago Pazos', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/112599820219898244230/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GgA7NkrvNTmy-EOjHsXsQiSqrwyfEtBoewe5fw7jA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '7 months ago', 'text': 'One of those unexpected museums you end up enjoying. And it is free! I was walking around and decided to give it a try. The moment I went they had an exhibition focused on artesanal Mexican culture: sculptures, rags, dresses ... beautiful. The museum, architecturally talking, is fantastic as well. Did I mention it is free? GO! Pics taken with Pixel 4 XL', 'time': 1583280387}, {'author_name': 'Rodrigo Zenji Hida', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/100444067583972865444/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GhCSZECpVAYNh5mT51TenT28Pb3cq_g7ssC7DpkIOE=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 4, 'relative_time_description': '9 months ago', 'text': 'Exhibit of modern local art, near Zocalo.\nWonderful artwork, specially the trees', 'time': 1577208745}, {'author_name': 'Jeff Sakari', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/103299987099691039628/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GgcU0CMJV6E1GUhOCdU2NqNoooaEena02qs_6o6gr4=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '8 months ago', 'text': 'Loved it, so much variety in the art and craft of Mexico on display!', 'time': 1580365426}, {'author_name': 'Joe Giambalvo', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/110789648629830005241/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-29SZp3Rel8A/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/AMZuucl_KpUthKTgGjgPm2JlijtfcNu5qw/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo/photo.jpg', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '10 months ago', 'text': 'Excellent display in an historic building,  celebrating 20 years of "Grandes Maestros" of Mexican Folk Art. I originally saw this exhibit years ago in Oaxaca, so it was a pleasure to see the expanded display on 2 floors. All that was missing were the wonderful photographs of the artisans that the book accompanying the exhibit provides.', 'time': 1575990554}]

Cost was very low, only 28 pesos for adults and 13 pesos for kids, so very affordable and enjoyable. I also noted that the display information in the "evolucion Humana" room was up-to-date with the most current science and literature on human evolution which was great to see.', 'time': 1579808192}, {'author_name': 'Enrique Betancourt', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/117405716808506916362/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Gha3coyrgFTLkm6iP2h7ZMijVAy7YDFIBmArnT4=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': 'After its renovation, the order of the exhibitions improved. The museum looks really tidy and well-preserved. It will take about 2 hours to look all the museum, several activities are offered during the week, so its a good idea to visit the museum official page prior your visit. There are several parking lots around the museum.', 'time': 1556403335}, {'author_name': 'Taj Meadows', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/100573186309473670764/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GhSL7T92Yd6TbYUjFXLGHZyrtwEw6CgQcKWK8S2ITk=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '7 months ago', 'text': "Such a great spot for kids. Main room is awesome', 'time': 1583191233}, {'author_name': 'Sonia Knoblauch', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/115569235340361087698/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Gj7QuMIV39w5Uc8vWwnwKdp_ZINhh3q4tM8jzAicw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '2 years ago', 'text': "Excellent museum with clear explanations about it's subject. It was recently renovated and now it has different approaches to the information, which I find very useful. It is also very attractive for young explorers.\nNow you can find information both in Spanish and in English, although not everything is translated.\nI can't wait to see the space section renovated as well. But the dinosaur is pretty impressive.", 'time': 1533091617}]

[{'author_name': 'rakhabel Dart', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/101084977796146303134/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/-bnulfjkegeo/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/AMZuuclnQ3PqfW5ZBiATne4z8Gxy3zcMTQ/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo/photo.jpg', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': 'I was exploring the Santa Maria La Ribera neighborhood in Mexico City when I came upon this great Mezcaleria called Estanquillo El 32. They have a great selection of Mezcals and the two women who run it are passionate about agave spirits and only buy direct from Mezcaleros that they know and trust. They also have a Cupreata growing in the courtyard!', 'time': 1562845419}, {'author_name': 'Zhura Sagara', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/116745057814514674932/reviews', 'language': 'es', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-b3edcCw4vDI/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/AMZuuclGsCUrCORbkSWjUfQ35yHfCRVTcQ/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo/photo.jpg', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a month ago', 'text': 'Pequeño rincón lleno de mezcal y cerveza artesanal local, cada mezcal un origen y una historia, excelente atención', 'time': 1597521317}, {'author_name': 'Frida Velázquez', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/113620179021714346103/reviews', 'language': 'es', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GgdGRSDx46uyRux_V-jPwCMLolgVzvdTW00HF_TcQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': 'Un lugar tranquilo, precios bajo-medio.
Cerveza en 35 la más barata, tienen mucha variedad de mezcales, cerveza artesanal y comida muy diferente como hamburguesa de conejo, puedes estacionarte afuera del lugar, la zona es segura.
La música es bajita para platicar.', 'time': 1561404103}, {'author_name': 'Dilara Durmus', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/116214903808315251007/reviews', 'language': 'es', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/-mu8SgvnyCAM/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/AMZuuclTQ2I6owEZ9FvRES7fUAkT1Pdalg/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3/photo.jpg', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '7 months ago', 'text': 'Tienen tamales veganos deliciosos! Son muy amables&atentos. Precios accesibles, buen ambiente. Feliz de haberlos encontrado.', 'time': 1581891681}, {'author_name': 'Arle vs el Mundo', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/102202179837951213855/reviews', 'language': 'es', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GgmS0M_leJQF0dqRzlTSScHtrTfoNeEgjxOkU3nKg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': 'El lugar es pequeño y curioso, tiene una estética muy agradable, personalmente me sentí muy agusto.
El persona era muy amable, las chicas que atendían eran muy simpáticas y agradables. El mezcal estuvo muy bueno, fuerte pero son sabor apreciable.
Lo que más me sorprendió fue el café endulzado con piloncillo, una sabrosura, sin duda es imperioso endulzarlo de esa manera. Te ofrecen el tarrito para servirte al gusto.
En cuanto a costos se apreciaba caro de entrada y así lo fue, el mezcal sobre todo.
Pero muy agradable experiencia.', 'time': 1551768428}]

column15:
[{'author_name': 'Ravindranadh Yelugula', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/116344022785575612753/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GjR9FF913R80XOcv6Zr_A_1vODphF8V8UXJ9xw9sQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '11 months ago', 'text': "The dive was amazing... my guide speaks English and he made the instructions very clear. I opted for 3rd person camera which cost 1350 pesos, worth it.. the diving video is of 90 sec long... But there were few more videos where they captured the flight take off, me preparing for the ride, how I felt before and after the dive...

Our flight took 6 clients (us) and 8(crew) members... Take off and watching your friends jump were the frightening things... Once you jump it's just the adrenaline rush on seeing the amazing view and the spins were awesome
(free fall spin - first 6sec,
initial mini parachute spin, you being horizontal to the earth trying to float - next 45sec,
finally the last spins with the parachute, you being vertical controling the parachute to have a perfect landing)…...

Try to take a slot which is afternoon or late morning.. the brighter the sky the better...

Also the place offers food and drinks.. they are affordable and the service is quick...", 'time': 1571674595}, {'author_name': 'Ariel Rodriguez', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/113640177947784766542/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Gh-NhLsY_RLiwZZ4H6Mq3DfBJl6CrIdSjEJ82reVAQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a month ago', 'text': 'Great experience. I wish they had wiffi and more activities to enjoy before and after the jump.', 'time': 1597423666}, {'author_name': 'Victor Garcia', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/113402556360381192256/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GjnC41QqAJisa7g9l5XapKCJ_AwXQlBdOCOlO2a2pc=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '7 months ago', 'text': 'Really awesome place to do skydive, absolutely friendly staff, including Chris, my instructor, to and enjoy at one of the busiest skydive places in the world!', 'time': 1582322552}, {'author_name': 'Pritesh K', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/112488600942788114638/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Gg8hKpQC-jb9LMhzfU2y3aT-97L5NQlEjPkRGXiH-w=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': "Skydive Mexico is one of the best and literally the cheapest sky dive experience in the world. Its located at Emiliano Zapata 19, 62680 San José Vista Hermosa, Mor., Mexico and is 2 hours drive from Mexico city on the Acapulco road. The drive is smooth and depending upon the crowd you can complete everything in 3 hours. The divers are extremely experienced, very well behaved and fun to be with in the overall experience. Don't miss this if you are in Mexico.The place also offers souvenirs and light munches. Overall a memorable place.", 'time': 1540268957}, {'author_name': 'Antonio Estrada', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/102523614553982948163/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Gj5Ur1ICcrnE5PF3wCTKDxGfXRxn7LlcNPcIeqw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 4, 'relative_time_description': '2 months ago', 'text': "It's a bit expensive, but it are so funny", 'time': 1595275826}]

column15: [{'author_name': 'Mario Kato', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/104308997047857044855/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GjViREU9ET0QAPtVXP5dW5k9VP6tVHgmSWJ4pHSuyQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6', 'rating': 4, 'relative_time_description': '12 months ago', 'text': 'Great for Kids of all ages. easy to get to.\nFriendly staff and very helpful.  Mostly Spanish speakers ,but some understand English.', 'time': 1570747018}, {'author_name': 'Diana Ruff', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/112056801724237521851/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/-RaVR8Xi5zCw/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/AMZuuck0gz3ROZw-_iXqxp_XcBTLpf1Itg/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4/photo.jpg', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '8 months ago', 'text': "Excellent children's museum with tons of hands-on exhibits, workshops and demonstrations. There are a lot of workers all around who are extremely helpful andand engaged with the kids, and those who speak English wear a badge that say they speak English. Since my Spanish is terrible, this is very helpful. I was very impressed and so glad that we got an annual pass so we can go and take our time because their is too much for just one visit! Both my kids (5 and 7) LOVE it and we haven't even seen the whole museum in our two visits so far!", 'time': 1578878110}, {'author_name': 'Nancy Dircks', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/118332076380486265442/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GhW4-W_EoEDRj6YSjx6PYegvXm57piFMHzcCrsUyU0=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': 'Amazing museum in the heart of Mexico City. My kids love it. We spent all day there because there is a Mega IMAX screen which plays two different documentaries and a Planetarium as well. So many exhibitions to choose from and kids can touch everything which is the way they really learn. This is a real interactive museum. Money very well spent.', 'time': 1569778721}, {'author_name': 'Scott Friedman', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/106489428578241604091/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GiCa6P_WxdyVmFxhRKN_VJZz10LCT3ExaPRAWjBsd0=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '9 months ago', 'text': "This was one of the best children's museums I have ever seen. If visiting Mexico City with kids I highly recommend a visit here. There were multiple areas for kids to explore with a lot of well staffed activities.  The museum is mostly in Spanish but it was easy enough to navigate and understand for those that don't speak Spanish", 'time': 1577542710}, {'author_name': 'Julia C', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/104256404953960682929/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GgQFUO2_VrF-YlXU8eEMgaCJRkztpjskryPXLE4BHU=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 4, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': 'Many exhibits. The staff was the best part, very knowledgeable, super friendly and very interactive. Movie theater is very cool. Took a cab in, which is easy because they have a drop-off area right in front. No food or drink allowed in, but there is a food court where you can eat and purchase food. Overall nice, enjoyable experience.', 'time': 1555551401}]

column15:
[{'author_name': 'Nina Chan', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/118130814145669664670/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/-IEOJkoN8rG4/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/AMZuucnpQsvyFWehp1xGVK0GoU9rkJQZsw/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo/photo.jpg', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': 'There are not many places that offer real barbacoa meat in Mexico City.  But this place is a MUST try.

We came here on the other day and The food was super delicious and big portion.  The service was exceptional. The owner was extremely welcoming and super nice.  They offer a different variety of items options on their menu.  You can order individual item or set menu .   Prices are very reasonable.

They slowly cook their barbacoa meat in a huge fire pit covered with some kind of leaves and sand.  They cooked their meat for at least few hours.

We ordered their set menu for 2 people.  It was a lot of food.  It came with consomé ( soup ) , freshly hand made tortillas , juice,  chicharrón (deep fried pork skin ) , avocado slices ,  some herbs, nopales , queso fresco ( fresh cheese ) , different types of salsas and the famous barbacoa meat.
The barbacoa meat was so tender that  melts in my mouth.  Very tasty.  Goes pretty well with their hand made tortillas .  The chicharrón was perfectly made , crunchy , not oily .

Loved every bites here. Will definitely come back next time when we are in Mexico City!!!

Take major credit cards or cash.
Open only on Sundays.', 'time': 1552020950}, {'author_name': 'Shantha Cokis', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/114457081894069753259/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Gjb2Cg_Q3YgLHfN63ZeGYbkDNRfwfvi6JxEQLCoMAE=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '8 months ago', 'text': 'Loved it! column15:
[{'author_name': 'Jose Carlos Alarcon Lopez', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/103393454877034258894/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Gg9ybyEA5HH9WgxcIkWZcrRNswjG4_hXoCXp5e5=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a month ago', 'text': 'Quintonil with the pandemic has taken the opportunity to add a counter that offers excellent view to the heated side of their kitchen and an inside peek on where the magic happens.
Chefs also took quarantine as a chance to reinvent the menu and it is sparkling!
Since international tourism is down, the restaurant is not that full and there are pretty good chances of being able to be seated as walk in, specially Tuesday-Thursday.

Most of the tasting menu items are new creations and they offer something unique and appreciated by your palate.

Currently tasting menu is $2300 pesos a little higher than before closing but still an experience to remember .', 'time': 1599336611}, {'author_name': 'Diego Torres-Palma', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/112995760995498953340/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-ttuRA5RNX54/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/AMZuucl1mW8ZmziNcAAk23c7YCzsUTi6qA/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3/photo.jpg', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a month ago', 'text': 'Tucked away in the Polanco area of Mexico City this restaurant delivers the richness and Mexican cuisine you didn’t know you were craving! These dishes truly make an quite the impact to your senses. The beet dish blew me away! If you can - sit at the bar as you’ll get a front row seat to watching the team in harmony.', 'time': 1597678644}, {'author_name': 'MvdD', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/102459397486163101124/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GgkD8_GMZClY3G8mktk-Vh4iqKVP0QLzPdo4PQo=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3', 'rating': 4, 'relative_time_description': 'in the last week', 'text': 'Friendly and attentive staff, great cocktails and an interesting tasting menu; all at a reasonable price. For me it really was the more refined Mexican kitchen I hoped it would be. I do have to downlight the decoration (felt like a high school canteen) and the size of the menu; two dishes less would have been perfect.', 'time': 1601667005}, {'author_name': 'Benedin Rosalio', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/105893035302392356937/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-kQaR-ZtxCW0/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/AMZuucnDfsCTYk7CgRKPqRB3LxYxgL7OIw/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3/photo.jpg', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'in the last week', 'text': "Tasting/pairing menu is the way to go. If fancy environment is what you're looking for, don't go. This is an experience for the taste buds and an adventure from the comfort of your barstool. Yes, I highly recommend sitting at the bar, it allows you to see the action.", 'time': 1601691982}, {'author_name': 'Taj Meadows', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/100573186309473670764/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GhSL7T92Yd6TbYUjFXLGHZyrtwEw6CgQcKWK8S2ITk=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '2 months ago', 'text': "The food here is simply incredible. We felt that it was more consistent and overall better in terms of quality, flavour and presentation than our experience at Pujol, though that was also really excellent. The one area I'd suggest improvement on would be the ambiance. There are speakers, but no music when we were there, and the lights were quite bright. That said, the food is absolutely amazing and worth every penny, so if you're looking for a wonderful culinary adventure this is your spot. We'll certainly be back as soon as we can.

Covid related - they had excellent protocols in place, which made us feel safe...but there's not a real outdoors area, so might not be something everyone is comfortable with for now. For us, it was a special occasion, and we felt it was worth it.", 'time': 1594775110}]

Delightful.', 'time': 1577457583}, {'author_name': 'Andy Martinez', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/102430384834165605115/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GiPqxj3pHAxQNCL7Z306_vN4Um7FbesTwxLju3EbQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '3 years ago', 'text': "Watercolor isn't as popular and this museum is simply a gem among other collections not only for the large size of the collection but varied artists that you will find. The exterior of the main galleries is also very peaceful and there is a small auditorium for showings too.", 'time': 1494523151}, {'author_name': 'Cecilia Alejandra', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/115660246973360429932/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GgSc0Lg91Ywc8yp1FKMkmQe0Rq4nBtGHDjhMp4e=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': 'This place is amazing for anyone who’s a watercolor enthusiast. The collection features different techniques and styles from mexican artists as well as international, that are a great inspiration and helps you discover more of what you can do with watercolors. The gardens are gorgeous too, and great for spending a little time sitting outside.', 'time': 1555085330}, {'author_name': '劉GS', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/104278547337467158384/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GgXTaYsNoj-KCQcwivKhllTkht6WcOJKUEotFSo=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 4, 'relative_time_description': '2 years ago', 'text': 'a tad small, not crowded, free entry (donations welcome of course) although you have to pay 50 pesos for a photography permit i think, the rooms dedicated to prehispanic and 19th century art are absolutely precious though small, the museum cafe is well-priced (amusing to see gangs of sparrows nibble tortilla crisps), there are also a few stone statues/sculptures around (based on prehispanic styles eg mayan) which are quite lovely as well
it definitely takes less than an hour to finish going through the museum, leaving you time to explore other museums in the area

personally i think watercolour is an expressive medium for depicting qualities of light and colour, such as the unfathomable gentleness of white-pink roses. it also lends itself to styles such as abstract art and cubism.

overall worth a visit', 'time': 1535070310}]

I wanted to give it 4 stars because waiters were not around when we needed them and had to fetch them a couple of times, but the place seems new and willing to provide top quality', 'time': 1577931642}, {'author_name': 'Isabel T Garcia', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/100509610729365254452/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Ghut5m1HTCcoE9c3fo48EymsSlVHAyBABMhDEN-170=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '10 months ago', 'text': 'The concept is unique and and the food is incredible! column15: [{'author_name': 'Raynaldoangel@gmail.com Southside3', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/103216893348633902156/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-_jfVM4YPDBg/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/AMZuucn_sgZMLRtEyIxqd7V1CibLoSlyYg/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3/photo.jpg', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '6 months ago', 'text': "The hike to the top was about 40 mins , before I go on I would like to strongly suggest to appreciate the tour guide offered before the hike. Not because you would want the guide to guide you but for the simple fact that each time that you take a break there's a story along the road to the top. Our guide was extremely helpful excited about his job and passionate to tell us the stories. When we climb and when we descended there were stories to the whole mountain and the city.", 'time': 1584252809}, {'author_name': 'Jesse Felan', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/117479022649230310113/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Gh8eZ5Q9pAf0PbhfQ5jPd1Qx-L5UPTj0jQBbQdptA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '10 months ago', 'text': 'Awesome climb up. Takes about 40 minutes to get to the top. We did it in 30 non stop. There also a great market with artisanal crafts. You can get a massage pretty cheap too. There also a hot spring some where', 'time': 1575734780}, {'author_name': 'Victor Baeza', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/117225035204023683579/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GgpcQyaWCUn5ophOHLlf3BHIP--hv-B70NUZwzr_A=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'in the last week', 'text': 'You must come before everybody else can.', 'time': 1601775049}, {'author_name': 'Simon Rivett', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/103169314006544689836/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GgKSk7F69ZMRj2KlEg6XcMvdUs2jdmKfsf4zN85kg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': 'Be prepared, it’s a very long climb to the top. It took us 1 hour 45 minutes from the end of the market stalls to the Pyramid. You can never see more than 20 - 30 meters so you don’t know or realize how much it is. Also take 55 pesos for entry. Take a bottle of water. Once at top, views are spectacular, but if I realized the climb I would not have done it. Took 1 hour 20 minutes to come back down. It’s not steps, the path is made from rocks and sometimes very slippery.', 'time': 1562200954}, {'author_name': 'Gemi Nunez', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/111236273763182587147/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GhzTxQjtynpomBtkihmLlZSzjAKMaL6PrNNb4QkLag=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '11 months ago', 'text': "The hike it's a little intense, but it is so worthy, amazing landscapes and you feel one with nature. I truly enjoyed the journey more so than the destination. The ruins are pretty blunt and aside from the view there is not much to see.", 'time': 1572493902}]

column15:
[{'author_name': 'Carlos F. Villalobos', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/111299506354612729823/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-NXYPjQxx9Cg/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAFGA/AMZuucl6_FGzH2wF8cAHopiHT8t316yXJg/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4/photo.jpg', 'rating': 4, 'relative_time_description': '7 months ago', 'text': 'Quite an impressive museum, the collections inside are unique. One has to be thankful to the Slim Foundation for their contribution to the Mexican people. The building itself is unique and a true work of art.
