column15:
[{'author_name': 'Alexandra Woolsey-Puffer', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/113184292365006318561/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GgaFmp73eQwsSgWg2HmAoizOscGpd9ALdXemDemAw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': 'Excellent tours limited to 10 visitors. Note that you must book a timed tour in advance on the website, but they offer tours in both Spanish and English which is great.

Keeping the groups to a small size makes it very intimate and special. Since this was a residence, it was never meant for crowds, and so this strategy is appropriate and respectful.

Photography inside is permitted for a small fee.

There is a gift shop with some excellent book selections and an open-to-the-public (no ticket required) garden across the street.

This was one of my favorite experiences in CDMX.', 'time': 1565448177}, {'author_name': 'עינב קגן', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/104797183429171207382/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GiI-0i21bcatqVlaomhQXAJK6rmcKd75l5rlbrzXA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': 'What an experience! We took the Spanish tour even though we don’t know Spanish (there were no slots for the English one during our visit). And it was totally worth it! Definitely wouldn’t miss it and will go back if I have the chance.
PLUS
important to know that even if there are no open visits while in Mexico City, his  garden is open for free and there is a free architectural and design Museum next door!', 'time': 1569375884}, {'author_name': 'Thomas Myers', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/105502198620715593569/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-j8oJYDOvX90/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/AMZuuclkM9LXWPIKihZ0nANMXAYz-XIFBA/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo/photo.jpg', 'rating': 1, 'relative_time_description': '7 months ago', 'text': 'An insult to the memory of Luis Barragán.
Terrible customer service.
The door was slammed in our face as the tour was starting with no explanation. Then I was yelled at not once but twice by a very aggressive young man.
As a customer and guest this is not the way to be treated.
I spoke to the manager who did not seem to care ! Unfortunately- as the tour guide was very nice and the house is ravishing.
Hopefully the staff will improve to be at the level of the house. Right now there is a problem to be resolved.', 'time': 1582835333}, {'author_name': 'Sanjana Dayananda', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/103025182453676585598/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GghmQPPH40gOcvrKKlpcPHAoXKvmskVPYKRSnIj=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba2', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': 'The tour was incredible and very informative. I didn’t know much about the architect before going but I have a new found appreciation for his style and choices now. You have to book the tour well in advance online (at least a month or two) and they go fast! The English tours are only a few times a day so pay attention to which ones you are booking. There are no cameras or phones allowed on the tour. But you can take pictures of his garden across the street and that’s free to enter whenever, no reservation needed.

P.S I highly recommend checking out the Archive gallery and cafe next door!!! It’s free and open to the public.', 'time': 1554054018}, {'author_name': 'Ron Wong', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/109995492420355032061/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GhZl7O-BMbewUqImWfuKURKhH59VG9y5bbONmR8BQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': 'Wow. A rare glimpse into the home environment of a trend setting architect and design mind. Our guide, she was awesome explaining all about each space we were in and how it relates to Luis Barragan’s vision for his house, adjoining spaces, the light and the outdoors. We were engrossed the entire time. It lasted a good hour. You must make reservations at least 1 month in advance just to be safe. It was a busy weekend so we visited on a Tuesday midday. It rained a touch so we were limited in time on the roof patio. Also they charge a fee of $25 USD ($500 pesos) to allow camera into the museum during the tour. We opted not to which allowed us to enjoy the guide and the spaces without worrying about getting photos when people left each area. But next time I might pay to play! Across the street is a garden where some of these photos are from.', 'time': 1563063000}]

column15: [{'author_name': 'A Montiel', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/104603411969190387565/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Gh09fLJKJSdaIX49xL4aQCWG2jmZEim6prxc_RRWA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '7 months ago', 'text': 'Overall it was a great experience. Beautiful place, very well cared for by staff,  it\'s always clean.  The only concern we had on our visit was that we rented one of the rooms with nine beds (Four bunk beds and one single bed) for our party of nine.  We read the contract and it does say the room comes with four towels.  When the room was given to us we asked if they had more towels as it did not make sense that they only provided four towels for nine people since each party is paying the rate of 600+ pesos per night. The attendant gladly contacted the reservations department via radio in which case the attendant "Vicente" confirmed the room only comes with four towels as stated in the contract.  We said not a problem and were about to ask him if they would be able to rent towels and how much it\'d be when suddenly another person was heard on the radio saying "the room only comes with four towels, didn\'t they read and sign the agreement?"  We were very surprised and speechless by that lack of professionalism from this person. We later found out it was one of the managers by the name of "Paty Cuecuecha."  The attendant at the reservations desk had already answered our question and she probably didn\'t think the other attendant was still standing in front of us and you could see his embarrassment as he repeatedly said "I\'m so sorry"  we told him not to worry about it as he had been very kind to us.  Other that that incident, we were very pleased with our two-day stay at Las Estacas so they still deserve a 5 star rating.  Hopefully this manager will get a little more training 🙄', 'time': 1583550124}, {'author_name': 'ESSAKI MUTHU', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/103892608269121994560/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Gi4bKeGaNxftvs3QvSmzoqk2r8lxa-2pXGDqAgu4w=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 4, 'relative_time_description': 'in the last week', 'text': 'Pleasant place to stay for week end. But little costly for nothing ..', 'time': 1601517789}, {'author_name': 'Octavio Miramontes', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/109221555862189714422/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GhwawWadV0rWn-fv845_JwiauZbl1SO9PW8hrknvag=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a week ago', 'text': 'This is a place no one should miss. Very close to Cuernavaca', 'time': 1601170083}, {'author_name': 'TheCrazyMax', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/117266176528825319031/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-jlnpS8ltfT0/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/AMZuuclkavXxHQ2V8Cs3gfMyick7jkMcBg/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5/photo.jpg', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '6 months ago', 'text': "It's a beautiful and well kept clean park, with swimming pools and also a natural river. It's a must to come and visit. Well worth it. Pics speak for itself yet nothing compared to living the experience.", 'time': 1584499835}, {'author_name': 'HARPRIT BHATTI', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/107613222241141442460/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Gg3Vxi92MkIm-ZvgRquPLwooomcymxKVtKVeroTzg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '9 months ago', 'text': "Amazing place to do camping. It's not too cols or hot. Completely natural place with swimming pools and jacuzzi. You can swim and cross the river which is really good. It's going to cost 550 MXN per person if you want to do camping here but it's worth it. You can bring your own things to eat since food here is a bit costly and fancy. There are more than one entrance here so make sure to enter in the one in the photo here. They have hostal and hotels too.", 'time': 1578405835}]

column15: [{'author_name': 'Josh Musgrave', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/100432959857259208103/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GgdV-wgn3vnE82G0Rz2GfYH4GMK2oX2YjtHCuLLmQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '8 months ago', 'text': 'Amazing to walk through! A huge labyrinth of costumes, clothing, candy, snacks, eateries, etc. We eventually stopped to have tostadas. So delicious! Waitress was very friendly and accommodating. Spoke very good English. Service was quick. Such a lively environment! Of course, you’ve got the typical shop owners dragging for patronage, especially around eating areas, but that’s everywhere in Mexico. The area around the market is quite pleasant, and nice to just walk through.', 'time': 1580227736}, {'author_name': 'Manuel Lopez', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/118212727672109084376/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Gg4BVZfE9xr1VWg7t_95D96vZekieoAHVLvLmPG=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 4, 'relative_time_description': '2 weeks ago', 'text': 'Excellent place to get all vegetables and fruit you want, you find everything you can imagine, and also, if you like market food, there are several places to try from breaksfast to Lunch!!', 'time': 1600547207}, {'author_name': 'Kathleen Herring', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/100974202323162019766/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GjCfjViHS--UkBOPOZ5lwNKezCwc6fGnkEoFE8wxQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '3 weeks ago', 'text': 'Prices were increased because we are American tourists but food was great, everything was still reasonable, vendors were all very nice & helpful.', 'time': 1599876385}, {'author_name': 'haelyn millan', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/110639190280708263870/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/-DahbfF-uZY8/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/AMZuucladJFQ3AGCfEmtMRvgYFJzWh5Llg/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo/photo.jpg', 'rating': 4, 'relative_time_description': 'a week ago', 'text': "If you are obviously a tourist it will be more expensive. column15:
[{'author_name': 'Nathalie Léon', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/109443789935719634849/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GiHniMJ2XqY-Oyn8elDHwv09k3kcO0yGup0An4k=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a week ago', 'text': 'This place is amazing, unique and has a powerful energy. You will see an enormous collection of authentic artifacts in an impactful atmosphere.
It is a must see and worth the drive!', 'time': 1601450195}, {'author_name': 'elizabeth contreras', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/107650014904077074987/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-7VHkHzzF_tI/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/AMZuucn5BXJBpVjdMXMhNaGyxT60ODvmlg/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo/photo.jpg', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a week ago', 'text': 'Absolutely Wonderfully 💭 Designed Building!
Unbelievable, Impressive! The pre- columbian artifacts are the Mexican Treasures! They Are well preserved and actually seem to come to life! I can spend hours and hours on each floor! The museum is a replica of Chichintza, Yucatan!
Also, several pictures and sketches of Diego’s work! You wan walk outside on several of the levels!
Frida Kahlo’s museum has lines wrapped around the corner! This museum never seems to have a line! Great option!
What a national treasure!!!
Thank You to his Family 4 sharing all his work w the World!
Sincerely La Profesora de California', 'time': 1601020258}, {'author_name': 'Alejandra Cardenas', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/104736042711201844463/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GgHU-gqr_tZXo0YSrVXz_OE2JhSSWSQ9zSK1nw4ghA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': 'It is a very different and unique museum. Planned through the eyes of the artist Diego Rivera. All the pieces of art are from his personal collection or his own art. The gardens are beautiful. Some of the pieces are not original pieces but are exhibited as he acquired them because he liked them not because he thought of them as investment. His intention with the building of this museum was for people to go in and enjoy the art exhibited there through their own eyes  and not as part of history.', 'time': 1566778704}, {'author_name': 'Thomas Paterson', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/106623673851170002007/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/-1f3PMuoSqEA/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/AMZuucn-rJsLLP3kL1V6snE3WSBMmMUvvQ/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo/photo.jpg', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a month ago', 'text': "Shhhhhh.... Don't tell anyone this is the best museum in all Mexico - or the most interesting.", 'time': 1597014754}, {'author_name': 'Mike Duran', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/111358696850494649826/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-UnxvfThgmjI/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/AMZuucm9T2M9l5I2CWkoOKAfpme0_Wf2NA/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba2/photo.jpg', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '7 months ago', 'text': "Diego Riveras  museum, which he erected in honor of his ancestors, with a vast collection of mayan relics, and amazing mosaics along the ceilings made by Diego him self. If you haven't been there go. Heads up, if you visit fridah kahlo's museum you will receive a free voucher which gives you access to Diegos museum.  Amazing deal right.", 'time': 1581481957}]

[{'author_name': 'Lizeth Calderón', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/114773145123736458963/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GidSLZrEHIfkRRdgHUL7MJfBnPZnooNiQhw7wvVbOA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '2 weeks ago', 'text': 'Well I loved this small park because is safe, there are patrols driving around the park constantly and that made me feel secure.
There are some concrete benches where you can sit and read a book while you enjoy the environment or the view.
You can even rent a remote control ship and have a great time in the little fountain or maybe rent a motorbike.
On the other hand there are some outdoor cafes and restaurants around the park where you can spend time listening to nice music, having a conversation with a friend or just working on your laptop if you have some pendants.', 'time': 1600538911}, {'author_name': 'Robert Khatchikian', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/100371814140717824986/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-SzJseYToZh4/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/AMZuuckDusIkvRPUg-txhvohmsmhywp0lg/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4/photo.jpg', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '2 months ago', 'text': 'Beautiful Park in the heart of the Polanco district in Mexico City.', 'time': 1595641775}, {'author_name': 'Felipe Barousse', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/115687750973873654821/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GhZ21WXE-1AJhoYhc_ysNyOzaczHdcBfK60SMs6lM0=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '8 months ago', 'text': 'Great park. Have known it since I was a kid...trees were barely sticks back then. Today, they are huge making it a beautiful park for long relaxing walks. Lots of squirrels as well.', 'time': 1581060021}, {'author_name': 'lisa derepentigny', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/105434914332035733170/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-dyaVO-tEY0g/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/AMZuucljA4nWbQyrENVYNd0dV7Veygxb4g/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3/photo.jpg', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': 'You can go into a protected bird park. You can see live entertainment, and lots of good restaurants. Very hip and trendy', 'time': 1567409384}, {'author_name': 'Lexy Luzhikaru A.R.', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/100651379733451907360/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GgDmk8P2h6iobXqUPQwowFgV9ygDojuNNZO0UuXAII=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': "Usually it's a nice park to have a nice time walking or sitting in a bench, having a coffe or an ice-cream. This time, we visited it for the FYJA and it wasn't disappointing. All the installations were very pretty. The topic was very interesting and educational, the pollinators and their importance in our lives.
As usual, the fountains were beautiful with all the figures made by flowers. Sadly, we couldn't visit the kids playground because it closes at 5pm. It's a good point for the park, a close children's space for playing safely", 'time': 1555200609}]

column15:
[{'author_name': 'Marisela DG Sakal', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/107656342045038365428/reviews', 'language': 'es', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GjQLAz8wCmHT2mrEHjfHGQlpd5-DEFg8Ne7xrB8Ug=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': 'Agradable lugar, su decoración te recibe con los brazos abiertos, su vibra te sumerge a sentirte cómodo y como si estuvieras en casa.

Menú basto, con opciones para desayunar, comer, tomar algo o consentirte con un postre.

El sabor de sus platillos es delicioso, tienen buena presentación y las porciones me parecieron adecuadas.

Buen precio y servicio, me quedo con ganas de regresar.', 'time': 1553403571}, {'author_name': 'hilda patiño peña', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/111712785722710842489/reviews', 'language': 'es', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/--KzVEGXVwGA/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/AMZuuckn7tFdj9BMlfvJSJTwlUv3T37mRQ/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo/photo.jpg', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '7 months ago', 'text': 'LA COMIDA ES MUY SABROSA Y EL LUGAR SUPER RELAJANTE 😊', 'time': 1582747272}, {'author_name': 'Elia Bautista', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/112526753777167535801/reviews', 'language': 'es', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Giob5zL0YUoPLtwkNe07NP5aICWWiutsu6uF7ijvA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 3, 'relative_time_description': '9 months ago', 'text': 'Es muy rica la comida, tiene precio justo pero la atención es lentísima. [{'author_name': 'Tahir Sharif', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/118038071772413777660/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GgKApdV1c4iju53LpRp3UdybY93WLGuyQre24qZ5eM=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': 'Delicious food. Warm, friendly service. Despite location, few tourists, mostly Mexican groups of business people, friends and families.  Sadly too full and jet-lagged to try the amazing looking desserts.', 'time': 1549822658}, {'author_name': 'Jason Zhang', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/101087892207167283074/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-Ta0lMyjXhW8/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAGg/AMZuucnWFphooHIfF3kECky-HtycM-oseA/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo/photo.jpg', 'rating': 2, 'relative_time_description': '7 months ago', 'text': 'Food was fantastic and great service expect the waiter waiting on us was trying to rip us off
In Mexico generally you don’t have to tip but if the service is good you can tip 10%-15%(if it’s really good). So when the bill came and the waiter asked me how much I would like to tip I said 10%. Instead of choosing 10% on the machine in front of my eyes he turned his back towards me and then handed me the check to sign.
I thought that was weird and noticed the tip was at 20% on my bill. So I told him I don’t care about the extra few dollars but it was very dishonest what he was doing and ruined my experience of the night because the food was really good. He turned red immediately and pretended he doesn’t understand me anymore (even though he was speaking English to me all through dinner).

It’s a very authentic place so I would still recommend anyone to try this place but if you are a tourist like me watch out on the final bill lol', 'time': 1581726424}, {'author_name': 'Ravinder Singh', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/107039303721646915013/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/--odPt5OKFbk/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/AMZuucm0AiONNedyCYbVh9u9VqeNlrpH7w/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4/photo.jpg', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '7 months ago', 'text': 'Truly authentic Mexican food n excellent service.', 'time': 1581661958}, {'author_name': 'Shayne King', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/107970127240054531693/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GjiZRdmssVcnh0prrS4tCwakJey3f1toYZu1Z1tgFM=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '7 months ago', 'text': 'Nice place. column15: [{'author_name': 'Nas Sol', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/116966755472162556279/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Ggof3p9yPoz54IZTpz-v4YHzJV17M16XWGZdIauqg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '11 months ago', 'text': "What a marvel! Different perspectives of economics that you would least imagine. One of the most insightful museums that I've visited in CDMX. This one is definitely worth the visit.", 'time': 1571186491}, {'author_name': 'Hector HUERTA', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/115692502658586885202/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GgsDbnzAa0_6ahadVXfyXT_MiTSZ7pbjVYi22s7yg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6', 'rating': 4, 'relative_time_description': '7 months ago', 'text': "Actually, I could not get in, because a street protest happened, which prevented tourists, students, and researchers from getting in. It was very disappointing not to be able to visit this one-of-a-kind museum, on my last day in the nation's capital, for it is one of the first museums worldwide to illustrate and document the history of economics and its importance to our every day lives. I managed, however, the day before, to visit the nearby museum of the Stock Exchange (MUBO for its initials in Spanish), a 40 minute walk from there, which I highly recommend. Oh well. I hope to visit the Economics Museum on a future visit to the oldest capital city of North America, bar any protests that target world heritage sites, monuments or museums.", 'time': 1583013920}, {'author_name': 'Ian Cockerill', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/105919471432032114681/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-r5P2E7zRHcM/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAB0/AMZuucn1YcLcAuRVzLNpNgErlvI7Iu6iFQ/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3/photo.jpg', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '8 months ago', 'text': "Looked like a cool place. But be aware that there isn't a lot in English", 'time': 1580301520}, {'author_name': 'Andy Martinez', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/102430384834165605115/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GiPqxj3pHAxQNCL7Z306_vN4Um7FbesTwxLju3EbQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6', 'rating': 3, 'relative_time_description': '3 years ago', 'text': "The museum has a great presentation with the most notable part being climate change and promoting sustainable growth for our planet. The museum is ideal for kids, a sort of field trip. They can definitely do better as far as the darker sides of capitalism, really making an effort to educate yourself about what can happen if you don't handle your finances well. It might as well be one giant commercial for banks and loans.", 'time': 1495677126}, {'author_name': 'Evelyn', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/103349709027804218511/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GhPYY-aZLHn6LA73lGi6zu1XFpucJ1na3DeKup40Q=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '8 months ago', 'text': 'Interesting museum, even for kids, it has 4 floors, each one with a different section.', 'time': 1581256302}]

column15:
[{'author_name': 'Ajnu Jacob', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/110936085514306754684/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GjoBjfzbNnVw92Kw6TeV6tEKx8gHIhQrHvIWvB8tio=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '7 months ago', 'text': 'Remarkable experience to walk through Trotsky’s home. A complete tragedy and a huge sacrifice to human kind, that this museum brings to life and makes accessible to the public.

The tickets are cheap and the history is incredibly rich and tragic. A must visit if you’re in Mexico City.', 'time': 1582170777}, {'author_name': 'Cristal Dieguez Chilin', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/112547981560519108248/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Gh4MOe7NNfcFJXjis2WMDtys3xaUlhqUNxTL9O0D8k=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '7 months ago', 'text': 'Interesting place with a lot of history.  The tour guide was great at explaining how trotsky died', 'time': 1582246893}, {'author_name': 'Michelle Zhang', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/108078050377291557988/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GjcO1QsGfIkHIP8O21SphJZtshspz-pRa1DObXvOME=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '9 months ago', 'text': "Unexpected and fascinating find! I didn't realize Trotsky lived in Mexico near the end of his life and this intimate museum, which used to be his house, was eye opening! It also had a quiet, beautiful garden, great way to get a serene moment amidst the hustle of CDMX.", 'time': 1577574195}, {'author_name': 'Philippe Bun', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/116262175111069062563/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GiLY-1e-EwEk-H9d9jadl6xVL6SDGOXN9611HyR1w=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': 'This small museum located very close to a speedway and is a source of historical facts for those who'd like a quick but exhaustive reminders on Trotsky Life in a general worldwide context.
Efforts have been clearly put to preserve the house and its amenities: great glance into Trotsky "private Life. The garden is well preserved and is the perfect place to enjoy a coffee.
For 40 pesos (entrance fee), this museum is worth a visit! Don't forget to have a look at the drawing exhibition!', 'time': 1553464893}, {'author_name': 'Andrea Gregor', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/105658073948948787505/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GiNG0Wvh7UHordOa_9KiHe2ZIwbS7fpGQlSECwMSQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '8 months ago', 'text': 'I really like the museum of Trotsky cause they show you all the story I recommend it seriously.', 'time': 1580854758}]

Realmente es triste la basura que se genera con todas esas bolsas. Una opción que recomiendo es que si las quieren seguir usando, busquen las nuevas bolsas biodegradables. Así contribuimos todos a cuidar nuestro entorno.', 'time': 1552926153}, {'author_name': 'Marin Cortes', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/101080634169218800150/reviews', 'language': 'es', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-VJ8ohLzML-s/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/AMZuucl0TAaEwHPJnbZmaG7AZerjrQYubA/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo/photo.jpg', 'rating': 3, 'relative_time_description': '2 months ago', 'text': 'Muy buena atención y exelente sabor de las carnitas y la cebollita', 'time': 1596904219}, {'author_name': 'Omar Gonzalez', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/102273602595223340635/reviews', 'language': 'es', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GhJoy_9e9Z2CDzvQVzGc4f6H-KsPS9GvLIp2_lR=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba2', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'in the last week', 'text': 'Buen sabor 😋', 'time': 1601599342}]

column15: [{'author_name': 'Isabella Parks', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/104296010325573631542/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GgA5Z-KHt6u14qscOYkVg5GXMadgPCg2r95Lw5K0Q=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '7 months ago', 'text': "A beautiful, beautiful restaurant. We sat on the second floor, where there was water cascading over the clear roof. We had extremely attentive waitstaff that were very sensitive to my egg allergy. We got the 6-course tasting menu and the wine and beer pairing. It was a LOT to consume. While each course was small, the contents were heavy (though, still very delicious). If I could do it again, I'd get a bottle of wine instead of the pairing - the drink portions were huge - we were so stuffed, we couldn't finish our drinks! The bill came to $220 CAD for two of us, which would be the price for one person if we did this in Canada. We also went on Valentine's Day and they gave us an extra plate full of desserts! So good. We managed to fight past our fullness to eat them! Would definitely recommend for a splurge dinner date in Mexico City.", 'time': 1582645203}, {'author_name': 'Kyuwon Lee', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/110778779454043925617/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Gg43cgZtPRd0RkzgJYQQxGGC0Lw1AMqGEWoW_ezfg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6', 'rating': 4, 'relative_time_description': '4 months ago', 'text': "Definitely a great ambiance and superb location that's very close to the downtown/touristic area but slightly outskirt so it's not too loud. I might've got a wrong menu choice but their meat was not the best. We requested medium for it but it came as even 'rarer' than regular rare and we had to request recooking for two more times. But the service was good and cocktail was great.", 'time': 1590534660}, {'author_name': 'Danny Bannister', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/103956351331707026109/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-T6VLS6ciXqU/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/AMZuucnlodd6P5PFsPvscUECmdia6XlwRg/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4/photo.jpg', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '9 months ago', 'text': 'So I stopped in here because I saw all the wine bottles at the entrance. After having a great evening drinking wine with my wife and watching the amazing food being carried by we decided to go back and eat the next night. It was just as good as I had hoped. This is a wonderful place to try small plates. Taste as much as you can because this chef has a way of combining flavors that works on many levels', 'time': 1576290903}, {'author_name': 'Homar Sánchez-Olguín', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/108843675505827221143/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Ghz6NugaakvSEZCOiWgJVnkba9Kbmjmf_z-qBeo7g=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a month ago', 'text': "Extraordinario lugar. Buen sabor y excelente calidad. It's a must in México City downtown for a good drinks stop and faboulous super Mexican meals.", 'time': 1599018064}, {'author_name': 'yesenia haro', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/116761389916202996486/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GhbStQsm8j8gSGikFblk8_0kgp-r4ubuk5QRNuz=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '9 months ago', 'text': 'The food here is amazing such a beautiful blend of flavors. Definitely come here if you love intricate flavors. The atmosphere is nice, quiet and dim. Very romantic place as well.', 'time': 1576290887}]

column15: [{'author_name': 'Mihai Palea', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/117550468946428182969/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Gim7O7G4HsB9CuJ1HHoiqvyIKTIQNTH_e93PjK48w=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '6 months ago', 'text': "If you are willing to walk up the hill (it's both a ramp and stairs so wheelchairs are able to go up the hill with help), then it's worth visiting for both the church and the view. The church is highly decorated for such a small one. Currently under minor renovations but that won't stop you from enjoying it.", 'time': 1584284440}, {'author_name': 'Ivan Russell Lara', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/104317236420399555345/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GgCXFAJJMnwZv6l2QpRKadXchXjCccuvueJQxQbwQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '8 months ago', 'text': "One of the most beautiful places of worship I've evered entered. This church left me awestruck. Wow, was the expression I gave upon entering. The tough climb up was worth it.", 'time': 1581212004}, {'author_name': 'Nas Sol', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/116966755472162556279/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Ggof3p9yPoz54IZTpz-v4YHzJV17M16XWGZdIauqg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': 'This is definitely worth the short hike up the hill to see the iconic church and beautiful views of Cholula. You cannot miss this church and perspective of the city!', 'time': 1564854515}, {'author_name': 'Krithika Mukund', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/114183612576586751395/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GgP32OTbav79SMjEsY0FJYNyR9RKt6pgLKrEEM3qg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '9 months ago', 'text': 'Relatively easy climb on well made paths and stairs. Great views all around, of the town below, Puebla and the smoking Popo volcano. And can tick off one’s list , climbing to the top of the largest manmade pyramid in the world!', 'time': 1577409832}, {'author_name': 'Daniela Navarro', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/108072622239741358541/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Gi-Ml6xI_FG_BnV8PTlCUoorBfIntzOUfDmwEFOVA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '2 years ago', 'text': "Amazing! column15: [{'author_name': 'Claudia Lopez Perales', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/103514212367216426749/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Gj_ykv3er7kRCsQ3fLbdmNKkAewUe6M4U7VtggAOQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '11 months ago', 'text': "Spectacular viewing of famous Mexican artists and various other nationalities. Their room setup was amazing! Way better than the one at SA. Staff spoke English. During Day of the Dead celebration, staff was dressed up and allowed us to take pictures of them. They were all so nice and welcoming! There was also a horror section which I did not take part of but based on everyone's screams I'm going to assume it was good.", 'time': 1572878815}, {'author_name': 'Evelyn', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/103349709027804218511/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GhPYY-aZLHn6LA73lGi6zu1XFpucJ1na3DeKup40Q=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '8 months ago', 'text': "I went on a school trip, as a teacher, and some students aged 8 cried knowing there's a horror section and also in the tunnel from the Ripley Museum, so I would recommend this place for people over 10 years old. The kids enjoyed the rest of the museum though, especially the 4D experience. The staff were really helpful and entertaining, they had a lot of energy and helped a lot when the kids had to queue with interactive activities and chants. The food and beverages is a bit overpriced, Icee drinks are $62 mxn, but some interesting souvenirs are sold such as wax hands and carnivorous plants.", 'time': 1581256072}, {'author_name': 'Jesus Covarrubias', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/100571789964914577421/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Gg5Gvz-9uVBkuL1WyF9_CNPKvAFIYeT_5_e4_tnCa4=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '8 months ago', 'text': 'Greatest of all Wax museums so far!\nBig exhibition, lots of different rooms, all kinds; real & fiction.', 'time': 1578957070}, {'author_name': 'Jesse Castillo', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/102133632285830589190/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-6buyFL3IN14/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/AMZuuck_8QvximYheRMeTL0ikdwhsBFw-Q/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3/photo.jpg', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': 'Great experience, highly recommended if you come to Mexico City. The wax status look so real and incredible! An awesome experience.', 'time': 1566578039}, {'author_name': 'Zoe Del Valle', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/110900421055760069943/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-7FVkG1i0DqA/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/AMZuucmkgIwnGXzr1z3ghwHNuShZ4WEPqA/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3/photo.jpg', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '8 months ago', 'text': 'Kids love it. Some pieces are really well made. It is a place to have fun, go with friends or family and take tons of photos. The statues are from all over the world from all fields of professions.', 'time': 1578881620}]

column15: [{'author_name': 'Angie Zepeda', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/100791042461783418596/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GjwVuhK3us0mDRgx7md7GwLNDWPIqFQRWumGXU32Q=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '2 years ago', 'text': 'This is really Mexican gourmet food!\n\nI love desserts specially the xoconoztle 😍, the service is excellent, the food is delicious and abundant dishes, the building is like to go back in  the time machine to Mexican colonial era, really nice.', 'time': 1526185901}, {'author_name': 'Alexandra Johnson', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/107529495383100630979/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-YLqvb4oYnFc/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/AMZuucmsG02-fVfm7kwPPMVDFjlMDvFhCA/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3/photo.jpg', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '11 months ago', 'text': 'Delicious, adorable spot!!! We had a blast with my grandma and mom!', 'time': 1572475198}, {'author_name': 'Patrick Harris', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/107290791610229390897/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/-8G28h7IrXPQ/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/AMZuucnQ5C08LaOFVPpy08Ray7wJg_ooNQ/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5/photo.jpg', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': "Excellent assortment of different authentic Mexican foods, with a variety of both seafood and land animals and a good set of healthier fares as well. Prices are extremely reasonable for the quality of the food. Parking is secure and valet which is a bonus. Guacamole and salsa are made tableside at whatever level of picante you prefer. Menus in English and Spanish and staff are quite good at speaking English if needed. Didn't have a chance to work through their tequila and mezcal list but I was told it's very good. But maybe they should have a guide.', 'time': 1570108644}, {'author_name': 'Kristin Vernon', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/103360195698920032626/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GjxA03pmMipc_9M10Vr9agkHiWtK8M5X37K2yaBLA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '7 months ago', 'text': 'Rather interesting little museum in a a gorgeous area', 'time': 1583193950}, {'author_name': 'Antonio Callà', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/116209087343169770973/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/-8HuapYaQs_E/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/AMZuucl7X4CiXBMueHmw-5wliWoxLVzzZg/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4/photo.jpg', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '7 months ago', 'text': 'Both macabre and educational. Sadly, no photography permitted.', 'time': 1582870478}, {'author_name': 'Scott Crisman Sworts', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/112223631984941128300/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GgivPWqCIz25JkZMr28sV3DcBBDrfZJJqGx2z8q30c=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba8', 'rating': 4, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': "This is probably the gold standard of museums dedicated to torture, with pretty much every atrocity committed by humans on display, and most of them are original.  They do address the fact that some of these are actually fantasy, or at least the product of imagination.  The main drawback of that it doesn't delve deeply into context of why the torture happened, especially with the Inquisition, but it does give a good idea of how the devices worked.  One thing though, this isn't a museum for kids, unless you want a lot of questions, and possibly significant nightmares.", 'time': 1562634457}]

column15: [{'author_name': 'Krithika Mukund', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/114183612576586751395/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GgP32OTbav79SMjEsY0FJYNyR9RKt6pgLKrEEM3qg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a month ago', 'text': 'The last 3km to reach the place are on a bumpy unpaved stretch but it is worthwhile to reach such a place of beauty. One could walk all around the lake in about an hour. One has the view of the lake throughout the circuit, do not venture into the forest behind . We went on a weekday and had the place nearly to ourselves. The zipline was not functioning. There were several cabanas, fishing, camping and barbecue areas, picnic spots and toilets dotted all around. The entry fee of 30 mxn per adult,15 mxn per child was reasonable. Parking was free but appeared to be only limited space available for it. Please do not leave any trash behind!', 'time': 1599003209}, {'author_name': 'Superman RH', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/111199336432047127694/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GggmFzk9YReaGdJjCmM53Vs0UXaPZG56x3rBGZaLg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '2 months ago', 'text': 'Beautiful place, a little bit scary at night and so noisy in rain season with thunder and lightnings, i will suggest have more bathrooms and food areas. Be careful when walking and climbing with rain you could slip and fall', 'time': 1596781597}, {'author_name': 'Isaac Medrano', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/102572742728076736003/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GgwnC4pKRpT43qRgXh4EJ7YF-Dp7P4BwYTztdNy=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '9 months ago', 'text': 'What a nice place! column15:
[{'author_name': 'Giovanna Chavez', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/111403691329848665976/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Giiwsy9ZigaqcxncOgsiSJ5XRM7uP6dRpQMRs5AHw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': 'Excellent costumer service. Small spot but worth waiting to get a table. All kinds of tacos were wonderful, they have such a large array of salsas. Don't forget to get "chicharrón de queso" which is a cheese crust rolled in a big cylinder you crack and eat, unbelievable, so good! They also have beers and their agua de horchata is to die for.', 'time': 1550190147}, {'author_name': 'David Topete Salmorán', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/102803359626396243143/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GjBVGXDfkG5Wf5FlSAjhem8eum0dE3aQkBIHSsy=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '8 months ago', 'text': 'Best option for non pork lovers. Wonderful idea! Delicious tacos.', 'time': 1579263522}, {'author_name': 'Richard O Flaherty', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/106666076333122838842/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-VsvJg-Md8Rs/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/AMZuuclAU2KpQa4lLxK2gEDgq3vKmJvRww/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4/photo.jpg', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': 'Fantastic atmosphere, attentive and friendly staff, authentic and tasty food - only 3 minutes walk from the Fiesta Inn hotel', 'time': 1553418189}, {'author_name': 'Elena Oros', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/103424608868022902210/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GhBOgoXFgs_wowSvXEkUxW9SoUVAPky4VMrGXRf5g=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 4, 'relative_time_description': '11 months ago', 'text': 'The place is a small joint with two levels and no more than 15 tables for parties of no more than 6 people. The turn out takes a title long in the evenings and that's why you'll probably have to jot down your name in the waiting list they have at the entrance. The menu options are limited, but it is because their specialty is sirloin, so you have the tacos and "volcanes". Tacos= soft corn tortillas. Volcanes= tostadas (flatten hard shell (tortillas)) with cheese. There are combo options for big appetites or groups, and the selection of soda pops and fruit flavored waters (not sure about beers). Some deserts are also offered, but didn't try any.
Ambiance is relaxed, a little warm on the top, but was like having heaters in a cool rainy evening.
The quality of the tacos is really good, they also offer a wide variety of salsas, that is a plus (red smokey one and guacamole my favorite), but volcanes are my thing (easier to handle and bite). Service was a little slow, not sure whether it was because we were on the top floor, and price wise it is more expensive than (street) tacos stands, but definitely worth it.
Limited place to park, so think about parking somewhere else and walk or Uber.
Will definitely go back.', 'time': 1572892997}, {'author_name': 'S. T.', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/106697830021080604696/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-Ov--hozbRsg/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/AMZuuck5YinTkMjnju9a3WwL3Z5sRvRs3w/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3/photo.jpg', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': 'Awesome flavors. Whether you like them well done, but I strongly recommend asking for medium rare... house special... the best ones ever!', 'time': 1556231655}]

[{'author_name': 'Joel Cordova', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/107555244381527653804/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GgeoLwMkWhDuNHTwFrgn3hDhL8AZoiSg73RhukLvcY=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6', 'rating': 4, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': 'Admission is free. Small museum. 3 stories of exhibitions. I visited for the first time. Interesting. The Mexican movie star exhibit is interesting.', 'time': 1568747701}, {'author_name': 'Nadja Mayumi', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/110579653494906717299/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Gi85S_zf4YlR7wRUgBWGYOrF_oRGci1CtqIJh_IQA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': "A great museum always with a great exibition! And the best, is for free, Wednesday to Monday, from 10h to 18h. Going there, don't miss the visit to the Cafe and bookstore and the roof top. Has a nice view. The only thing is, the roof top isn't wheelchair accessible. The rest of the museum is. Great place to go by yourself, with friends, family or the special one. If you are in Mexico City don't let to go there.", 'time': 1543554774}, {'author_name': "Victor O'Farrill", 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/100308312749819228575/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Gg0fwakI_WwVt4FU00OgYN5o49gPlKCA5lKN8SSKdM=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '7 months ago', 'text': "First of all you feel you're well welcomed.

The museography was excellent.

Once you seen it, reach the highest floor, a great terrace, where you will have coffee and meander the shop...", 'time': 1582050612}, {'author_name': 'Giovanna Florencia Guzman Garza', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/114336035502521684823/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Gjjp5EIMe0SBgjaRnWw1MiOfIZTgMMOpo4e3dCD8Q=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '12 months ago', 'text': 'Great place to go and see artists of many kind, some of them include Miguel Covarrubias, Lola Álvarez Bravo, José María Lupercio, Agustín Jiménez and my personal favourite Leopoldo Méndez.

Not only that but it also includes a nice rooftop view with a cafeteria and mini library.', 'time': 1570734929}, {'author_name': 'Shelby Elkins', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/105679139196460752954/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GiCiq6-BgoRJ-ZJCBpuGAdKGml_EIrv4la416QjXA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '2 years ago', 'text': 'This museum is a must see in Mexico City! They are multiple floors of different exhibits. There is also a rooftop that has a coffee bar and gift shop. Entrance was free, but you have to let them hold your bag once you get to the stairwell. Everyone was very nice and welcoming. I loved the small art they had that was very detailed. I highly recommend and would visit again with friends.', 'time': 1520304422}]

Sin duda la mejor opción en renta de espacios por hora. Súper céntrico! Bike friendly, cuenta con servicio de cafetería y barra! Luces, proyector, sillas y mesas (originales). column15: [{'author_name': 'Jacqueline Torres', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/107194009494311527519/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GgJmYDx1CwHvVt7_b0vhQRhbOQQuqdUl62R0U4f=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': 'Awesome museum, very educational and informative.', 'time': 1567275170}, {'author_name': 'Cheryl K', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/109310630010525520697/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-J8bmpvQwPIo/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/AMZuuckTbMcqQXzr_bN1SLITPFq1Qyww4g/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo/photo.jpg', 'rating': 3, 'relative_time_description': '5 years ago', 'text': 'Quite disappointing and it\'s sad that others think it\'s worthy.  The fact that it took until 2012 for a museum about the indigenous Mexicans to open contradicts all the propaganda stated within.  Add that it\'s a small museum with only 2 rooms and there is no cohesion of the items and info on display only worsens the situation.  It\'s as though a few people were sitting around a table one day trying to come up with a reason to create yet another museum in this city and they said, "Hey!  Ya know what we don\'t have?  A museum about the indigenous!"  There isn\'t even a map showing Mexico and where all the indigenous tribes are located.  Sad.  The room with 3 video screens is a waste because each is so close to the other that you can\'t hear what\'s being said.  Better if the indigenous had opened a museum about themselves.', 'time': 1425861912}, {'author_name': 'omar inclan', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/107296251687933259921/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-smTdz02TaDA/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/AMZuucljGoCV1aSS-K6bL9S8HyddBJ1u9w/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4/photo.jpg', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': 'I love', 'time': 1567082088}, {'author_name': 'Yann Luna', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/108450357801759708979/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Gjq6n0GDK8aCEv72FNnNVyvd1Nw18e0X6cE-V4Fdw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba2', 'rating': 3, 'relative_time_description': '3 years ago', 'text': 'San Bartolomé Atlatlahucan', 'time': 1504673473}, {'author_name': 'bryan yankee show', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/100395115579968315280/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GiB5GcsvZ70nI6VL5Jmbj2FPmna33c8xOnKz7RL=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '11 months ago', 'text': 'Super.', 'time': 1571782817}]

This restaurant serves Baja style Mexican food which is more like what we get in California.

No mistake their cuisine is very good and their tequila collection too much to sample for one night. I do npt really remember all the dishes I had that night except for the Baja style shrimp taco, a beef dish and a couple of others I do not remember the names of. But they were all good and I will return.

The decor is modern but very cosy. There were groups that were smoking and very noisy but we asked to sit in a different area and all was good.', 'time': 1570090585}, {'author_name': 'Niccolo Spataro', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/100957553601759795862/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Gj7sYSLG-RdSv33fBcC5EKNsqf0fD1pSG2PQjqb=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': 'Great Mexican Food, Service and Decor. column15:
[{'author_name': 'Amanda Crook', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/113458124621196445763/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-B3sIf1OBFn8/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/AMZuuckJLnqPradw1Gvsv0guAbWvSA1LKg/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4/photo.jpg', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '6 months ago', 'text': 'This place was amazing, possibly my favorite meal on the whole trip. The drinks were superb and very photogenic (as was all of the food). We had ordered steak and the duck confit ravioli, both were cooked and seasoned perfectly. For dessert we had the tasting menu of 5 desserts. Each one was unique and tasty. The first one even got us a special interactive experience of going into the kitchen! The staff were all very kind, professional, and helpful. The views from the restaurant were amazing. We will definitely return the next time!', 'time': 1584830847}, {'author_name': 'Luis Jr. Peña', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/106241461761110185768/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GjbqmfXVzZtBwJnbefOkbMHifRYei2QNiB5BismKQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5', 'rating': 3, 'relative_time_description': '8 months ago', 'text': 'The ambiance was great and the view was spectacular.  The food, just ok.  Our steaks came out way underdone and when asked to be cooked more, they took a very long time.  As the rest of the table had finished eating, and were waiting for the steak, we decided to cancel The waitress was rude and refused to bring the manager.  Finally we met him and ht was very kind and generous.  Omar, is his name.  We will most likely NOT go back there.', 'time': 1579536910}, {'author_name': 'Jeff Hirai', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/103454841601856668726/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GimCFSCDlw5wKypk3VUIv1nQTc4b957b-dTUNrQ9Q=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 3, 'relative_time_description': '8 months ago', 'text': "Good view of the national palace but the food tastes basic. We ordered the 5 course appetiser with wine pairing which was underwhelming. The only thing that was worth remembering is the ahi tuna on tortilla topped with a prawn cracker. Paired wines were low quality and didn't compliment any of the dishes. If you just want the view, I would stick with just the drink menu with a glass you prefer rather then what is recommended.", 'time': 1579919832}, {'author_name': 'Farrah Ratnaike', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/104147198488410210858/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GgnYyIkUmjQxTtH0XbbQbi7iEYcYefMgIdAn7F7ZA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '10 months ago', 'text': 'Delicious food, excellent hospitality and not over the top pricey. Tasting menu was really good.

For a change, fine dining was served very promptly which was a refreshing change instead of the usual  lengthy service times.', 'time': 1574599832}, {'author_name': 'Rodrigo Arrambide', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/111575538849899642566/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-kGcqNavnaHw/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/AMZuuckMX5G-8NsGb6MEgTSyXgisQBHFIg/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3/photo.jpg', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': "Amazing restaurant with food that is simply : Superior.
First, the staff was warm and welcoming, we got given a very nice table.
Then the ambiance of the place is clearly made for an upscale crowd. Good music, quality furniture and decor, very nice and appreciated.
We had several cocktails from the menu that were a very nice balance of flavor and the kick of the alcohol.
Then the main component: The food...
There isn't much to say more than: 5/5. We had the tasting menu that was very well explained and we got the opportunity to visit the kitchen and talk with the chef.
It is a culinary experience that is worthy of being one of the best tables in Mexico.
Congratulations to the chef and Team for an outstanding job.", 'time': 1557461670}]

column15: [{'author_name': 'Diana Ruff', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/112056801724237521851/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/-RaVR8Xi5zCw/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/AMZuuck0gz3ROZw-_iXqxp_XcBTLpf1Itg/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4/photo.jpg', 'rating': 3, 'relative_time_description': '8 months ago', 'text': 'Cost was 80 pesos, which is the same as Chapultepec Castle but with much less stuff. The focus is on mostly Mexican revolutions from approximately 1700 to the early 20th century. The museum is completely made up of informational wall placards and dioramas. The dioramas are great but there are no other visual displays other than that. The only other display, which was really awesome, was at the end in a circular room, which I assume is the center of the snail shell, which held a book that I think was the original Mexican Constitution, and had a yellow stained glass ceiling and a giant Mexican eagle. Since I was translating every wall placard into English, it took longer than I expected to get through the museum, but still only took me about an hour and a half. If you are a native Spanish speaker or can read Spanish, I assume it would take you less than an hour.', 'time': 1579635422}, {'author_name': 'Shai Ghelberg', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/105691477810586363760/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Gh4l2ndmcXe8p3Y3aVCzuY5kqRlLprNiLkJJmZ3dw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5', 'rating': 4, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': "Everything is in Spanish :(\nBut the maquettes are very beautiful and the building itself is very special. Its one huge spiral that's very fun to go through. The roof has many amazing cacti and a brief explanation of each species.\nIt's a pretty cheap attraction you can definitely spend an hour or two here.", 'time': 1567956046}, {'author_name': 'Rose Cavenagh', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/111079475350765653168/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Gh726WeYK4WHVzBibn_SM7zHCZDMhRFUWWuS9EA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 4, 'relative_time_description': '7 months ago', 'text': 'I think you can get a good initiation to some of the history of Mexico and all the players from other countries who wanted a piece or all of this beautiful country. Take your time and read the information with each picture or representation. It will make you want to know more.', 'time': 1583101220}, {'author_name': 'Lars Edeen III', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/113581345379898526448/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Gizx0gLu5RJjdRXG35giWYL0KPRpFXPZBUt9wTxqg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 2, 'relative_time_description': '7 months ago', 'text': 'I would avoid this museum if you do not read/ speak Spanish. Está algo escondido y fue mera casualidad que terminé ahí pero es una experiencia bastante nueva.
La comida no es algo muy fuera de lo común, buen sazón, precios algo elevados de lo normal para el tipo de menú que tienen a mí parecer.
Atención espectacular, los y las meseras son muy amables y cordiales.', 'time': 1545885250}, {'author_name': 'Xhaarts is here', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/108270356080599477411/reviews', 'language': 'es', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Gi0vjKfES3Sqi_gK3z1GdE6Gyx5Pl1-pNxdoQAA-3s=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': 'Muy rico y aunque no es tan barato, la atención es muy buena y el día de hoy que se festeja a los papás hubo un cantante.', 'time': 1560732316}, {'author_name': 'DEC Espinosa', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/111831278914734161023/reviews', 'language': 'es', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Ggoj7Hz6TbZJfpNZbU7kQznmZLWneKXFQmOoOkLMQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '11 months ago', 'text': 'Un lugar de antojitos mexicanos con un muy buen sazón!!!

Me tocó probar la sopa de médula y la de hongos ambas muy buenas me ahorran el viaje a la marquesa.

Compartimos en la mesa un molcajete grande y de entrada algo muy bueno es que no le ponen pollo, la cantidad de carne es suficiente para cuatro personas!!!

En esta ocasión el consumo promedio fue de $220 por persona

Muy buen servicio de la chica que nos atendió la mesa', 'time': 1573362540}]

Great ambiance and well trained,friendly staff. Highly recommend it for a special lunch or romantic dinner.', 'time': 1551566744}, {'author_name': 'Sergio Nieto', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/100489466016498345615/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-IjptKWMeFC4/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/AMZuuck5R_TtGqLiGiwnsKmMZejCnvVHDw/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4/photo.jpg', 'rating': 4, 'relative_time_description': '2 years ago', 'text': 'Very cool place, great service and good food. column15: [{'author_name': 'Will Hunter', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/110534888132526384364/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Gjf1SDhCbz4sJKzFXg2zFE2I_8H5Se0IkDof_QWCg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba2', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '7 months ago', 'text': 'A beautiful place, a real treasure. Grounds are very relaxing. Cafe is also good. Highly recommended & you can also deepen your understanding of Mexican art and the people who made & shaped it.', 'time': 1583041031}, {'author_name': 'Amanda Crook', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/113458124621196445763/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-B3sIf1OBFn8/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/AMZuuckJLnqPradw1Gvsv0guAbWvSA1LKg/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4/photo.jpg', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '6 months ago', 'text': 'The property is very beautiful and spacious with lots of peacocks. For any one that is a lover of Frida or Diego artwork, this is a must. A great stop on your way to or from Xochomilco.', 'time': 1584831383}, {'author_name': 'Josh Rickards', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/102705740046331751637/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GgLEAHEA02mbmdSpd079izTYWwG9Jmja1_fJ1PhPQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '7 months ago', 'text': 'This place is incredible and a must visit. More to see here than Museo Frida Kahlo and for much less of the price. You can easily spend over half the day here with a bunch of eye candy and great spots for photos. So much history! This was one of our highlights during our visit to Mexico City', 'time': 1581932118}, {'author_name': 'José Carlos G.', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/113247287526301708270/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GjJCcZ_Kqv3zzt3ycNk4YnZr1AWegTW0QK53U2it6E=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '6 months ago', 'text': "This is one of my favorites museums to visit in south Mexico city, it has the biggest art collection in the world of Frida Kahlo and Diego Rivera's work in the world including  Frida Self Portraits!! Theres is a whole room dedicated to sunrise and sunse paintings by Diefo Rivera.Dolores Olmedo was sponsor and close friend of the couple. Among the permanent exhibition there are  also Mexican classic  furniture and pottery ( talavera), the colonial style building is quite a place to admire. An unexpected and amazing surprise you might find, the many free peacocks that wander the gardens and jump around from ground to ceilings. There are also live xolo dogs in closed gardens. There are galleries for temporary exhibitions, the Dia de muertos offering art is very famous in  November. The museum shop is very big and has a great variety of items including many Frida Kahlo themed stuff. Bathrooms are clean and spacious. It is close to Xochimilco canals, you could plan a visit with both locations in one day. Did not visit the restaurant, but was crowded and smelled delicious like mole sauce.", 'time': 1584231491}, {'author_name': 'Rachael Fajardo', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/102939397027843105801/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GjjVOBELPnpWpmDMMcHd6KtXDGtHXW118f2B6hF=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba2', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '8 months ago', 'text': 'This is such a pleasant place to visit on a beautiful day. I love the gardens and all the animals. The exhibits are thoughtful and a nice size. You can easily see an entire exhibit without losing anyone in your group, and since most are in different buildings, those built in breaks make this the perfect museum for groups where not everyone is deeply interested in art.', 'time': 1579038887}]

column15: [{'author_name': 'Ilona Rybka', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/100326993888643790188/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GggRVSCFwTMxkIsi-faDgVFbaD_r4UjXlY0m1aOAQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba2', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '4 weeks ago', 'text': 'Amazing experience. Be prepare for a long queue even if you bought your ticket online. This place attract a lot of people and it is maybe a bit difficult to be there - at the end it is just a house with a limited capacity. The place is very well preserved and beautiful. A lot of personal stuff so you can imagine life of Frida. Definitely a must-visit place!', 'time': 1599611596}, {'author_name': 'JONATHAN A', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/102132563616213468506/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GhkzvKv_fNvn4mNs4MoS1Ya4tAaxZIhClolYbL9HHI=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a month ago', 'text': "The Blue House in Coyoacan is where Frida Kahlo was born, lived with Diego Rivera, and died. It is now the Frida Kahlo Museum. Though crowded nowadays, it is not to be missed. Inside and out, Kahlo's life and work are on display. Beautifully acessible and maintained.", 'time': 1598481141}, {'author_name': 'sal paradise', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/114076134028921245736/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-v_jfDBNKrOk/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/AMZuuckn5Of4iJqrz0l5kmx9C2gpDjBY6g/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo/photo.jpg', 'rating': 1, 'relative_time_description': 'a week ago', 'text': 'You absolutely must buy your tickets online with a credit card. The have a little hustle going at the front gate, where if you pay with cash they pretend to be unable to dispense change because of covid. I have never encountered this BS rule anywhere else in Mexico City', 'time': 1601052597}, {'author_name': 'Johnnyomd', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/112200650547814147972/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Giq1nC27fOG-4wP7knhtvrOAIQpg336P2hSOPjK=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '2 weeks ago', 'text': 'Nice to see where she lived! She was such a badass; way ahead of her time', 'time': 1600490048}, {'author_name': 'Emily Anderson', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/117613627475394346752/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GiJ4dOaq19WxOSjFXCUBm5Dx0hG9hs-od6JLl-GC-s=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '7 months ago', 'text': "The line is a thing. The bigger line that goes to the left of the entrance is if you do not have tickets purchased... When we got there it wrapped around the building. The line to the right is if you have tickets. We almost considered doing one of the local tours not this to skip the line ... Probably should have done that.\n\nThe museum was great. I'd highly recommend for any Frida.. or art fans", 'time': 1581797268}]

Too many vendors throughout the park , but they don't  break into our gathering and disturb us..

We played with some huge squirrels during a break, was fun.", 'time': 1600858044}, {'author_name': 'Mohamed belfakih', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/105343172516050966347/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Gg73PvT2nxHs9BCJIH8huq6gM_yHk4u0gd8-j6B=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a month ago', 'text': 'It is widely accepted that Taj Mahal is the best-known attraction in India. After 17 years of construction, the Taj Mahal is known as the most beautiful monument of love.', 'time': 1598786232}, {'author_name': 'Nico RN', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/111519432392243781413/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-qQ629UFwLh4/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/AMZuuckEIk3jkw7jUiSHqsAlDBPwB8G-2w/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo/photo.jpg', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'in the last week', 'text': 'A fantastic open space in the middle of the city. I highly recommend to visit both.  Lots of food, clothing,  and toys vendors.", 'time': 1580177196}]
