column15:
[{'author_name': 'Jennifer Wu', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/103571982152110956660/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GhX0CydaZ6JN2XS3cn9PqIOEfHP0VPrM5paLEY9fw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 2, 'relative_time_description': 'a month ago', 'text': 'My husband and I booked this place for two nights and was confirmed by hotel that it was okay to check in at 1pm however when we got there, the gates was closed. Called the phone number several times and was unable to get through. Ask the officers on the street to call and find out for me if they were open and they were also unable to get in contact with hotel. So 1.5 hours later at, we decided to just get a room at the hotel across the street. Right when we got into our new room, they call us and say that they are waiting for us.........

We did not get a refund. They said that no one called.... pretty upsetting. They say the gates were closed but the hotel in the building is still open. If you are expecting guests, you should have a valid phone number posted and someone at the gate at all times to open it for the arriving guests. That just my opinion. Overall, it’s a great location if you decide to stay here. Tacos across from the hotel are excellent and cheap. Just that the hotel is poorly managed.', 'time': 1599230097}, {'author_name': 'burton cooke', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/104869614043221501222/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GgKdnfhkSVW4igEb-NvXRwooHCzINmJcJWvpc5I=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '6 months ago', 'text': 'This is a review of my experience as a guest at the hotel.  I had high expectations after seeing the photos of the unique rooms, and in person it exceeded all expectations.  The room I stayed in had a fantastic atmosphere and was immaculate in its cleanliness.   The free breakfast each morning was delicious and the waitstaff in the restaurant were all very courteous.  Additionally, they bring complimentary dessert to your room every evening.  The hotel staff as well were all very courteous and helpful.  The only issue I had was that sometimes it took the hot water a long time to get going in the shower.  That was literally it.  A delightful stay all around.', 'time': 1584248610}, {'author_name': 'Kavan TheKid', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/102725395301698939665/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Gh4ks-d7cXIEkaYMNJUC5lbjnnJOpkGU2jXNrEYGFg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '7 months ago', 'text': "This was hands down the GREATEST hotel experience of my life. I am telling you right now. If you are going to Mexico City, THIS is the PLACE to stay. Everyone on the staff is so incredibly kind it is surreal. I have never, ever been treated this good at a hotel and I have stayed at hotels across the world. The rooms are incredible and spacious. The hotel is part of an art gallery and a cafe. Both are also phenomenal. Truly one of the best experiences in my whole life was staying at this place.  You are missing out if you don't stay here.", 'time': 1582754902}, {'author_name': 'Can Kırış', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/113106057233769135095/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GhVB-FPnhdSvziJLIll7JJsOjHK2l-3SquCK0KQ2g=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 2, 'relative_time_description': '9 months ago', 'text': "Don't visit here thinking that it's a design museum. We did precisely that and we regret it. This place is a design store and a restaurant and it looks like they decided to open a museum. Not everybody can and should be able to call their spare room a museum.
While we visited there was an exhibition for a graphic design project about the day of the dead. The ticket was for 55 pesos with the guide (the guide was the only good thing about our experience.)
After paying that 55pesos, they tell you that you can buy the posters for 350pesos. If everything is for sale, why is it paid enterence? It makes no sense.
If you're seriously interested 8n designer, or a designer, avoid the place as it's just disappointing.", 'time': 1577144292}, {'author_name': 'Laura Papa', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/115819695979513967830/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Gh7KhzwCBlBrtGzb2slHErbsgmqQuHevECJwF-D72w=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 1, 'relative_time_description': '10 months ago', 'text': "One of the worst experiences I had in a cafe! I went with a male friend and I was completely ignored by the host-guy, in a very sexist way: he greeted my friend and pretended I wasn't there; when I asked for the menu, he gave it to my friend. I asked for a mango soda and they gave me plain water. My friend asked for a drink with almond milk, they came with plain. Vegan menu has the same options as regular, but more expensive. They refused to cancel one order even 2minutes after we've done it. And finally I'm writing this review in English because although we were Spanish speaker, they continue to speak with us in English. Just don't go there.", 'time': 1575775631}]

[{'author_name': 'Jose Carlos Alarcon Lopez', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/103393454877034258894/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Gg9ybyEA5HH9WgxcIkWZcrRNswjG4_hXoCXp5e5=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5', 'rating': 4, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': 'For many years this location has had theater plus that are commercial hits.
It’s conveniently located in a shopping mall with the metro Cuahutemoc  station.
Food court is on the ground floor.
Entrance to orchestra and mezzanine ticket holders is on the first floor and entrance to upper level seats is on the fourth floor.
Generally 2 plays are showing in each of the theaters, so beware for crows when the shows are over .', 'time': 1564418009}, {'author_name': 'Monica Rivera', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/107074390665313624214/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GhY69r2-1TAhg1-kPBHM-YXoRSzKvU2woyVt8m-Iw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6', 'rating': 4, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': 'Nice venue, friendly staff. The theatre itself is comfortable, not too big, clean. This place is located inside a mall where you can find some small shops and quick dinning options. The parking is great as they charge a fixed tariff (60 pesos). WCs are available and very clean.', 'time': 1560094186}, {'author_name': 'Manuel Rodriguez', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/106165168188219094741/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GiCL1z1Z1bpbLTpEXoCPZdfejX1Qkw3qZoqNwaoCw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '2 months ago', 'text': 'Ok', 'time': 1596754919}, {'author_name': 'TMB77', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/101389690095159749785/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/-iA6t0kSzdtI/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/AMZuucnCmZxVwSZBpHEcPm9m6M5PAzvAvw/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4/photo.jpg', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': "It's a big center for buying, some restaurants, a theatre and also you can find an awesome subterranean accuarium. Love this place highly recommend!', 'time': 1584218105}, {'author_name': 'Andrea Pace', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/117975720869765983607/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GghwnLa2oJegOdTSautiU8oOpTI_Yet1b-gHCDeow=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '2 years ago', 'text': 'I live here in Mexico from a year now, I’m super foodie and love to try new things / new places.. Like the Tito cups but made out of actual copper.  Lots of silver but IMHO the craftsmanship for the silver jewelry in Mexico is substandard.  Uneven shapes and dull finishes.", 'time': 1595075143}, {'author_name': 'Barbara Gerhardt', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/100546474123975394288/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GgP0nBY9NYQCDQ5Aj2d7EdHNQo-3Qt7wedu82j-yZo=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'in the last week', 'text': 'Amazing place to buy presents from Mexico! column15:
[{'author_name': 'Cristian Nava Diaz', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/114917022188760570184/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Gj2yUB_l-_3ztk88pGeEN74X_3Erl7a5193Xc5W=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '6 months ago', 'text': 'Fonda 99.99 is a restaurant that specialize in Yucatecan Cuisine.\xa0Everything we have tried is delicious. Last time we visited the place we had the broad bean soup and chicken meat and both were superb. The waiter was very fast and helpful.  Without a doubt,  I will visit the restaurant the next time I am around.', 'time': 1585286529}, {'author_name': 'Alessandro Labelli', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/102758151592415481418/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GhVdNu7iJfbYXgdIZkhbO9z4M53R8ToA5N-wYXuwQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '7 months ago', 'text': "If you're a fan of traditional Yucatan cousin, you can't miss this place. Together with Humberto's it's one of the best places in town in terms of flavors of the food and its price. Services is good too. However, you have to be comfortable with a potentially long wait. I arrived shortly before 2pm on a Sunday and had to wait a solid 30 min for a table.

The menu is not huge, yet it offers traditional options. I tried panuchos de cochinita, tacos de lechón, doraditas de pescado, and despite the hot day, a lime soup. All tasted amazing. For dessert, I had a marquesita, which are made on a stand just outside on the sidewalk.

Service was very good, although a bit slow. Price was very competitive.", 'time': 1583116727}, {'author_name': 'Omar Gonzalez', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/107725746670996064890/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GhF6rWXEPR1IGylLIgkXjZuyWZtvcJeh4podFWPJw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '7 months ago', 'text': "If you want to try the real Mexican food of the southern part of the country, this is THE best place in Mexico to do it. Casual home-like vibe, this place holds the best Yucatecan food in the country, cheap and tasty, great and fast service.
If you want to come, be prepared for waiting at least 20 minutes, but I can assure you it's worth the wait.", 'time': 1582446561}, {'author_name': 'Gil Posner', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/102046724363398211106/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GjmgMWw1yEW7ymQycKDlFfFtHOF9aD3Zx68wbuJkw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': 'Excellent experience of the Yucateco cuisine. Not centrally located but worth the ride. We were there for a Sunday lunch and found ourselves the only foreigners (always a good sign). We arrived right on the opening hour. The queue was building up pretty fast and by the time we were finished there was probably an hour waiting time. We ordered a variety of traditional dishes and our favourites were Sopa de lima, Panuchos de cochinita and Pavo relleno negro. Service was fast although the place was packed.', 'time': 1550436675}, {'author_name': 'Diego QR', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/108456280105145208727/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GhSvdO2aoH7E9bLxVaUQb0z4itCGYanuzyZdtk5BA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 4, 'relative_time_description': '2 years ago', 'text': 'Great yucatán food. I️ particularly recommend Panuchos of Cochinita Pibil. The only downside is that the restaurant is small so there can be lines to enter as well as the food not being very hot. All in all, a must-visit cuisine place.', 'time': 1512512563}]

I can't visit without at least a bowl... and no sharing.", 'time': 1563743578}, {'author_name': 'Armando Gonzalez', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/108414029607291626280/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GgG5E0Ji6spiUTzQjkx8Q874aUT385FRfVg0xaA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '2 years ago', 'text': 'The place is quite small, it only has 6 or 8 tables so there could be a queue to get in, which is the only thing I disliked. I specially liked the mole and carne molida tostadas and the Aztec soup.', 'time': 1530460511}, {'author_name': 'Charlotte PARIS', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/111472736773403233057/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Gg1HIHE_H9gtarXIlpo5M66pQVnv_asZ3Hx22t0=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '11 months ago', 'text': "A smallish restaurant, with around 8 tables of 4, super nice and helpful staff, quick service, and.. Es recomendable llegar temprano pues el lugar no es muy grande. Alrededor de la 1 es buena hora para asistir. En resumen Aunque es un lugar pequeño A mi parecer es una de las mejores opciones de la zona', 'time': 1579306872}]

column15:
[{'author_name': 'Francisco Arevalo Sastre', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/117934716908755107181/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GjkdgN2MQtyNHwyZigkC9gzB4gfYmRDGA3mp7z6bg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'in the last week', 'text': 'Amazing restaurant, a little expensive, however it is a real culinary experience, great atmosphere', 'time': 1601692763}, {'author_name': 'Myra S', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/115963670618986909686/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/-wNI_YIaDC6E/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/AMZuucnwOovpbbu1Xdu4k8Q25i3ed98Sow/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba2/photo.jpg', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '2 years ago', 'text': 'I cannot say enough good things about this restaurant. The service was impeccable, the food was beautiful and delicious, and the space is stunning. If you can, sit on the patio overlooking the garden.

Our lunch took 3.5 hours. This is not a place you eat at quickly and go. You take your time here and savor the experience of being there.

We got a bottle of wine that was really reasonably priced and lots of food. We joked that the price tag would be outrageous once we got the bill but it wasn’t bad at all. If this restaurant was in the USA, the prices would be double or triple what they are.', 'time': 1519015031}, {'author_name': 'Dan Lam', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/118034639154165574533/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Gj-7z71Ho7jmtoLEpX2yn_heiJdoPSPtsPSye2fCg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 3, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': 'I agree with the fellow reviewers here. The restaurant is beautiful and has a very lovely ambience. The architecture is an added bonus for design lovers with some unique design touches. The food was delicious but could also be had at other restaurants nearby for much less. The standouts included their Tortilla Soup that came with a separate plate of garnishes and tortilla chips to add based on your taste level. The churros and tacos were delicious also. It was a finer eating experience than your typical meal and the service was impeccable.', 'time': 1554828109}, {'author_name': 'Jason Vasquez', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/103521744459788925064/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Gj1enPjxTAaMP_BdlnfYjeqki-0wQiQS40gK4p07A=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3', 'rating': 4, 'relative_time_description': '6 months ago', 'text': 'Beautiful ambiance, delicious food, lovely and attentive service. The hostess was unwelcoming and seemed very unhappy. Aside from that, definitely recommend this place. The Chicken and Mole and Fish Tacos Al Pastor were fabulous. Reservations were made on Open Table. Enjoy!', 'time': 1584115233}, {'author_name': 'Pablo Ben', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/116055486866505545366/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GgC20vcePYEx2ewp7pK6srqOIWZvEu-2NxW6TjBiQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 4, 'relative_time_description': '8 months ago', 'text': "Very nice ambiance, nice for an intimate talk with a friend or for a date. I had a drink at their bar but didn't try their food. The space layout and architecture is breathtaking,  but decor ranges from original and creative to busy and tacky. Great service. Overall great intimate space.", 'time': 1579342390}]

column15: [{'author_name': 'Alberto Sassi', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/109238366667309320140/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Gg1B61nHvz51AjSIabEyyyNxpI8ILJzQesJtvYLkQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': 'Wonderful museum in San Angel. The museum is huge and really cheap. There is a wide collection of religious art by mexican artists of colonial times. The crypt is a jewel with amazing frescoes and also well preserved mummies. Attach to the museum is a beautiful church with some astonishing domes.', 'time': 1562561132}, {'author_name': 'Pat Rodriguez', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/105478498959737058148/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-uyf6fD8UCDM/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/AMZuuclm8p_I5KXAfO9K0AAw4A6l8h0Hng/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo/photo.jpg', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '6 months ago', 'text': 'Visited the Mummys way back in 1970. Very interesting. I visit el DF quite often and hope to go back to museum on my next visit.', 'time': 1586311142}, {'author_name': 'Andy Martinez', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/102430384834165605115/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GiPqxj3pHAxQNCL7Z306_vN4Um7FbesTwxLju3EbQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '3 years ago', 'text': "I was very surprised to see that this convent has mummies that are very well preserved despite not going through a curing process, although there isn't alot of information about them other than being burried at the church and then dug up by soldiers looking for treasures but finding only bodies. The rest of the museum is equally impressive. Beautiful paintings and rooms where servant lived have now been converted to display areas. The garden although not fancy by any means is very well kept.", 'time': 1499741329}, {'author_name': 'Giovanna Chavez', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/111403691329848665976/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Giiwsy9ZigaqcxncOgsiSJ5XRM7uP6dRpQMRs5AHw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': 'Beautiful colonial masterpiece. Make sure you take the guided tour. Such an interesting part of the History of México!\nIs a very large museum, many chambers and even a crypt with mummified corpses.', 'time': 1564696457}, {'author_name': 'Anabel Ramirez', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/114929686688065194211/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/-YXtzdnf0b_g/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/AMZuucmp2FVuOTucW_AcTLejYXFgPw6N7g/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4/photo.jpg', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': "Beautiful former monastery. Very clean and well preserved. Lots of art pieces like wood sculptures and paintings. Mummified nuns' corpses  in the basement. Highly recommendable.", 'time': 1549750718}]

column15: [{'author_name': 'Sam Law', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/111701691347468606703/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Gi1dVlsDvbAlonr00xj9MEspZLiNDp9Ux4ZLyvqeA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '8 months ago', 'text': 'The Museum is one of Mexico City’s hidden gems — telling the story of the dirty wars and the relentless struggle by family members to find their loved ones who had been disappeared. If you are interested in Mexico’s long history of resistance and left struggle, you should definitely go. The cafe downstairs is also a great place to grab a bite to eat or meet up with friends', 'time': 1578770962}, {'author_name': 'Andy Martinez', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/102430384834165605115/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GiPqxj3pHAxQNCL7Z306_vN4Um7FbesTwxLju3EbQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '3 years ago', 'text': 'This museum takes a stance on the corrupción the Mexican government is capable of, but documenting important events but also some that are almost completely unknown you can really appreciate what this family has tried to accomplish by documenting and sharing what they have been through. A very friendly tour guide greets every single person who walks in to tell them about some of the events that have taken place, sharing how they hurt his family directly.', 'time': 1495429023}, {'author_name': 'Fernanda Villarreal', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/101720219243812966097/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-chNeVV3aQ2A/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/AMZuucm8r4kcVqwCxxPBGUlgavy8G3Dc-g/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3/photo.jpg', 'rating': 4, 'relative_time_description': '7 months ago', 'text': 'Great place to know about the "other" histories.', 'time': 1582348681}, {'author_name': 'Assael Ortiz Corona', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/110661834860994318541/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Giim6XBL7K4U2SHHoZR24lrZ7tqtGRAx7eNyPEBIA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': "It's a beautiful place.", 'time': 1567133908}, {'author_name': 'David Bellin', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/103165021204980812497/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GjirA-G1RoJ9kK-myEKc45_nS7vDMw1uE3ZGGGyRuA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '3 years ago', 'text': 'Amazing true and heartfelt histories of the sixties movements and after, in an intimate setting overlooked by many visitors, do not miss it', 'time': 1489539827}]

[{'author_name': 'Lorena Chaho', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/109249192942079248657/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GgHMn8Zoc_GF_8xcrJjv0dGeHNTpazGk4ANZLcaSg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '7 months ago', 'text': 'Facilities are beautiful. The entry cost $70 Mxn. The history about the mexican muralist Tamayo is really interesting and beautiful. The people working there is kind and welcoming', 'time': 1582951526}, {'author_name': 'Alexandre Bersia', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/104219876533216690901/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GioKhxSCLgdmRBZ-byTYmEo0SFTO5XU4okWDBjlsQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3', 'rating': 3, 'relative_time_description': '9 months ago', 'text': 'Great Architecture and awesome place if you want to take pictures of the building itself, but the content of the galleries was not so great unfortunately.', 'time': 1578452600}, {'author_name': 'James Concepcion', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/113825246372579967814/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-MvfFM1ehB0U/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/AMZuucnPCuLW5Xkmrf4heRRmKwVqLD5Lcw/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6/photo.jpg', 'rating': 4, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': 'Amazing museum. The works of Tamayo unfortunately are only a portion of the museum pieces. I had expected it to be mostly Tamayo works but it was a combination of several Mexican painters of the same era.

There was also a section on Oriental art that I tried to find out the connection to Tamayo. They also had studies of a particular subject in about 30 panels.', 'time': 1568018234}, {'author_name': 'Alexandra Woolsey-Puffer', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/113184292365006318561/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GgaFmp73eQwsSgWg2HmAoizOscGpd9ALdXemDemAw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 4, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': 'Free admission on Sunday. Beautiful space, great location, don’t miss the shop for unique gifts and the cafe for a snack.

The special exhibitions are quite good, showcasing international, high caliber artists; the permanent collection is not quite as first rate.

Worth a visit if you are in the area', 'time': 1565449024}, {'author_name': 'Santiago Pazos', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/112599820219898244230/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GgA7NkrvNTmy-EOjHsXsQiSqrwyfEtBoewe5fw7jA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': "First time here and what a delightful experience. Architecturally talking the building is excellent. Clean lines with tons of different textures. On the other hand the work in there is quite appealing and relevant. Modern and contemporary art. One day of the week entry is free. Don't forget to check the restaurant upstairs because it is delicious!", 'time': 1541906079}]

column15:
[{'author_name': 'Carlos S', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/117534207502573550168/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Gg-8QJlfd0XEu3Mnm0KyEfwMqY0qua-1yXVkcKRAw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '3 months ago', 'text': 'A incredible museum, which give the history of the original Mexican people and their journey to the land, which is now Mexico. Incredible display and archaeological artifacts. You will be memorized from the moment you get there.', 'time': 1593011798}, {'author_name': 'Francisco Martinez', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/116244492123148542606/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GjF6oVJrLR9hlPqHV7hmklQEPXa_efFDU5bmZt3=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a month ago', 'text': 'World Class Museum!  Staff is uniformed, helpful and easy to identify in a large crowd.  The entire museum is very large so prepare to spend half a day here at least. The whole day if your going to take your time and read about each exhibit.  I had to cram 3 hours and could not see it all.  I would love to go back and I intend to.  I like how it starts with human and ancestor evolution exhibits.   I later saw a model of ancient humans risking their lives to kill a mastodon. In the background was very large painting illustrating the megafauna that once roamed the earth and is now extinct.

There was super sized bison at one time! Imagine that.  Extinct due to humans.  We do like the hunt the big ones dont we? I relate this to the fact that the days of capturing super sized tuna just to beat records are gone as well.  I personaly discourage hunting purely for the best trophy animals. I imagine your taking the best out of the gene pool like that.

The mesoamerican pieces are further in.  Its like going into a time machine and getting a glimpse of mesoamerican life.  Facinating! Many pieces here are large and highly detailed works of art.  Im an artist myself and i can tell master artists created these pieces.   Many took serious skill, time and effort to create.  Sadly not many big wood pieces survived the conquest but this museum has some extremely rare ones.  The place is full of art and treasure.  Its free for Mexican nationals if i remember correctly.  Either that or nicely discounted with ID proof. Yes lots of tourists here from all over the world.

You can take the subway to the museum (if your not a complete sissy) to avoid traffic and save valuable time, if your willing to walk a little or you can take a taxi the rest of the way or the whole way.  Uber is available too.  Its located in a large park in a safer and beautiful part of the city.  Like anywhere of course theres good parts and bad parts of this mega city. If your not familiar with the city dont show off or wear jewelry on the subway and go bashing the place in reviews.  Common sense.

The gift shop has some nice replicas and souvenirs of course so be prepared to take home something nice if you really like mesoamerican art or you will wish you prepared.  Taxis are right outside of the museum and can take you to where you need to go. I will plan to bring back larger replicas with me next time.', 'time': 1599442970}, {'author_name': 'Isabella Parks', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/104296010325573631542/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GgA5Z-KHt6u14qscOYkVg5GXMadgPCg2r95Lw5K0Q=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '7 months ago', 'text': "Such a beautiful museum! We spent two hours here, and only got through maybe 1/4 of the exhibits. Definitely a half-day activity if you want to get through it all. A wide variety of artifacts, from bones, to pottery, to photographs, to building materials. I didn't think I'd be so interested in anthropology! BONUS: the restaurant & cafe here are amazing and very reasonably priced, given the quality of food. I", 'time': 1582645261}, {'author_name': 'Kyuwon Lee', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/110778779454043925617/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Gg43cgZtPRd0RkzgJYQQxGGC0Lw1AMqGEWoW_ezfg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '4 months ago', 'text': "A massive place with an world-class collection and presentation. I'd say it's a heavenly place for anyone who has any level of interest in anthropology, archeology, or human society and culture in general.", 'time': 1590531586}, {'author_name': 'Emily Anderson', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/117613627475394346752/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GiJ4dOaq19WxOSjFXCUBm5Dx0hG9hs-od6JLl-GC-s=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '7 months ago', 'text': "This is worth the visit... We did 3 museums this data and this was the last stop... We surprisingly got through it all in 3 hours...probably need more... It's definitely a half day experience. It. Is. Massive. And awesome.  Everyone told us to make sure we go here and I am glad we did!", 'time': 1581796551}]

column15: [{'author_name': 'Hamidreza Rafatnejad', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/110130141652262402975/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GhzBREXexNkxweOgOLLQPEEqPJjLoP2-9jwjtb5kA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3', 'rating': 4, 'relative_time_description': '10 months ago', 'text': 'It is a great place to see, but the only problem I had was that there are duplicates and if you are looking for original artifacts you cannot find any special thing in here. But still a great place if somebody wants to have a “general” knowledge of history and human civilization.', 'time': 1575351294}, {'author_name': 'A Y', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/105648742746002608462/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Gj0yt9efYNNmVLAt7A092RhqVBP--tifwgihzekKVY=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '8 months ago', 'text': "A hidden gem in the middle of Moneda street, an old building converted into a museum. A wide range of exhibitions of all the different cultures around the world. It's free on Sunday, but also means it's crowded as well.", 'time': 1580145950}, {'author_name': 'Rob Hdez', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/116504905415673992480/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/-aHfGFYNo1OY/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/AMZuucm_VlycnPoPNWZ7A26WqIUXPTg4qQ/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4/photo.jpg', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '8 months ago', 'text': 'Beautiful place to go...love it :)', 'time': 1581141994}, {'author_name': 'Viktor Ruppert', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/108212303123869341713/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GiztVEgjUBBYh2AQ56atRxfrkNA5Yc9nxSAvH8TxAM=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3', 'rating': 3, 'relative_time_description': '7 months ago', 'text': "Housed in a building that's architecturally quite interesting, and the collection itself is a good way to get a general overview of cultures around the world. My main beef with the place is that it's hard to tell which pieces are genuine and which are replicas, and all signs and explanations were in Spanish (fair enough, maybe I should learn).\nEntry is free on Sundays (otherwise Mx$14), so you can use the facilities if nothing else. Worth a walk around though, you'll definitely see something interesting, but don't expect Templo Mayor standards. NOT wheelchair or old-folk friendly though, there are a lot of stairs.", 'time': 1582234582}, {'author_name': 'Jose Huerta', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/106645800119460268962/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Ggop7LtN2XND1SoPRJCS0PhYN1LrrwJk2k9ny3WBs8=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '10 months ago', 'text': 'Great museum to visit, very well kept with wonderful people helping.', 'time': 1576113643}]

column15:
[{'author_name': 'Kevin Chan', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/104673164606260610793/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GhnZm8FlppvjunPuY1eRiXtJb3Erczx7ku8mjMDXgc=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '9 months ago', 'text': 'Wonderful restaurant with beautiful and delicious food. Wait staff is very nice and accommodating. Had the guacamole and chips, the Sopa Lima, and the Chicken entree all were spectacular and very tasty. The interior is open, airy, and modern with a view into the kitchen. Highly recommend.', 'time': 1577756357}, {'author_name': 'Ron Wong', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/109995492420355032061/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GhZl7O-BMbewUqImWfuKURKhH59VG9y5bbONmR8BQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 4, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': 'Wonderful ambience, well trained wait staff, creative drink list, tasty entrees. The only disappointment was the guacamole starter. Looks wonderful, like a pond in a forest. The center is runny and makes the guacamole wetter than most. To me it also diluted the flavor. Four of us struggled to finish it. The ceviche was fine, not as creative with flavors as others we had elsewhere. Entrees of grilled fish were wonderful as were the sides. We skipped dessert. The rest rooms are a row of stalls upstairs, very egalitarian. There’s an outdoor back patio that’s airy and lovely when it’s nice out.', 'time': 1563062390}, {'author_name': 'Jose Antonio Barreto', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/102273497377342126579/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Gjev76bukuUBngLpqrWLhAL_KN9k59d-iq3oPoy6g=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6', 'rating': 4, 'relative_time_description': '10 months ago', 'text': 'Without a doubt La Capital I s an excellent Mexican Gourmet Restaurant. One of the bests. You have to try the Tacos La Capital. Tasty and real feast to the eyes thanks to its great plate decoration. Service is good too. Try seating at the mezzanine tables for a better view of what is going on while you enjoy your meal.', 'time': 1574484614}, {'author_name': 'Anna Lisa Gentile', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/117392150429848852116/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GjGLveCRn2cf4dnvsTgg9pd3BU453DnvjM4dPE6TbE=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5', 'rating': 4, 'relative_time_description': '7 months ago', 'text': 'The place is nice but it can be really loud.
Food is good, my favorite was the pulpo asado and the chevice de camarones.
Drinks: we ordered a mezcal cocktail (Oaxaca 86) and it was very watery, not much taste.', 'time': 1582179998}, {'author_name': 'Thomas CASTERAN', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/110679349231255091156/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GhLyUVY8FpqytKXuI95phYnQb4RjKxZz1odGY_Zag=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5', 'rating': 4, 'relative_time_description': '11 months ago', 'text': 'Very nice place in the Condensa area to eat typical Mexican food.

The restaurant has a very nice atmosphere, and also an outside area. I removed one star because it is also really loud.

Food wise, it was very good!', 'time': 1571374263}]

column15: [{'author_name': 'Eileen Gao', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/107783253069897793323/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Gjqzz2woWqH9LFi3OzLjrXISBezxAmLvVS-Tref=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6', 'rating': 4, 'relative_time_description': 'a month ago', 'text': 'The only decent park in the center of Mexico City', 'time': 1599127542}, {'author_name': 'Miguel Soto', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/110557106081126566693/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-KQP7tB8Uwdc/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/AMZuuckubWrNTcyCM-uwSvxusBsxro1bNw/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo/photo.jpg', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '8 months ago', 'text': "If you're visiting Mexico City, this is a must!   Pastries and hot chocolate for breakfast are a wonderfully delicious Mexican experience.  Every time I have friends visiting from abroad, I take them here for breakfast.  Everything on the menu is very authentic and its very cheap for what it is.  Its in downtown so after enjoying a delicious breakfast, you can go explore nearby sites.", 'time': 1579754162}, {'author_name': 'Alice K', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/112481131850564576049/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GgU2Pkq1K7lU6r3A56yzwlsfH0cC0nx935mtxJMVKY=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': 'Hard to find - it’s located in the Hilton hotel. This place came highly recommended by a friend who knew CDMX very well so I was excited to try it. We arrived around 11:30am on a Saturday morning and there was a huge lineup. Good sign. We were told the wait would be 35 minutes but we only waited 25! We waited in Hilton lobby and used the outlets to charge our phones. The famous hot chocolate was a little overrated because I found it more milky than chocolate-y (I think that’s because the chocolate is bittersweet). They brought fresh bread for us while we waited for our food. We ordered the omelette with zucchini flowers and mushrooms. Incredible dish! Unique, flavorful and the corn cake with cream was the perfect starch to end this fish on. The lamb marinated with hot sauce maguey leaves was outstanding. It had incredible flavor and the additions of cactus leaves and guacamole was perfect to roll into little tortillas. When we ran out, they asked if we wanted more tortillas. The service was absolutely outstanding. I cannot wait to come back. Fantastic value and great place to try unique Mexican dishes.', 'time': 1554059221}, {'author_name': 'Juan Blancas', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/100715436607434276227/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GhN9JPWKnMbQ-RCSlzFZ4ZTjR0k17gwCriekQ_r7Q=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': "It's a really nice Mexican restaurant.  The food is delicious and the service is excellent.  On weekends is usually busy, some times you have to wait around an hour to be seated.", 'time': 1560374344}, {'author_name': 'yesenia haro', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/116761389916202996486/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GhbStQsm8j8gSGikFblk8_0kgp-r4ubuk5QRNuz=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '9 months ago', 'text': "The food here was amazing and you hav e to try the pina colada it's the best pina colada I have ever had.", 'time': 1576768158}]

column15: [{'author_name': 'Mirad Closa', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/100015050290650811008/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-fjm7wc4AuB0/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/AMZuuclBKZ6qLD_5nt_1Zyen2iwCd9J-Ag/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4/photo.jpg', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a month ago', 'text': 'Palacio De Bella Artes is one of the most well-known museum in Mexico. In addition to visiting the museum, check out the scene outside. Locals hang out here and it’s an extraordinary spot to people watch!', 'time': 1597911071}, {'author_name': 'Jay Wu', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/106752713490667721256/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GiUJtSIfHms4NWOD18eP3rmWypAgoD3Vr2ItDhleQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 4, 'relative_time_description': '7 months ago', 'text': 'The Palacio de Bellas Artes is beautiful, from the the garden hall to the architecture. There are massive art pieces in the gallery. Although the time I went did not have a big exhibit going on. But seeing the revolution pictures of Diego Rivera was an amazing experience. Pro tip, the ice cream sold outside are delicious. After spending time climbing the stairs, buy some cold sweets and relax in the garden.', 'time': 1582575837}, {'author_name': 'Shakey Official', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/100798151555056620374/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GgVf3i9PlyxC_MjKyal1QqzMygLfJeCsH0wNhsIG_Q=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a month ago', 'text': 'An extraordinary museum right in Mexico City, massive and beautiful architecture. Great place to explore art exhibits and spot interactive local people.', 'time': 1599305228}, {'author_name': 'Emily Anderson', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/117613627475394346752/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GiJ4dOaq19WxOSjFXCUBm5Dx0hG9hs-od6JLl-GC-s=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '7 months ago', 'text': "Really enjoyed these exhibits band the place in general. It's a beautiful building. If you're just looking for the art exhibits... When you enter go to the left and turn around to buy your tickets... Proceed forward if you are looking to catch one of the performances.", 'time': 1581796911}, {'author_name': 'Edel Ramirez', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/103362882179870596827/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Gj5_JetJtKG2goLGmO0zRHwOgO0HycVq2xDq25XRDo=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '7 months ago', 'text': 'Mexico City has a great way to please the art lovers and this place is just magnificent, also you can eat gourmet food just across the street, if you happen to lay off some time at the International Airport this is a place to visit just minutes from there, hope you find interesting the pictures', 'time': 1583437609}]

column15:
[{'author_name': 'Ela Opinska', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/114361943805303085738/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Gj6-rb39i0uStCn4Wl21nHgaB3kX89f-YzzFzjH6sU=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': "This a place every Mexican should visit. For foreigners it's a great knowledge of Mexico, its history, culture, evolution and development. The museum is free of charge. If you want to lime the top of the Revolution Monument, there is a small fee. Great views from the top! Expect to climb over 160 stairs of the last part to the 360 grade deck. Highly recommended!", 'time': 1567716031}, {'author_name': 'Gloria Ifems', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/103275143076921936564/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GjHqgvGMB32yCKFrd27S1Ej_ifDxSuVDElvv91nHA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba2', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '2 months ago', 'text': 'Beautiful but not much to do there', 'time': 1595376835}, {'author_name': 'Erin T.', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/114100924396912336863/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GhX6oNmCJa8_G39wR82ZbUeqCFobXoDhuplblZDs5w=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '2 years ago', 'text': "It's a great must-see place if your visiting Mexico or live there.  They offer tours inside the place the cover how the building was made, what it represents, who helped construct it, and how long out took to build. There's a level in the building in which they do serve food such as crepes and coffee which can be enjoyed with a great view of the building's surroundings.", 'time': 1534686832}, {'author_name': 'Kyle Morrison', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/111978793272601992672/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GhENChq1jTSdtkmqkAAMQkJBHPe7Z6HTYH4uvSS4bY=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 4, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': 'This is my first museum sharing history not in my native language or country.

For an experience, this was great an eye opening to see our history from a new perspective. The challenge related to much of the museum was Spanish only and caused a challenge for me with Spanish still being very new for me. I did enjoy some areas in both languages.

Overall, if you like history, this has many nice exhibits all in a beautiful area of the city.', 'time': 1560555259}, {'author_name': 'Martín Morales Rodríguez', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/100018611233465625321/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Gjsr7C3KrIHIurOsAWAGFB6mIdhs9P0Y-i9h9TIxw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a month ago', 'text': 'Great place to visit.', 'time': 1599341247}]

column15:
[{'author_name': 'Paul Carpenter', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/102403463315060937043/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GhR-_rQt4ACwgvYsSpeZvjuN3ii5BMI6qGR7cBapg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '3 weeks ago', 'text': 'COVID POSTING

I love this location and I love all the Artisans and the amount of beautiful artwork you can buy please note that if you are going during the covid-19 demek you will not be able to enter onto the site and you will only be able to drive around. If you are looking to learn about teotihuacan and the Beautiful land and location around it you will have many people willing to give you tours for a small fee but once again you will not be able to climb or go onto the location', 'time': 1600269585}, {'author_name': 'Jose Maqueda', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/101370216072139805503/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GhrebK1IPAF1zk38Laclz0nKC_XiEV2KGENObxewQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '2 weeks ago', 'text': "Teotihuacán is a relic of the time before Europeans colonized the land now known as America. The Spanish destroyed most of the native architecture during the conquest of Mexico. It's amazing Teotihuacán somehow survived the destruction by the Spanish. The pyramids are a bit of a drive from the center of Mexico City. It's totally worth the trip. When I went people could still climb to the very top of the pyramids. Im not sure if that is still the case. I've you ever find yourself in Mexico City with time to spare, do yourself a favor and go check out Teotihuacán.", 'time': 1600674480}, {'author_name': 'Vinicius Sartini', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/110277233752818856466/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Gh01kYEK9tpChDN6lFPseuNMvT_oT-WUQt0kuRwFyE=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a month ago', 'text': 'Wonderful views. Helpful hint: Do a little historic research before going.

Help the local community using their services/buying their goods (restaurants, salespeople)', 'time': 1597323079}, {'author_name': 'Ran Bar-shalom', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/109087339624474157377/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Gh4Lc_tG6g3xl2LGnBT0oOFCeEeUpzL33BMyrOJtw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '7 months ago', 'text': "3rd largest pyramid in world, and a must see if you're in the area of Mexico City - only an hour and half away. There are two main Pyramid of the Sun and the Moon. You can climb to the top of the Sun Pyramid, its about 77 meters high, and you might feel short breath in the way up. The Moon pyramid as a few minutes walk from the the Sun one, and can only be climbed to the first half of it, so might be more convenient for those who want an easier climb. Near the pyramid of the moon, there are also wall paintings dating 2000 years ago and is still in colour! If you'd like to eat there as well there are many many restaurants, I would recommend the furthest one (approx 5min drive) the Gruta restaurant, which is situated in a cave and is a really unique experience, and food is very good as well.", 'time': 1583232994}, {'author_name': 'Una Le Roux', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/104761942310306972837/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GhPqwHX-LlZ-4bxN8cEZ_6zYtyNSxkwbvOEiVGc=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '7 months ago', 'text': "It's absolutely possible to do this by public transport and not a tour. Recommend going early though, certainly filling up as we were ready to leave. So glad we didn't go on a weekend, heard that there were 3hr long queues to climb the pyramids. Can't believe we made it to the top!!", 'time': 1583880408}]

I was fascinated by the installations throughout.', 'time': 1582038021}, {'author_name': 'jean paul', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/113067929189145271811/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GiwsTottdq4D0wNon7k7gmEqrcIuZqJjgdJX6pi=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': "Beautiful place and quite well organized. Besides that? One of the best galleries I have seen!", 'time': 1562864838}, {'author_name': 'Lorena Chaho', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/109249192942079248657/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GgHMn8Zoc_GF_8xcrJjv0dGeHNTpazGk4ANZLcaSg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 4, 'relative_time_description': '7 months ago', 'text': "The exhibition i saw was really average and the price little high for what was. column15: [{'author_name': 'Sagar Shah', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/115579995074608517246/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Gh8We936gbuJsXmAQuLb12n0rCcslD-gGGcyf3ejRw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5', 'rating': 3, 'relative_time_description': '8 months ago', 'text': "The restaurant has a very friendly staff but the food was decent. We had me as the vegan in the group which they did a great job accommodating but I had a lot of help from my coworker who explained it in Spanish. But even the folks who are not vegan thought the food was good not great. The presentation of the food was very nice. The cocktails were better than the food.  We had a couple of nice bottles of wine but not sure if me or the folks I was with would go back.  I'd give it a 3.5 star if I could because it was slightly better than okay.", 'time': 1579374372}, {'author_name': 'Joshua Barsch', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/116029741988503232377/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Gjj91yDYMmVp6_HQWCzcPoisECwxOJdP4RxVm_r2w=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '2 months ago', 'text': 'Incredible food that would cost you four times as much in the US', 'time': 1594579806}, {'author_name': 'Luis Enrique Martinez', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/101354791356058168867/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GieyvILYOJE1c6hqSwk8603_DXdbSNtkeqQEzirBg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 3, 'relative_time_description': '8 months ago', 'text': 'Fancy and expensive Oaxaca cuisine. Not as good in my opinion for the prices. Mezcal Cocktails are great. Service very good.', 'time': 1579283617}, {'author_name': 'Luis Cabrera', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/115458850750524104549/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GhhFNZ6REvxguII2hMGASp2Rw2d4T1YMZBoF4YPyL8=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '10 months ago', 'text': "It has been a long time since I've eaten this delicious. If you are looking for real dishes from Oaxaca, this is the place to be. The pan of elote is amazing, the barbacoa is also really tasty. Their supplies are brought from Oaxaca two times per week", 'time': 1574146793}, {'author_name': 'Grace Yu', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/109930974081118164336/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GjP_KSKHAZkeRpob4nNe5NAYcClrtRy6PmwWCjPkg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': 'This was a memorable meal. Went here for an early dinner. The staff was so nice and accommodating to our broken Spanish. They gave great recommendations on food and drinks. Everything we tried was amazing! I would make a trip back to Mexico City just so I could come back here.\n\nHint: get the duck tacos mole and a couple of those gasolinazo cocktails! It’s a good time!', 'time': 1551021829}]

It took me one hour and a half to get there from metro Villa de Cortés area. Great play "Quién mató a Shakespeare?", I recommend it a lot! You laugh all the time! Hahaha!', 'time': 1531241854}, {'author_name': 'william chaves', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/100428415522271343349/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GjuneogNmQF3jYZl7eNEpJUIobhvoWEubkTMscCw6U=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '3 years ago', 'text': 'Wonderful place', 'time': 1477251160}, {'author_name': 'Jesse Hayashi', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/103822695714656486299/reviews', 'language': 'es', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-rewJkuakVp0/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/AMZuucn624D2mZ2WeW2Cf5yHaP0kWxMPJQ/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4/photo.jpg', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '8 months ago', 'text': 'El lugar, a pesar de ser pequeño, tiene lo necesario para disfrutar de excelentes obras de teatro con actores (a veces) no tan conocidos pero con calidad histriónica. La gente es amable y cálida. Lo único negativo es el estacionamiento, ya que hay que dejar el vehiculo en la calle con el riego de que ratas asquerosos te roben algún accesorio.  Se puede estacionar en el centro comercial de enfrente.', 'time': 1579740458}, {'author_name': 'miguel esquivel martinez', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/101226785813533469313/reviews', 'language': 'es', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Gi4HUmFym2UW06JIsRw13jKP25-1ics0SJj_gcD0Sc=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6', 'rating': 3, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': 'Un espacio para el desarrollo de las artes escénicas. Se puede acudir como espectador de las diferentes obras que se montan y presentan, así como iniciarse en la práctica en los talleres que se imparten. Lugar adecuado para quien desea algo sencillo, pero de calidad para divertirse un rato', 'time': 1566399623}, {'author_name': 'Sandra Guevara', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/106667480093732033722/reviews', 'language': 'es', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GiOYhN5hPaz2TmIKs6Wf4PQwaH-_w67t0O1jbBGxw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '8 months ago', 'text': 'Son foros pequeñitos pero eso permite a los actores interactuar con el público. column15: [{'author_name': 'León Loredo Aarón', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/117784489792594980923/reviews', 'language': 'es', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GjEm8gpnocVgzRYW8lIXCyP-lEbULoyTtXwi1EoHAo=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3', 'rating': 4, 'relative_time_description': '5 months ago', 'text': 'Me parece un gran lugar para comer a cualquier hora. Desayunos bien servidos y comidas completas muy buenas. Me gusta mucho la hamburguesa principal, gran tamaño, excelente sabor y buen precio.\nEl único “problema” seria la música ambiental, están a gusto de las señoritas que atienden todo el tiempo, pero entiendo que eso es subjetivo.', 'time': 1587508598}, {'author_name': 'guadalupe benavides', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/114283178934255002614/reviews', 'language': 'es', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GhykAQg5DZea0HTaT0KSZpjAAJ8EZBSU1lAfsFWIw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba2', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': 'Los precios muuuuy accesibles, el ambiente muy agradable (la música es tranquila y su volumen jamás impide la plática), el servicio muy atento y la comida súper rica; su preparación es completamente artesanal (nada de productos industrializados). Me enamoré del lugar!', 'time': 1546103243}, {'author_name': 'Diana Irais Diaz', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/111530098050626182844/reviews', 'language': 'es', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GjKSN2uE63CxpOdbLh7WxwEoKIaN7k0dbMWEl2i=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 4, 'relative_time_description': '4 weeks ago', 'text': 'Muy rico y muy bien servido. column15:
[{'author_name': 'Grzegorz', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/111127105551247076353/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GguepF0ovdy9BiRyDE0LfCYG9No-j_z2AH80IPSxA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '8 months ago', 'text': 'The third volcano in Mexico and North America. It has a very interesting peak ridge. Over 5000m, numerous peaks, two melting glaciers, an interesting path line, beautiful views of the active Popocatepetl volcano. Interesting mountain next to the huge  of Mexico City.', 'time': 1578859559}, {'author_name': 'LUIS FERNANDO GARRIDO', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/112463655730542520701/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GgQi5Cnm1SqiFEvCT4w9VtWF0hJl6wSD7JWEIO9rV8=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '8 months ago', 'text': "It's too late for me to climb this beautiful volcano. I used to climb volcanos from my country when I was adolescent,  I should delight this one.", 'time': 1580312019}, {'author_name': 'wnegrao', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/110515578175468581183/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-hCUkfr_Dl-I/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/AMZuuckeiEZK-TUvjbVIaFalKHmdNsd_DQ/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4/photo.jpg', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '2 years ago', 'text': 'outstanding landscape and hiking site', 'time': 1526169029}, {'author_name': 'The_Louis_Mx', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/115967870606088856925/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GgKfhCqAlicHiw5tGzzz8yFSnU8NAkA9xcgh8wfgQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '2 years ago', 'text': 'Epic place to visit if you like outdoors/into the wild, well as you may know this is a non active volcano called locally "Sleeped woman".
The most dangerous season to climb this volcano is on apr-may because the precipitations, it rains, snows and if you haven't any experience you could die, in fact the highest number of accidents is in this dates, well if you have the right equipment and experience you can sign your name on a list reviewed by the army and estimate time you'll spend in the mountain, after this lapse of time if they notice you haven't come back they start a search of the people.
On winter there exists a race called "The mad race"  'cause many people start very early in the morning a race from the base of Popocatepetl to the summit of the sleeped woman and back to the goal, it is awesome.', 'time': 1525322339}, {'author_name': 'Elias D S Caballero', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/116038723589245290290/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GgBgMD_mQZX_CmPBCjjibkHblTnK-rJNe4aIPegAQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '2 years ago', 'text': 'The remains of the stone "tetzacualco" or shrine were found in the middle of a natural pond, some 3,870 metres or 12,700 feet above sea level, in the shadow of the dormant Iztaccihuatl volcano. Archaeologists from INAH have been working on the site since 2016.
It takes the geometric shape of a quincunx, with stones forming a rectangle around the area as well as a central point depicting where Cipactli would have lurked.', 'time': 1532918415}]

column15:
[{'author_name': 'Ryan Howard', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/110104749630306395880/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-GMoGS7lRGSU/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAqDY/AMZuuckWnksNInhqfALDckdvdZE8SHJpRA/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4/photo.jpg', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '7 months ago', 'text': 'Beautiful Church, built under mandate by Cortes himself shortly after the conquest of the city. The apse is very impressive, and be sure to look for the ghost of Brother Lego, whose ghost it is said places roses at the altar of Mary.', 'time': 1583361711}, {'author_name': 'JI', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/114219700683636272172/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Gjjs-6OUMuk7md4kmF0kkcmzy2LBYHktymXVMXWCw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '10 months ago', 'text': 'Its a Catholic Church with great interiors. Location is perfect for walking around with the family and it is a very safe area. Parking could be extremely difficult at peak hours. Surroundings offer great food variety and handcrafted products stores.', 'time': 1575523264}, {'author_name': 'Ess See', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/116037709942562108012/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GgglWuSgNwtPtLZtFwNc9HCtPR6zZGsIuKpdnONxf4=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 3, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': 'The architecture was built for Catholic architecture and figures. And that is art for me.

Though, for a place of worship and "godliness", not much is being offered to the less fortunate, who all seem to surround outside the church and not a single seat was offered.', 'time': 1563942759}, {'author_name': 'CJ Gold', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/112155669730391478744/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-Uwmo0Bno3wo/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/AMZuucn7nXgfWt8VcolPQ18WhkJQnCLpEQ/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo/photo.jpg', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': 'In our trip to Mexico last week, we visited Coyoacán.
As we were getting out of the car, we were welcomed by the rich sound of church bells calling for the one o’clock mass.
After the celebration ended we stayed to appreciate the impressive beauty of San Juan’s Bautista architecture and murals.
As in all colonial cities, the church is located across the town’s main plaza and there was a lot of activities going on around the plaza.', 'time': 1565471221}, {'author_name': 'Ivan Toscano', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/102372096259899394905/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Gi3jlkE5oaNT0hwqgzjGMQM9elvpwC_FR_kcHWYZnM=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '9 months ago', 'text': 'One or the most beautiful church in Mexico. Don’t forget to look to the sealing to see the marvelous paintings', 'time': 1578501226}]

column15:
[{'author_name': 'Syd R', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/114151270608292510397/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Gj8ORLnPyayuCnvHXDonLGTY03QQS-ozoEZPczM=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5', 'rating': 2, 'relative_time_description': '3 years ago', 'text': 'A tiny museum of the pyramid.', 'time': 1502805056}, {'author_name': 'Araceli Garcia', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/105148518855931475948/reviews', 'language': 'es', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Gjn_zfAhif8z1vrV-8-6Ft0Qc5QWEfNjHR6WBA00w=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': 'Un lugar muy tranquilo, se pueden subir a la pirámide y no tiene costo, me parece que si cuenta con estacionamiento, o lo pueden dejar en el estacionamiento de la plaza Inbursa que se encuentra en Cuicuilco, es muy bonito para ir a pasear', 'time': 1554249881}, {'author_name': 'Tonantzin Creaciones', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/104135491939315916711/reviews', 'language': 'es', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GhQme-xh3HsCbHGU2uU3GrnUngilf__yeCAcgYXQA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '2 years ago', 'text': 'Este museo es muy pequeño pero con suficiente información, cuenta sólo con dos salas: exposición temporal y exposición permanente. Suficientes si te aburre leer.
Está a un costado del centro ceremonial por lo que hay que caminar bastante desde la entrada para llegar a él.
La entrada tampoco tiene costo.
Sí hay sanitarios gratuitos también.', 'time': 1522678914}, {'author_name': 'Hane Karlstein', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/113216152912738852070/reviews', 'language': 'es', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Gj5SU0leF8KJ1MpfYfmoILO734peSCEtsKJB41XXLk=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3', 'rating': 3, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': 'El museo posee suficientes elementos que permiten conocer sobre la cultura cuicuilaca, tiene información de cada aspecto y al final cierra con un mural que representa la erupción del Xitle que desencadenó el abandono del basamento. Lamentablemente la información está desactualizada por falta de presupuesto pero no está de más que pidan información a la responsable o encargada del lugar. Tristemente se las construcciones cercanas han sido edificadas sobre parte del territorio cuicuilca y mucha información se perdió en ello además de descontectualizar el sitio. Vale la pena conocer lo poco que ha quedado de esta civilización antecesora de Teotihuacán.
Algunas de las piezas no fueron encontradas en el sitio sino que fueron prestadas para ejemplificar.', 'time': 1552718085}, {'author_name': 'Cristy Lòpez Liceaga', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/110621520881906875954/reviews', 'language': 'es', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GjAwGKEfk6LuMFpwg34KdMWU9HRAAlpzXfzeeHH=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 4, 'relative_time_description': '11 months ago', 'text': 'Muy grato él lugar. Acceso gratuito', 'time': 1571516601}]

column15:
[{'author_name': 'David Galpin', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/105909378769398369901/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/--VbEhPvnsW0/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/AMZuucmdX1jrLDa7ZzF1C2Ed2BmTnty2ww/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5/photo.jpg', 'rating': 3, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': 'Some interesting pictures but lacking any real blockbusters. I liked the portraits of Phillip II and Frederick of Saxony. There was a nice Ribero of San Sebastian. The building itself is probably as interesting as the pictures, and probably worth the entry fee. It costs 50 pesos to get in and 5 pesos to take photos.', 'time': 1552054301}, {'author_name': 'Carlos Cli', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/113942887617515417473/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Gg4l-Urj1xthoiJzyO8VWPcIPKVtJ97eWpfKvhCJ-0=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': "A jewel hidden in the city.
This extraordinary Museum is one of the best in the country. It hosts a  excellent collection of Colonial art. This magnificent building was designed by Manuel Tolsá, the famous and multitalented architect.
It's one of the most extraordinary buildings in an area trapped by time & chaos. Fortunately the building remains safe thanks to it's grandeur.

For anyone seeking for Mexican art from 1500 to 1900 this wonderful museum will surprise & fulfill your search. Take your kids to learn about the splendor of colonial and the independent Mexico of the 19th century.

Last but not least, this extraordinary mansion from the colonial times has one of the most impressive circular patios ever built during the neoclassic period.
San Carlos is a wonderful experience to discover and a Unique Masterpiece of architecture, painting and the utterly Exquisite Mexican art.
Carlos Cli", 'time': 1542561422}, {'author_name': 'Solo YH', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/106672992627018162416/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-gd128k4EVsU/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/AMZuucnga5f3LelxKWIBhZi7rOVDR-o47w/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3/photo.jpg', 'rating': 3, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': "There's really not much going on here. Beautiful architecture with nice outdoor area, but as for art, very lacking. It's half mid-century European paintings and half Catholic art. I wouldn't recommend unless it was free. I paid 50 pesos plus 5 extra to take photos.", 'time': 1560044308}, {'author_name': 'I Pickett', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/112354188355777928089/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Gja6tzYtmsGH5fcH6g4NpYub0UgqfybAtjgIBEvBQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6', 'rating': 3, 'relative_time_description': '2 years ago', 'text': '$50 pesos per person. Free entry on Sundays. Quick and interesting.', 'time': 1536349774}, {'author_name': 'Jose Miguel Perez Castillo', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/102932751113396744278/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Gh9Foy6ppdaAxV-MBbXA2FjZy8ReNAaQNZTKh4fR9c=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5', 'rating': 4, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': "The building's arquitecture is sublime, the place offers an art Oasis and a fine collection. The place needs more advertisement or special activities.", 'time': 1562793311}]

column15:
[{'author_name': 'Daniela de la Torre', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/117130384507045192136/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GirZfA39IWSCI4UUCE4cPkXFwidadYI4EKl0691JQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '2 weeks ago', 'text': 'Yes, it is worth the hype! The service is impeccable as you might expect.

There is a setup menu (7 courses) All of them amazingly planed an explosion inside your mouth.

Go with an open mind and to enjoy one of the most delicious meals in Mexico City.

Tip: if you can’t find a reservation you can still enjoy Enrique Olveras food at “El Molino Pujol” (also in Polanco).', 'time': 1600576180}, {'author_name': 'Eddie Rico', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/103671328925613399995/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GjZ16x--WBZRCoIyStP9-IKy-nFPWnG4KZcctelVQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3', 'rating': 4, 'relative_time_description': '3 weeks ago', 'text': 'The service was polite and fairly knowledgeable. The drink recommendations could be refined. My drink did not pair well with my food. Also I was plenty full and the dishes that were intended for both vegetarian and omnivore such as the mole and corn were absolutely wonderful. However some of the vegeterian offerings didn’t seems as thought out or complex as the omnivore offering. I loved that the only lights as a spotlight over my plate making it feel like I was eating a work of art. The textures and flavors of most dishes were very balanced and delicious. I would bring my out of town friends for the experience. I hope they work in the vegeterian offerings a bit more. I wish they would seem as appealing as the non veg plates. Wish I have experienced at other placesz', 'time': 1599836137}, {'author_name': 'Pankti Thakkar', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/102449580219569197318/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GhwkSxLsxK4vCKdlJg7kv8LdSfUU_BF4ZbdzZvOug=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a month ago', 'text': 'This place is magical and worth the price! I had the veggie tasting menu and absolutely loved it. We did the taco omakase and for the money you pay it was a fantastic experience. I will def be back. The mole madrè was a great dish like you would already expect! Every since course was filled with surprise, favor, elegance and authenticity! I can’t believe this place is not further up the list. FYI there is no Michelin guide in Mexico so it’s not the Michelin list but for me this was one of the best tacos I have had in Mexico! I highly highly recommend it. The inside is so inviting! The only thing that I didn’t like as much was their after dinner espresso. But such a small minuscule thing. The cocktails were on point. The outside garden was not open but looked very warm and inviting as well.', 'time': 1599372424}, {'author_name': 'Diego Torres-Palma', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/112995760995498953340/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-ttuRA5RNX54/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/AMZuucl1mW8ZmziNcAAk23c7YCzsUTi6qA/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3/photo.jpg', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a month ago', 'text': 'What a culinary treat! A new menu (redone during COVID) and it’s the essence of foods meets art. I can only describe this as very clean and delicious cuisine. If I had to pick my favorite dish - I think the mole was the most memorable but they were all absolutely amazing!', 'time': 1597677857}, {'author_name': 'BYRON A.', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/111074946555015333499/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/-ywBcqOZtz2k/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/AMZuuclZFtXLCekt7j_pl43ptHW1Adgx8g/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo/photo.jpg', 'rating': 1, 'relative_time_description': '2 weeks ago', 'text': 'Firstly, the service is what one would expect of a Michelin starred restaurant. Our table of two had a rotation of four to five different servers, they were all very nice. Unfortunately, that was the only good thing about this overrated and overpriced restaurant. Every single course of the seven courses were bizarre and not at all to either of our liking. This restaurant most definitely does not live up to the hype! Mexico City has great food and countless great restaurants, but this is not one of them. You can have 5 great dinners in CDMX for the undeserving price of this one. If presentation over substance matters most to someone, then maybe you will like it.', 'time': 1600688603}]
