column15:
[{'author_name': 'Sukhbir Jolly', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/101516584130947512686/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Gg8SVMNyn_yWrHrOrLfOB0ie-6iQ862ouvZ0y0M-Q=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5', 'rating': 4, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': "Nice looking restaurant with good service. I was recommended sirloin steak,which was brought over, but I said I don't like gristle/fat. Waiter then recommend another piece which turned out to be sirloin without bone. It was cooked to perfection but wasn't the kind of cut I like to eat.
Dessert was tiramisu which could of been for 2/3 people....it took the whole plate size!

column15: [{'author_name': 'Robert Gtz', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/104410331234892773777/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GhUQASpbXSQ6re4MTITMkfxw9MWgaqSHyFJy3VZ6Q=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '4 weeks ago', 'text': 'The Basilica is full of rich history and culture. The holy area is a must visit no matter what your spiritual background may be. It’s a place that unites people from many backgrounds and cultures. A must visit historic site of CDMX.', 'time': 1599508099}, {'author_name': 'Ajnu Jacob', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/110936085514306754684/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GjoBjfzbNnVw92Kw6TeV6tEKx8gHIhQrHvIWvB8tio=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 4, 'relative_time_description': '7 months ago', 'text': 'An iconic place of worship that’s rich in history and heritage. This Basilica brings people from around the world here, has several chapels within it for you to peacefully pray. And large areas to walk around in worship.', 'time': 1582515640}, {'author_name': 'Eileen Gao', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/107783253069897793323/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Gjqzz2woWqH9LFi3OzLjrXISBezxAmLvVS-Tref=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6', 'rating': 4, 'relative_time_description': 'a month ago', 'text': 'The Guadalupe church district is very grand. 7 churches in total. Clime up the hill and enjoy the lovely breeze and the lovely garden and view', 'time': 1599128125}, {'author_name': 'Lora Martinez', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/116434768113699005961/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Gh3e64kRd3qj_jA6yG2EpG2H4uR7eUQW8ODohta6A=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '9 months ago', 'text': 'Magnificent compound with many chapels to see and meander around. There is definitely a presence in this area. I recommend at least 2 hours to take it in. The gift shop has rosaries and other icons to buy and you can get them blessed by a priest on the side of the church at the “Bendiciones” station. Blessings🙏🏽🙏🏽🙏🏽', 'time': 1578403434}, {'author_name': 'Arman Barbuco', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/100089815269554047770/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GgLiqwNDNW-5-w4fYlB08pZVKsSyrLs5zblZO9N4w=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': 'The Basilica of Our Lady of Guadalupe is located in Zumarraga which is around 25-30 minutes ride via Uber from Bolivar street where our hotel is located. The Basilica is huge and beautiful. There is an entrance wherein you can see the clothe where the venerated image of the Virgin. Beside the Basilica there are two old churches. If you are a Catholic this place you should not miss. The architectures are simply amazing. The two old churches are not leveled if you try to look into the details maybe because of the earthquakes and there are also some cracks. A must see if you are visiting Mexico City.', 'time': 1567448265}]

column15: [{'author_name': 'Amanda Crook', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/113458124621196445763/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-B3sIf1OBFn8/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/AMZuuckJLnqPradw1Gvsv0guAbWvSA1LKg/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4/photo.jpg', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '6 months ago', 'text': 'One of the best if not the best meal we had in Mexico City. The place itself is very beautiful and the food equally so. Each dish was like eating a piece of art that thoughtfully designed and created. The food and drinks were delicious! The service was superb. We came for my birthday and they gave us Moet and some cake and ice cream. The restaurant is located in a very safe and well-to-do part of town. We will definitely be returning on our next trip!', 'time': 1584833070}, {'author_name': 'Tae E. Kim', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/110031824226270752928/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GhENxzDRVVRd81fZvG2btYwt_ArfmRgNTMd-DmGPSI=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a month ago', 'text': 'Excellent selection of food and wine, fantastic service and a distinct CDMX experience for visitors.', 'time': 1597033806}, {'author_name': 'Todd Hata', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/116578504618817290080/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GgGNT-EIMeG9_QUmpV4m7NWDOPj2hmhoK475IS2yQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '8 months ago', 'text': "This is my favorite restaurant in Mexico!  I'll eat here once or twice each time I visit Mexico City.  This time our group ordered a bunch of appetizers, a few salads, and were too full for entrees.  So we just ended up ordering some desserts to finish off this amazing meal.  Dulce Patria never fails to impress me with their creative and delicious dishes.", 'time': 1581296837}, {'author_name': 'Kevin H. Nguyen', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/116234507640906992056/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-Ao5-SU4Kt70/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/AMZuucnnZoyOQPz44jt62UB-pzoNqNti6A/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5/photo.jpg', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '11 months ago', 'text': 'This is a great restaurant.  Great foods, desserts, and services.  The wait staffs and chefs take their time to present the foods and desserts accordingly to Mexico traditions.  Also, great wine selection and must try the Flag drink.  Love is here and highly recommended.', 'time': 1572705644}, {'author_name': 'Laura L', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/115097159934076181159/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/-hl7BzUta7nc/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/AMZuucls_3e3CHMDar1lxvnpz_jxUBvj-Q/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo/photo.jpg', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '11 months ago', 'text': 'Wow, what a meal and what service! I visited Dulce Patria this past Tuesday evening and had the “pink menu” in honor of Breast Cancer Awareness month. Unique and delicious plates, paired with the yummiest mezcal cocktail. And the service was 💯 I highly recommend this place! Solo traveler friendly and welcoming :)', 'time': 1572097305}]

column15: [{'author_name': 'Nicolo Nisbett', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/105092974688256137749/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Gh6pccVykTi1cTLy8VC9H1hGAdmtF_YAo8xDjksDGw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '3 weeks ago', 'text': "You will find here food items that you simply cannot in other markets and most supermarkets. Examples: tahini and bok choy. Oh scorpions and other insects too if you're into those sorts of things.", 'time': 1599682710}, {'author_name': 'Claudius', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/110025838724539765332/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-zRDr4My76JI/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/AMZuuclLsGXU8nm_NSMxJyAEezauhq9zHQ/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba7/photo.jpg', 'rating': 3, 'relative_time_description': '2 months ago', 'text': "Mid July 2020 roughly half of the stalls are open, very few clients to be seen.  Local produce abounded but the stands who sell the more exotic stuff were closed for obvious reasons.  Had an espresso at the stand on the left hand side that claims to have gourmet coffee and has a Conde Nast traveler poster - it was good, not great but I'd still recommend it if you'd like an espresso.  Just don't come here expecting an exceptionally good espresso.\nOne of the stalls had fake Cuban cigars. See picture !", 'time': 1595074664}, {'author_name': 'Nick Villanueva', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/114958019316678379134/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Gj5YL2YQQzoUvsrbqYRV5a0b4VKiYlm4cgd5M3Z=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 3, 'relative_time_description': '7 months ago', 'text': 'Regular market. Nothing expectacular. Some curiosity eats like scorpion, but I suspect it is more for tourists than local consumption. Food stalls inside the market.', 'time': 1583865907}, {'author_name': 'Alejandro L', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/110486245145073897295/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-Mz5MvnasQRA/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/AMZuuck9K5-EMCPnx5ykbo4Z64jOPRkSdw/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5/photo.jpg', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a month ago', 'text': 'You can find pretty much everything you want for your own personal foodie life', 'time': 1598916804}, {'author_name': 'Jose Maria Noriega', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/100969431916581701057/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GjVAnUVXyO0vDGpWv8E-dg6f_T22InT4XV86_ZJSALNetQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '9 months ago', 'text': 'The best market in Mexico City the place to go for all Chefs, Gourmets and Gourmands. Fui por su calificación y es real. Si bien el menú es reducido los platos son muy bien presentados y deliciosos. La atención es muy buena. Les falta publicidad y la zona creo que los perjudica, pero es uno de los lugares a los que hay que ir. Ojalá tuvieran mas sucursales. Volvería sin dudas.', 'time': 1583786117}, {'author_name': 'Diana Bedolla', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/111188797739212985280/reviews', 'language': 'es', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Gg9DGo1NX97pl0TaK3VaK85zA7XbYUH3HiVHwhe=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '8 months ago', 'text': 'Simplemente excelente. Platillos finamente diseñados y muy sabrosos. Una muy buena selección de vinos que combinados con la comida hace que sea una experiencia particular y exquisita.\nSimply excellent. Very tasty with interesting and very well designed plates. Also very good selection of wines that combined with the food makes it a particular and very pleasant experience.', 'time': 1580913306}]

column15:
[{'author_name': 'Jose Carlos Alarcon Lopez', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/103393454877034258894/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Gg9ybyEA5HH9WgxcIkWZcrRNswjG4_hXoCXp5e5=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5', 'rating': 4, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': 'Located in the hotel that has the most restaurants of “Mexico’s 120 best”  Chapulín never disappoints.
The drinks are awesome and change seasonally. Food is Mexican with a modern twist. Service is kind and prompt. Location is always busy so reserve in advance. They have smoking section for those extended family reunions.', 'time': 1564691244}, {'author_name': 'Ale O', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/101712432884384820858/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GiBS7JsJ-ExgaRCx_Ha0378cOZnyWQvx9txTOHnBA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': 'Superb food.

If you have foreign visitors who want to have a good take on Mexican food, this place serves the purpose.

The place is beautiful on its own right, they really take care about the details and atmosphere, make sure to have chapulines (crickets) and escamoles (ant eggs) as they are very well prepared here.

They have insignia dishes, try them, you won’t be disappointed.

Attentive and efficient staff, prices on the higher end but well worth it.

This is a must to visit.', 'time': 1567199559}, {'author_name': 'Patricio A.', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/101641188816530562076/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-wnaEDSU-TNc/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/AMZuucnOeo19Jz36SJUqoBsbx87ZmPBw-A/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5/photo.jpg', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': 'Fantastic Mexican Restaurant inside the Intercontinental Hotel in Polanco. Service is outstanding, food is great and price to value is fair (surprising for a hotel based restaurant). I would highly recommend the Chapulines as an appetizer to share and Rib Eye Tacos are surprisingly good - yes, it is a bit excessive to pay nearly US$20 for 3 tacos, but they are a full meal if you have all 3. Great option if you have foreign visitors as there is something for everybody despite short menu.', 'time': 1561345413}, {'author_name': 'Esteban Sanchez', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/108259203098302231517/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Gj3FhbZpjBTLdFsyLtc4w5_5Sr4M8TYUtB3IYjdlMk=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '6 months ago', 'text': 'Best Service and food. Tacos and chapulines.', 'time': 1584316687}, {'author_name': 'Mario O. Martínez Ordaz', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/114200050021601711740/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-ACVMJC5hP4E/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/AMZuucmkq8pzxsUVFUct1DtIdIdOBISVbg/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4/photo.jpg', 'rating': 2, 'relative_time_description': '9 months ago', 'text': "Simply put: this place is way too overrated.
Giving a little bit more details from best to worst...
1) decoration and architecture: this is the only outstanding thing of the restaurant. Really amazing every single detail. That's why it was among the 21 Prettiest Restaurants in Mexico City according to Food and Pleasure. But... That online report never mentioned that we were to expect amazing food nor good service at all...
2) food: it is good, but it does not blow your mind... It is honestly flat... Without surprises nor anything that could make you remind of Chapulín as a good and unique restaurant.
3) service/attention: the worst without hesitating. They left us at the very cornered table, our original waiter disappeared after 20 minutes, they never offered us a clothe rack, the sommelier (first one attending us) was a disaster (he brought us the wrong wine bottle twice, then he surrendered saying they did not have what we ordered). Afterwards, the other sommelier, Hector, moved faster and found us quickly our alternate choice. However, we had already had our entrée so the damage was done...

Definitely not recommended for any occasion.", 'time': 1577244999}]

I am glad they saved this mural from the '85 earthquake that destroyed many parts of the city and where thousands died (sad day).  Like must masterpieces of Diego, this is history!", 'time': 1580573344}, {'author_name': 'Elizabeth Vecchio', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/108395094501718768503/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Gi6gMr9bvYhCDmqqXMZAmOVmGuCPAt45-wU1Tev-Ms=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5', 'rating': 3, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': 'This museum is very small. But a wonderful piece of history. The mural has all the important figures of Mexican history in one image. You can see in English and in Spanish an explanation of who each individual in the photo represents and a little bit of their personal history. This is the only item in this museum. Entrance is very inexpensive under $3. Easy to get to and a quick 30-minute explore', 'time': 1557939294}, {'author_name': 'Tra Hitt', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/109144969972202034254/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GjsEoYQnD_nOivRAemz-ab3UEcI0o-cE-pgotea4HU=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '11 months ago', 'text': 'Nothing can prepare you for this.... If you are even remotely a history nerd or a Riviera fan, come, do this, thank me later', 'time': 1571228745}, {'author_name': 'Rick Zablocki', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/109083406818132753397/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/-2Vs2tTJwcOE/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/AMZuucmTVKpnw6gxWJUAGtFyTk6EcEwN-w/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo/photo.jpg', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '9 months ago', 'text': 'This is such a treasure to see. Imagine  a day when most of the important figures of Mexican History spend a day together in Parque Alameda.  Spectacular mural.  Can you find Diego and Frieda?', 'time': 1578441013}, {'author_name': 'Nora Sourouzian', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/101243292073815500226/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GhS18lJYloppEds0PKiCBG7Kk8A33aWpGSbcEql=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': 'It is worth to see this one and only work in that museum. 40 pesos with the right to take pictures. This mural of Diego is a good Witness of the Mexican history.', 'time': 1550782793}]

column15: [{'author_name': 'Elijah Monroe', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/103883979009057959135/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GjUtV9ELe43cHai5cPP2iDgMMIeOLSes-zFlDkeWeU=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': "The culinary vision of the chef is unmatched in this area (and in this price range). It's the perfect blend of creative originality and traditional touches. It's rare to see a place take so many chances and just hit a home run nearly every time. Carrot and habañero salsa on macaroni - sounds weird? It was amazing. Calabaza relleno paired with chicken stroganoff and horchata. Guess what? Also amazing. Deep fried corn full of hibiscus flowers? Yep, that was amazing too. I'm such a fan of the traditional food in this city (there is nowhere in the world quite like it) that I'm skeptical of fusion or anything experimental. However, this casual little restaurant is pushing the frontiers of an already fantastic cuisine. Eat here now. Let the chef decide what you eat. It's fun. It's new. And eventfully there will be a line down the block.", 'time': 1558396200}, {'author_name': 'Antonio Albanés Santana', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/111763911279526163260/reviews', 'language': 'es', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Gg11AA6jGQd5IOJaI_4S-c5HSYI2p6msE3M5Y3sHQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 1, 'relative_time_description': 'a week ago', 'text': 'Es un lugar al que solíamos asistir antes de la pandemia. Ahora que estamos en la nueva normalidad y en semáforo naranja, es desafortunado que las dos veces que hemos intentado entrar, la persona que atiende la primera vez no tenía cubrebocas y estaba manipulando alimentos; la segunda, no nos tomó la temperatura y al preguntarle nos dijo “no es necesario pero sí quiere se la tomo.” Es importante apoyar los lugares que cumplen estrictamente con la normativa sanitaria para el cuidado de todos.', 'time': 1601219374}, {'author_name': 'Gerardo Daniel Martinez Vázquez', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/117536038273490168291/reviews', 'language': 'es', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Gja0EKZuGzlgVikh54Glzt4nJgpmS341g4TnERMMw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '3 weeks ago', 'text': 'Si de repente no sabes en donde ir a comer y las terribles opciones de Alsea ya te tienen hasta el copete, te recomiendo este restaurante en la Narvarte que aparte de ser muy bueno tiene precios muy accesibles. El menú cambia todos los días y es comida Gourmet. Muy recomendable.', 'time': 1599928372}, {'author_name': 'Javivi Coach', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/117411831451112665833/reviews', 'language': 'es', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GhJUPbZhiwvrixylOORpHA2mlWOfaoyJQ5I6G2YIg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 4, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': 'El lugar es muy agradable y el servicio muy atento y cálido. Tienen una propuesta interesante en cuanto a los platillos y la presentación y a pesar de, el precio es bastante accesible.\nSu café maravilloso! Su sazón es lo que a mi parecer puede mejorar un poco.\nRecomendable 👌🏻', 'time': 1554054944}, {'author_name': 'Fernando G Bustamante', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/107894556795015642481/reviews', 'language': 'es', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GiP-Sqr24AS0ltW-11toRxZzxrrodBUjNCoO7Empw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3', 'rating': 4, 'relative_time_description': '2 months ago', 'text': 'Agradable lugar, recomendable para desayunar, con precios accesibles y bien ubicado', 'time': 1594575318}]

Pero sería complicado volver.', 'time': 1577992465}, {'author_name': 'Alhely Gonzalez', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/106622866943441506902/reviews', 'language': 'es', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Gh5urjnNYlFLr0yC-ZgY1_rZHqqlXjD0HfYw8j8EQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '2 years ago', 'text': 'Muy bonito y pintoresco el lugar, se desayuna rico y me platico la mesera que los viernes y sábados va un señor a tocar trova, tendré que regresar !!!', 'time': 1536556026}]

column15:
[{'author_name': 'Monica Rivera', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/107074390665313624214/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GhY69r2-1TAhg1-kPBHM-YXoRSzKvU2woyVt8m-Iw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '9 months ago', 'text': 'Great everything! The service was outstanding (Thanks Alfredo). Food was super delicious, it is not cheap but it is not overpriced either, at least the quality and portions are decent for what you pay. Loved the ribeye, great quality steak! The baked potato was delicious too. As an appetizer, the plantain “chalupas” with beef “tinga” are a must, and I was able to order 4 instead of the regular portion of 3. Drink menu was varied and the Mexican Caipirinha with mezcal was very tasty, (maybe the drinks could be a bit overpriced though). The dulce de leche dessert was big and very tasty, another must. The venue was nice, cozy, it can get a bit loud though and people can smoke in most part of the restaurant (those last 2 things would be the only cons). Reservations are a must as the waiting time was about 40 minutes for me as I did not book in advance. Overall, a great upscale option for a nice, fancy meal in Southern Mexico City.', 'time': 1576719091}, {'author_name': 'Niccolo Spataro', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/100957553601759795862/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Gj7sYSLG-RdSv33fBcC5EKNsqf0fD1pSG2PQjqb=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '9 months ago', 'text': 'The best steakhouse in Mexico City has a new location in the Artz Shopping Mall. column15: [{'author_name': 'Guillermo Ortiz', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/109544679615424359755/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-HEM8nRhNDjU/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/AMZuucnUnXEOQTK80HQ42fXsOw3kVX2VcA/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4/photo.jpg', 'rating': 4, 'relative_time_description': '7 months ago', 'text': "It was nice because it has a lot of toys most of them old toys, I remembered when I used to play with them, but I think that the facilities aren't that good. It was cozy and quite dirty. But in general it was good", 'time': 1582499738}, {'author_name': 'Robert Victor', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/114067929415105541724/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-5IwmJ5y6QQI/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/AMZuuclFSUxEtXwF0gSFJ_oOmzqJLLnlzQ/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3/photo.jpg', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '9 months ago', 'text': 'Absolutely amazing place. Congratulations to the curator for producing a walk down memory lane over four floors and a roof terrace. Something for young and old to behold.', 'time': 1578379582}, {'author_name': 'Nancy Ableser', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/113594534469462184448/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-tQhxyKTlwIw/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/AMZuucnfhOyoTI-BZwAhOE5sNkXgRsiJVg/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo/photo.jpg', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': "This antique toy museum is FABULOUS! I've been twice, and I'll definitely be back. There's so much to see. Everything is displayed in a very artistic manner. Such a fun place to visit!!!", 'time': 1560901700}, {'author_name': 'Andrew Elcock', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/115191428930745191717/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GhMS5eYFNFzIUoJssclcZKLu83cnJYoeAhDGsD53g=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': 'An amazing collection of toys complimented with wonderful street art in the most amazing unmolested building. The museum is arranged over 4 floors. During our visit, we actually met the collectamaniac himself. What a gent. So precious of Matchbox from England, explaining the history of the company & the cause of their demise. Very fascinating guy! Various items are for sale, quite tempting. Well worth a visit & strongly recommend.', 'time': 1552788454}, {'author_name': 'Inga Jahn', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/102448017089366750037/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GiBqgKuWW3FJhh7Ug3vXQH53KJD10rRoZpn1M0l=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 4, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': 'An amazing colection of old toys. The combination and presentation of the toys is sometimes quite artistic and surreal. It also seems quite chaotic in some places. We wondered why there are also old cigarettes packages or beer cans on display. Very cool street art presentation on the upper level. Amazing Barbie collection.', 'time': 1558816700}]

column15:
[{'author_name': 'AndresRafael StefaniSucre', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/112023776705256157793/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GgNq9Qc_dga8LxXIycVGF9b9qx9OUwgncTD4O-84A=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba7', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '2 weeks ago', 'text': 'The Cholula Archaeological Zone marks the location of the pre-Conquest city and pilgrimage site. The pyramid there is considered the largest in Mexico, and stands now without its cladding.
The pre-Contact city was sacked in 1519 by Cortes, his followers, and an army of Tlaxcala allies.

Ancient Pyramid that lost its cladding. There is now a church on top. Passages can be explored, where you can see the different layers. Around the large mound, you can see the remains of temples. There is a large stone head and a an exquisite stele. The construction consists of loose material. It was the largest pyramid in Mexico. The location given is for the pyramid ruins.', 'time': 1600464907}, {'author_name': 'Sonia Pires', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/109363432272646751783/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Gg6ALzOUofKfLXnJfUZuGDZgLcT9P7MpPuQ0BYUJw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '11 months ago', 'text': 'The ambiance here is so great! If you want to experience a full Mexican experience, this is the place. The variety of restaurants with good food made from scratch; the cultural events on the plaza on the weekends made you feel the full experience in such a small place. You can enjoy the streets full of people walking around buying  Mexican crafts and food. I totally love this little town!', 'time': 1571446210}, {'author_name': 'Sonia Perez', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/101826614838142619047/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GifR2yNN7VhguitAM9KICpAhqBOMydsbrgmCStPiQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '11 months ago', 'text': 'The ambiance here is so great! If you want to experience a full Mexican experience, this is the place. The variety of restaurants with good food made from scratch; the cultural events on the plaza on the weekends made you feel the full experience in such a small place. You can enjoy the streets full of people walking around buying  Mexican crafts and food. I totally love this little town!', 'time': 1571455237}, {'author_name': 'vladimir tovar', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/112413746618565461508/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-zUlIBpo_sjc/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/AMZuuckbXImK-9QyINoQi4dMvz9hcOe1FQ/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo/photo.jpg', 'rating': 4, 'relative_time_description': '2 weeks ago', 'text': 'Tha place is closed by the contingency, but it still quite beautiful.', 'time': 1600692991}, {'author_name': 'Sharon R', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/112343827306743122075/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-Swpw9azlwMY/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAABSJU/AMZuucmSRe_kxmfC8PpZIBP7uQ6k_dRB2A/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5/photo.jpg', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '7 months ago', 'text': "Hilariously visited this by accident and didn't find out it was a pyramid until after we left (just thought it was a small hill). The church at the top is beautiful and gives an amazing view to the entire surrounding area. The climb is tough - 20+ minutes of stairs and no way to reach the top by vehicle - but well worth it.

Didn't see the archiological side because we arrived too early and it wasn't open yet.", 'time': 1582499156}]

column15: [{'author_name': 'J skeep', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/104471087216911665853/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-EcXaxUOpkLc/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/AMZuucnAS7Uvj3djIwv2B8sHnycyyVZTMg/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4/photo.jpg', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '2 years ago', 'text': 'Birria bowl is fantastic. Comes with pretty much unlimited tortillas as he kept refilling it. He will also refill your broth (which was the best part in my opinion). The sides of pickled onion/habanero and fried chilies were very good, but also very spicy. I paid 100 pesos for this plus a drink. Easily worth it.', 'time': 1524079008}, {'author_name': 'Valentin Dorigny', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/108226532638692266015/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GhBRZWwd_WViaebS4LD6-HnCHi9GhEkxZVuWf_sJ68=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': "Excellent Birria ! Still open at 6:45pm when we showed up, the guys is super friendly and the soup is simply amazing. Can't recommend enough !", 'time': 1559306725}, {'author_name': 'Muhammad Huzaifi Bin Mohd Kamil', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/109148353310154915178/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GgNPA2YbUA3jG5zdcOM9i-3KDGBlnITPfCPxnoVOg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba2', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': 'Friendly owner and great food! We hardly spoke any Spanish but the owner was really kind and friendly to us. 90 pesos for the Birria and he will just keep topping up the tortillas as you eat.', 'time': 1553823232}, {'author_name': 'Ca Li', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/102952825356070081404/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/-wU-oaL_A-mI/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/AMZuucl-lsURV6NdphX2DpJVruMYuZ6kkQ/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3/photo.jpg', 'rating': 4, 'relative_time_description': '7 months ago', 'text': 'Good birria (beef stew) with strong broth, and lots of beef. The owner gives you hot tortillas as well and offers extra soup. It was a bit too spicy even for me, perhaps he added extra chili by accident this day, as no one else seems to mention this.', 'time': 1581729515}, {'author_name': 'Tehneya', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/115053188841946655830/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-y3wbQJguMR4/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/AMZuucndmDoVUMnqp99VBaHqZ7IJ4lMKSQ/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba2/photo.jpg', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '11 months ago', 'text': "Best Birria in the city! This food stand is always busy with both locals and tourists. Excellent service, the guy working will give you warm fresh tortillas to have with the Birria. He also fills your bowl up when you're getting low. If you're looking for delicious street food, give this place a try!", 'time': 1573188216}]

column15: [{'author_name': 'Jovanny Celis', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/103018000673466676120/reviews', 'language': 'es', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GgRn4YHzsA8q5RhldkTNZ0u7HpfLxli8-GWr1qu=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '8 months ago', 'text': 'Este lugar está genial para comer enchiladas!! Tienen 9 variedades: rojas, suizas, con chile pasilla, de mole, enfrijoladas, ahogadas... También hay diferentes tipos de huevos: con jamón, a la mexicana, tirados... Hay burritos, consome servido en un tarro de barro, chilaquiles, etc. También hay paquetes que incluyen jugo y café, estos no aplican en servicio de Uber Eats. Es un local cálido donde predomina la madera y es muy tranquilo. Son muy amables y el servicio es veloz. Aceptan tarjeta.', 'time': 1580959163}, {'author_name': 'Abraham González', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/109206403988964432921/reviews', 'language': 'es', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Gg7jshxClp38N2MYk7SMkuSBIf1MwSLdbh_F1gH6e0=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '8 months ago', 'text': 'Muy buen servicio, precio accesible y muy buena porción !!!', 'time': 1580065347}, {'author_name': 'Paola Vazquez', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/103092719750295097123/reviews', 'language': 'es', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-MpibedZJIEw/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/AMZuucn2Vp8j0FemwAB7PbhYd5eEnJ_VKQ/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5/photo.jpg', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': 'El lugar abre los siete días de la semana. El menú es pequeño pero tiene suficiente variedad para todos los gustos: huevos, burritos, pollo, cafés, jugos, chilaquiles, enchiladas. Por las mañanas los paquetes incluyen el plato fuerte, fruta y café; mientras que por las tardes son los mismos platos fuertes pero en lugar de fruta y café añaden consomé y agua de sabor. La atención del personal es excelente y los precios son justos. Lo mejor: es pet friendly! Hasta le puedes ordenar una torta a tu mejor amigo!', 'time': 1569277890}, {'author_name': 'Tule Patoni', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/112937567468374785790/reviews', 'language': 'es', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GjgiLq-5LopHtFzXjGqFmZ6zKaiqXo21WXFZbKZww=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 3, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': 'Buen servicio, sin embargo el sabor no es nada para recordar. Sweet place. Will certainly go back if and when visiting Mexico City again!', 'time': 1567307977}, {'author_name': 'Nimue Le Fevre', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/115189901396101401790/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GjK1WNFCGx7u7GxXkGfAYrnhOrMIkqrcn4Ik65pjg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': "As a vegan tourist I was nervous about finding places I could safely eat, especially with my limited Spanish. I was so lucky to find this place while walking around, I could order anything on the menu without having to worry and the food was delicious and just like authentic street food, so I didn't feel like I was missing out on the culture. I highly recommend the pastor tacos, I'd never tried pineapple in my tacos before but it was so good, especially with salsa and lime. The staff were so friendly and helpful and customised our orders when we asked. Whether you're a local or a tourist, a vegan or a non vegan, I highly recommend trying this place.", 'time': 1540605718}, {'author_name': 'FlyingPigs Bicimensajeria', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/104116254208300822964/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GiHwq2Ru6Qzarr-KdSjyBOV4CXbrx5AYY9nmng=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 3, 'relative_time_description': '8 months ago', 'text': 'Poor portions, good taste.', 'time': 1581184367}, {'author_name': 'Timko Germany', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/104021072160001132458/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-UMh6Xw3bdc8/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/AMZuucnT7YKmR2D3QtrenbHViicZMHwBZQ/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo/photo.jpg', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': 'Great Burritos, very delicious! Aceptan tarjeta y efectivo.', 'time': 1578805302}, {'author_name': 'Yuliet Marquez', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/109428859193934427635/reviews', 'language': 'es', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GjMRVWe-wiAIfNdl76eIgyYxRHatC7vBRFT-Qsqa6I=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 4, 'relative_time_description': '6 months ago', 'text': 'Los tacos ricos,  pero me parecen algo caros ya que antes les ponían nopales y de sabor ricos pero nada extraordinario y el queso que pides como extra en tu taco es lo que le sigue de malo no lo pidan.\n\n¿Volvería a ir? La opción de trigo (a mi parecer) siempre es mejor. También encuentras trufas y flanes (obviamente veganos). La atención es excelente. [{'author_name': 'Claudia Lopez Perales', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/103514212367216426749/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Gj_ykv3er7kRCsQ3fLbdmNKkAewUe6M4U7VtggAOQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '11 months ago', 'text': 'Very educational on the start up of the cocoa. At entrance you are offered a cocoa bean for tasting. Staff offers free guide of the museum. They have a small room with walls covered in chocolate! The smell in there was amazing!! Next to the gift shop is a small Cafe area that sells all sorts of chocolate. For Day of the Dead they had skull molded chocolate made with tequila, rum, whiskey, wine and others.', 'time': 1572878365}, {'author_name': 'Una Le Roux', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/104761942310306972837/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GhPqwHX-LlZ-4bxN8cEZ_6zYtyNSxkwbvOEiVGc=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3', 'rating': 3, 'relative_time_description': '7 months ago', 'text': 'Who knew real chocolate without sugar could taste so good x', 'time': 1583800571}, {'author_name': 'Shai Ghelberg', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/105691477810586363760/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Gh4l2ndmcXe8p3Y3aVCzuY5kqRlLprNiLkJJmZ3dw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5', 'rating': 4, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': "Interesting take on history of chocolate and other interesting related fact.
A lot is in solely Spanish, which made it a bit hard to dive into the explanations, but it's pretty easily understood by the context.
The shop is great, and very worth a visit.
It's a bit overpriced for a 30 minutes attraction.
I'd definitely recommend the shop and coffee though.", 'time': 1568060297}, {'author_name': 'Мария Стручкова', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/109885123819566687732/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GgZI50dzqVIwtw98n7WgLGkAjmXoauskiYwQ6Dp8Q=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 4, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': 'I admired chocolate store. Prices were cheap. Marshmallow chocolate was 7 pesos. Also there are some interesting flavors such as tequila chocolate. I think it’s a good gift. Chocolate is good, but I still think that Que Bo chocolate are way more better, but they are also 2 times expensive.', 'time': 1567471571}, {'author_name': 'William Ford', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/101218336127481917043/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GgsINFWJTVKRQNBWIzhCp1sTceHo9Z-3XDksTIESPY=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': "Nice little museum! Shout out to Juan who was our unofficial but excellent guide in English. It's small, but comprehensive and very interesting if you're curious about the interface between prehispánic and European culture", 'time': 1569794943}]

column15:
[{'author_name': 'Antonio Villa', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/116671638423188141620/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GgFvIHi0X1A1sJMliqm8wcXfNIzd1mAJeB66X9P=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3', 'rating': 4, 'relative_time_description': 'a month ago', 'text': 'Ride a horse, ride a quad or just have a decent meal and drink.', 'time': 1598415274}, {'author_name': 'Alethea Mata', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/109324445879478479889/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-ImsiBx9nJhk/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/AMZuucl2ZOzJqVtiVR4X78qSjgDoEGKbgA/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3/photo.jpg', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': "Great place to visit if you're around Mexico City. We made about 2 hours from the city. They have horses, quads, fishing, canoeing and restaurants. The food and activities are very accessible. We rode horses for 100 pesos for half an hour and they let us free ride. The quads were about 180 for half an hour. My food was a little under 100 pesos. I also got a piña colada for 70 pesos and it was really good. Overall really good with good prices!", 'time': 1561588410}, {'author_name': 'Edgar Castillo', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/107856272999360078345/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-psDpeYSyOV4/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/AMZuuckh3GA8pFJwkK1O7VGXU0Q_lOWD4Q/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo/photo.jpg', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '10 months ago', 'text': "Great place for the family. Went during the weekdays so it wasn't busy and prices were more negotiable. Riding the atvs was epic and it's a must. Missed out on the horse ride(got late). I was disappointed there was trash around the area but the people there were friendly. Dont be afraid to ask what else you can do or directions. That's how we get around.", 'time': 1574907371}, {'author_name': 'aimitch', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/110783179062930790650/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Gh6q0S2pF_n8ynANRyONUyao2sE7UUGgECio9XhKg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '2 years ago', 'text': "A really good place to visit with so much to do. Horse riding, quad biking, zip lines, wonderful walks. Especially good to take the kids. There are plenty things to keep them occupied.
Be prepared for very changeable weather, one minute rain, literally 5 minutes later, brilliant sunshine. Seriously, be prepared for any weather!
On holidays and weekends the road leading up to it can be very busy but weekdays are ok.
There are many places touting for your business so if you don't like a price, try elsewhere. This also applies to the food. So many places to choose from but they are always glad of the business so the food is good and the service is excellent.
Really worth a day out, the views are worth it alone.", 'time': 1522547212}, {'author_name': 'Omar Abbas', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/107029865460086569233/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/-J1oee7Db9nY/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/AMZuucktc2kZGyFd5q6v9Gpa9vBRi6qdng/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3/photo.jpg', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a month ago', 'text': 'Nice place for a saturday', 'time': 1597528177}]

They even have a small show where they climb the pole and spin from a rope while they play music.', 'time': 1578192461}, {'author_name': 'Tegan Fellows', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/116903292554830161047/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-VbOP72XqGPE/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/AMZuuckXM5lLtqZI0Up3Rt0Xvu6vGwblgA/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5/photo.jpg', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '11 months ago', 'text': "A lovely attraction, a little difficult to get to for a short ride.
While eating on the boat is. Avery quaint idea I would say it's worth eating at a taco stand before hand as a meal on the boat will set you back about 200pesos as opposed to 20.

Best to pair up with other tourists as the price is per hour and not per person. It'll set you back 500 pesos, maybe 400 if you haggle.

The mariachi bands Are a nice addition for only 150 pesos", 'time': 1571290876}, {'author_name': 'Rene Aguirre', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/117453023725368353543/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GivFi_35_jBQh7_t9KUd9ytPij3xKjBuZSpl5v3nA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba2', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '2 weeks ago', 'text': 'Loved it .. if you can bring your own beer or tequila..', 'time': 1600651180}]

column15:
[{'author_name': 'Annette Robbins', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/111893294681690968650/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-IBi7dA4JVwk/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/AMZuucn8Bgl8f4FMN0IBzy7pu9iRhnA7Tw/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3/photo.jpg', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '10 months ago', 'text': 'Amazing.
Ask for Oscar to be your pilot
Balloons dont steer... the float on the breeze. However...air currents move at different speeds and directions as you go up or down. More than a dozen balloons took off this morning...only a couple skillfully floated over the pyramids.
You are at the mercy of the winds... but skill plays a factor too.
Oscar spoke English... took pics of us... showed us geographical details... and landed the balloon on a trailer with us inside.
Great teamwork.
The experience was professional... fun... and something I will remember forever
I cant think of a single thing I wished was better', 'time': 1575072542}, {'author_name': 'Todd Bailey', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/101984034115514214411/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Ggh_2bB7zbD--aW_wTJISfgqNBYNTu5J6kQ1oNTgg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '3 weeks ago', 'text': 'Great price and everything was very professional!!!', 'time': 1599747659}, {'author_name': 'Maikol Jimenez', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/108582269959214383391/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GidSp22tCgTLSYOMwIATQOdOtokRWyvuzjJlLluGA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '3 years ago', 'text': 'Great Experience!', 'time': 1506057138}, {'author_name': 'Blanca Barcena', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/101195635127275672643/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-CZ4aJ6Jxha0/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/AMZuucl_5T7OcpyjGlV9JvBJCVK8coqbaw/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo/photo.jpg', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '2 years ago', 'text': '.lll.lllllllll.ll.ll..l........lll.llpp.l...l.ll.......ll..llll.ll...lllll........l.l..............ll..l..ll....l.........lllll.........ll....................l..llllll.llll.lllllllll.llllllll.ll.l.ll.l.ll.ll.l.l.llll........................ll.l............................................................................................', 'time': 1512836533}, {'author_name': 'PAWA BONGA', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/112625021330211569825/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Ggt2A4PX-yVOtAdjpmVVgAG6NSlY2KzSLkLkIYc2xc=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3', 'rating': 4, 'relative_time_description': '2 years ago', 'text': 'Color fest!!', 'time': 1521403305}]

[{'author_name': 'Mark Pabst', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/117054556390643971643/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Gj5hIzN3KQloDp06ig4OTbkIPjAFXkqv0fN-TcI=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 4, 'relative_time_description': '8 months ago', 'text': 'The signage is in both Spanish and English at this well maintained although small site.  Unfortunately the conquest and urbanization have taken its toll.', 'time': 1579703097}, {'author_name': 'RAM IMAGERY', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/114290696883181775441/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GjeU2mcew5eHvouCFe-toUfCLlH69MUYBHUEiDHb9I=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '10 months ago', 'text': 'Beautiful sight! Such a historic & significant location for Mexican culture. A true testament to archeology,  religion & cultural influence.', 'time': 1573739382}, {'author_name': 'Antonio Gutierrez', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/109498964188124133309/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GiYOkC9SlLv6Vkmq79nGh5SNQWUjrKNvb6YBbGf0w=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '11 months ago', 'text': "Ruins right in the middle of the city, less visited than the templo mayor by the main church at zócalo.
If you live in the area, there's a doggie club that meets everyday from 8:00am - 10:00am lots of dogs, and at 6:00pm if you don't want to get Chased by a schnauzer or a Chihuahua avoid at all costs! (Joking)", 'time': 1571751874}, {'author_name': 'Christian Cortes', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/106487570129452776497/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-Y8kUeKByGlo/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAD4k/AMZuuckmYQ9rMt7o_ptRWVKMKiCQa3IzqA/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba2/photo.jpg', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '9 months ago', 'text': 'Amazing how this archeological site sits in between this metropolitan area. Must see if your in the city.', 'time': 1578550963}, {'author_name': 'Nancy Foster', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/115216618459592148813/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/-OXkU2-prbdI/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/AMZuucltYT3_CoZv4w1la5_lrSbbm4nfrw/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo/photo.jpg', 'rating': 4, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': "Eerie place when you know that this was the place where countless college students were murdered by overnment backed military forces in 1968, it also gives you a strange vibe of peace from the hustle & bustle of the city. You feel like you have been transported 60 years into the past.

The museum is very small and doesn't have English translations which could be an issue for non Spanish speaking tourists. Due to the 2017 earthquake, several outdoor walkways are still closed pending permits to reopen that have not been done yet. This gets especially annoying because some alternate exits that take you directly to the Santiago curch are walled off, which forces you to walk a huge U turn for pretty much nothing since there are no large buildings next to the affected exits that could fall down anytime soon. There is a tent between two of the Aztec structures with no notices anywhere towards its purpose. I presume archeologists are doing a dig and the tent serves to protect the site, but the lack of information to the tourist is a letdown.

On the plus side, there is zero garbage, staff is friendly, and the grass is kept immaculately cut and well watered. The site usually has next to zero tourists on weekdays, you pretty much have the site all to yourself since very few foreign tourists visit it.

As a pyramid site that is far better condition from Templo Mayor, it is a rather underrated Aztec archeological site that is reachable by bus from Bellas Artes very quickly. Another option is to walk around 15-20 minutes from the Tlatelolco subway station.

It continues to be one of my favorite pyramid sites in the city!", 'time': 1561349524}]

column15: [{'author_name': 'AndresRafael StefaniSucre', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/112023776705256157793/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GgNq9Qc_dga8LxXIycVGF9b9qx9OUwgncTD4O-84A=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba7', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '2 weeks ago', 'text': 'Superimposed pyramids in exact East West orientation. The structure was probably started by the Chichimecs with the final 3 layers in the Aztec style. New layers were made every 52 years, the pre Columbian Century. The final structure is 17 Meters tall and covers 43 square Meters. There are 88 stone snake figures representing Quetzalcoatl around the base. The altar of skulls is now in the Mexico City Archaeological Museum.', 'time': 1600464126}, {'author_name': 'Monica Rivera', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/107074390665313624214/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GhY69r2-1TAhg1-kPBHM-YXoRSzKvU2woyVt8m-Iw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6', 'rating': 4, 'relative_time_description': 'a month ago', 'text': 'Nice “pyramid” located in the State of Mexico. Unfortunately it was closed due to the pandemic but it was possible to get a good look of it from the outside. However, investments should be made as it looked kind of neglected. Safe zone for a quick visit.', 'time': 1598366542}, {'author_name': 'Robert Victor', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/114067929415105541724/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-5IwmJ5y6QQI/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/AMZuuclFSUxEtXwF0gSFJ_oOmzqJLLnlzQ/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3/photo.jpg', 'rating': 4, 'relative_time_description': '9 months ago', 'text': 'Get to Indio Verdes subway station then catch a taxi or an uber. There is also a very interesting museum that could benefit foreign tourists understanding with more English language signage. I was the only non Mexican tourist and many visitors were speaking an indigenous language perhaps Nahuatl.\nIf you are a foreigner do not visit on your own the surrounding area is very poor and a group visit might be safer.', 'time': 1578379681}, {'author_name': 'Manuel Marin', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/107888839699526043470/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/-vx2Gldxu7n8/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/AMZuucm_5HXyd7DqORLAKI8ZSPbPM4r6hA/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo/photo.jpg', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '11 months ago', 'text': 'It is nice, but small. I would not spend more than 30 minutes walking around the pyramid. Outside the pyramid there is some fast food cars.', 'time': 1571744445}, {'author_name': 'Eric MC', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/107947965334005424796/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GhS4TGD5PZgsYVd0oDqBqEi2S-o_K2Bk5M27rQV=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 4, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': 'Nice prehispanic place, with more than 500 years old part of the ancient Mexican tribus sorrounding the aztec people, unfortunately the site museum and the pyramid was closed to public for remodeling, but can be admired from outside at least...', 'time': 1568481534}]

Saturday and Sunday there is a market at the entrance where you can buy organic vegetables and fruits and some arts and a fantastic breads.', 'time': 1581606655}, {'author_name': 'Diana Sencion', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/106379501176255386920/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GjfTYX_hmAYi6n7HngPDU8VvMSAB70jbs_Wo42_hw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba2', 'rating': 4, 'relative_time_description': '2 weeks ago', 'text': 'A bit lonely they oughtta place more surveillance at the less transited spots. column15:
[{'author_name': 'Italia Rodriguez', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/100875899663664723767/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-e5jmv-G7aVg/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/AMZuucnviLO7Fc7rAfzWvSBjvj_aOlwVpw/s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5/photo.jpg', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': 'Easy, informal and great Mexican food.

This place is cheap and informal, service is great but can get slow if the place is full. If you are not good for spicy food then order all the spice on the side. Specially the aguachile is amazing but crazy spicy. The torta ahogada is really good and they will give you a glove to eat it with your hands.

If full they will write your name on a wait list.', 'time': 1544321916}, {'author_name': 'Molly Wang', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/114020198155889608609/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GisGaBf7zYtVdz0LcpzgMKk1C2k13ze3koVb_n8bA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '3 years ago', 'text': "Definitely the top three Mexican dining experiences I've ever had. No words can describe how tasty the food is. Almost no empty table even though it is kind of in a quiet and subtle area that's rather off tourist track. I noticed it's very popular with locals and people from Guadalajara region.", 'time': 1492335479}, {'author_name': 'Mely de trotamundos', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/107402434963293717432/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GhabsykWBcTjJxh7fA-kjNg3GRPy3LhJf0zYHudxsc=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': 'My first time in this place and I really loved my meal. It's a cozy place and you can have a delicious drink named "Cantarito" it's a mix  of orange juice, lemon and tequila with salt.

And Pialadero Shrimps are so delicious. You will ask for more tortillas when you eat it.

Cost : medium
Flavor: legendary!!', 'time': 1565990229}, {'author_name': 'Kamlesh Chhetty', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/117812116701397851409/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Gg9KwqRR1g555o5kOyI0daFqzWhRL9Dy9m_8ekEUTU=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': 'Had lunch at this amazing small restaurant after a visit to the Chapultepec Castle. The place serves amazing sea food tacos and other authentic mexican cuisine. The servers are super helpful and very knowledgeable.
